00:14:05.920 --> 00:14:06.988
LAURA: Briorities.

00:14:06.988 --> 00:14:08.241
MATT: Taliesin!

00:14:08.241 --> 00:14:12.111
TRAVIS: We don't know if we have any further to go
from this crypt? Uncharted?

00:14:12.111 --> 00:14:17.582
LAURA: That's my thing! Oh, there's no drink in
my--

00:14:17.582 --> 00:14:18.969
LIAM: Well, go quick.

00:14:18.969 --> 00:14:20.553
MARISHA: Do it, it's fine. We're just starting.

00:14:20.553 --> 00:14:21.950
LIAM: I didn't want to touch it.

00:14:21.950 --> 00:14:25.163
TALIESIN: We've literally not had a conversation.

00:14:25.163 --> 00:14:26.504
MARISHA: We haven't done anything.

00:14:26.504 --> 00:14:28.031
SAM: All right, I'm going to charge in!

00:14:28.031 --> 00:14:31.428
(laughter)

00:14:31.428 --> 00:14:38.971
TRAVIS: I would like to take a vial of holy oil
that I have out of the Bag of Holding and keep it

00:14:38.971 --> 00:14:43.563
in my hand. Just out, so I don't have to get it
out.

00:14:43.563 --> 00:14:49.118
MARISHA: Grog, speaking of. How many health
potions do you have? I feel like we might need to

00:14:49.118 --> 00:14:50.308
redistribute.

00:14:50.308 --> 00:14:52.918
TRAVIS: I have a shitload. I never really use
them.

00:14:52.918 --> 00:14:54.550
MARISHA: You should do that.

00:14:54.550 --> 00:14:59.514
TRAVIS: I have two level awesome-- what are the
biggest ones?

00:14:59.514 --> 00:15:00.807
SAM: Greater?

00:15:00.807 --> 00:15:02.210
MATT: There's greater or superior.

00:15:02.210 --> 00:15:07.304
TRAVIS: I have two superior, one the top one, and
five of the low ones.

00:15:07.366 --> 00:15:09.355
TALIESIN: Can I take two of the low ones,
possibly?

00:15:09.355 --> 00:15:12.621
MATT: Superior would be the highest you've
received so far.

00:15:12.621 --> 00:15:14.047
TRAVIS: Okay then I have one of those.

00:15:14.047 --> 00:15:18.725
LIAM: I am all out of tricks, just about, so may I
please have a superior, Grog?

00:15:18.725 --> 00:15:21.528
TRAVIS: Oh boy, does everybody want a piece of this
pie?

00:15:21.528 --> 00:15:24.252
(laughter)

00:15:24.324 --> 00:15:26.653
TRAVIS: Well, what are you offering?

00:15:26.653 --> 00:15:34.535
LIAM: I'm offering safety for your facial hair for
perpetuity.

00:15:34.535 --> 00:15:36.403
TRAVIS: Nope. Give me something else.

00:15:36.403 --> 00:15:37.659
LIAM: Now it's in danger.

00:15:37.659 --> 00:15:43.616
MARISHA: How about safety for your life because
we'll be having your back and whatnot?

00:15:43.616 --> 00:15:48.898
TRAVIS: How could you have my back if it's on me?

00:15:48.898 --> 00:15:52.035
MARISHA: I'm going to let that one go.

00:15:52.035 --> 00:16:00.974
LIAM: I will let you flick me hard, hard in the
nads, should we survive.

00:16:01.043 --> 00:16:06.246
TRAVIS: How about you let me flick you hard in the
nads now and I'll give you a healing potion?

00:16:06.246 --> 00:16:08.377
LIAM: Can we take a short rest after that?

00:16:08.377 --> 00:16:10.577
(laughter)

00:16:10.577 --> 00:16:12.638
LAURA: What is happening? (laughs)

00:16:12.638 --> 00:16:16.207
TRAVIS: Just a little one. I won't even rage or
nothing. It'll just be a quick little tap on your

00:16:16.207 --> 00:16:17.533
walnut.

00:16:17.533 --> 00:16:19.279
LIAM: I will do this trade.

00:16:19.279 --> 00:16:25.145
TRAVIS: Yes! I kneel down and I get right up to
his bits.

00:16:25.145 --> 00:16:30.744
LIAM: Wait! I pull a stick out of my bag and I put
it in my mouth and I bite down very hard on it.

00:16:30.744 --> 00:16:39.077
SAM: I'm going to use Minor Illusion to create a
bull's eye right around his crotch. Concentric

00:16:39.077 --> 00:16:41.414
circles glowing.

00:16:41.414 --> 00:16:45.257
TRAVIS: And like the second grader I am trying to
write in cursive I have my tongue sticking out

00:16:45.257 --> 00:16:52.163
like-- and I shift from using the middle finger
down to the ring finger because we're being nice.

00:16:52.163 --> 00:16:54.933
And I go for-- are you right-handed?

00:16:54.933 --> 00:16:56.279
LIAM: Yeah.

00:16:56.279 --> 00:16:59.729
TRAVIS: I go for the left nut. (whack)

00:16:59.729 --> 00:17:01.838
LIAM: (groans)

00:17:01.838 --> 00:17:07.064
TRAVIS: Does he throw up?

00:17:07.064 --> 00:17:10.735
MATT: No, but you do take one point of damage.

00:17:10.735 --> 00:17:12.055
TRAVIS: Yes!

00:17:12.055 --> 00:17:16.350
LAURA: Just one? It's just a ring finger but it's
still a goliath.

00:17:16.350 --> 00:17:18.884
TRAVIS: Is there a little cough?

00:17:18.884 --> 00:17:23.315
MATT: Yeah, there's definitely enough of a
reaction to be worth your--

00:17:23.315 --> 00:17:27.389
LIAM: (hoarse) There's no sound. At all.

00:17:27.389 --> 00:17:31.225
TRAVIS: All right. I will give you one of the--
there's three different levels or just the two?

00:17:31.225 --> 00:17:36.094
MATT: Well, you have, you have common. Sorry, the
healing potion, the greater healing and the

00:17:36.094 --> 00:17:37.004
superior.

00:17:37.004 --> 00:17:39.089
LIAM: (hoarse) The good one, fucker.

00:17:39.089 --> 00:17:49.975
TRAVIS: I'll give you the greater. I give him a
greater. And Percy. I like it when you turn into

00:17:49.975 --> 00:17:55.383
the giant cloud thing so you don't have to take a
nutshot. Would you like a common or a greater?

00:17:55.383 --> 00:17:59.173
TALIESIN: Actually, if I could steal two commons,
just to be on the safe side.

00:17:59.173 --> 00:18:03.725
TRAVIS: Yeah, okay. I give him two common.

00:18:03.725 --> 00:18:07.902
TALIESIN: I offer the satisfaction of Vax knowing
that I got them for free.

00:18:07.902 --> 00:18:18.982
MATT: Cassandra also steps forward and says, "I
myself do not have any sort of potion of

00:18:18.982 --> 00:18:21.793
"protection. Does anyone have anything which they
could offer?"

00:18:21.793 --> 00:18:26.509
SAM: Yes, hello, hi. I look like your brother but
I'm shorter.

00:18:26.509 --> 00:18:29.349
MATT: Yes, that's right. By the way, everyone is
currently--

00:18:29.349 --> 00:18:31.169
TALIESIN: Currently everybody looks--

00:18:31.169 --> 00:18:36.406
MATT: Like either Percy or Cassandra, thanks to
Scanlan's Seeming, which is really awkward.

00:18:36.406 --> 00:18:41.454
LIAM: (hoarse) Are we going to hold this up for
when we go against the Briarwoods? I think it'll

00:18:41.454 --> 00:18:42.906
be confusing.

00:18:42.906 --> 00:18:50.727
SAM: Yeah, for them. You can have one of my
greater healing potions. Will that suffice?

00:18:50.727 --> 00:18:55.782
MATT: "Certainly, thank you." And she comes
forward and reaches out towards you and you have

00:18:55.782 --> 00:18:58.692
to reach up and put it in her hand because she's
reaching out towards a much taller figure.

00:18:58.692 --> 00:19:01.345
SAM: Oh, I look like a full-size Percy?

00:19:01.345 --> 00:19:04.999
MATT: A little larger. In between.

00:19:04.999 --> 00:19:05.842
SAM: Oh, cool.

00:19:05.842 --> 00:19:07.898
TALIESIN: I throw her one of my commons as well.

00:19:07.898 --> 00:19:13.878
TRAVIS: I have three commons, two greaters, and one
superior. I'm a walking medicine cabinet.

00:19:13.897 --> 00:19:15.194
MATT: You are.

00:19:15.194 --> 00:19:18.874
SAM: Speaking of looking like Percy and Cassandra.
Vex.

00:19:18.874 --> 00:19:20.240
LAURA: Huh?

00:19:20.240 --> 00:19:22.355
SAM: That is you, right?

00:19:22.355 --> 00:19:24.487
LAURA: That's me, yes, what?

00:19:24.487 --> 00:19:33.077
SAM: Vex, if you, if you look like Cassandra, you
could conceivably get in front of the Briarwoods

00:19:33.077 --> 00:19:38.522
without them knowing that it's an enemy for a
moment. Maybe long enough to fire off one of

00:19:38.522 --> 00:19:41.438
your-- don't you have some sort of sunbeam arrow
or something?

00:19:41.438 --> 00:19:48.241
LAURA: I have no sunbeam arrow, but I would like
to dip some arrows in some holy oil at this moment

00:19:48.241 --> 00:19:49.564
in time.

00:19:49.564 --> 00:19:50.745
MATT: All right.

00:19:50.745 --> 00:19:55.618
LAURA: I do have potentially an exploding holy
arrow.

00:19:55.618 --> 00:19:58.788
SAM: That would be pretty baller.

00:19:58.788 --> 00:20:00.990
MATT: Is this the one with the question mark?

00:20:00.990 --> 00:20:04.879
LAURA: No, this is a normal one, and then I have a
question mark, as well.

00:20:04.879 --> 00:20:06.387
MATT: Do you want to dip them both?

00:20:06.387 --> 00:20:07.699
LAURA: Fuck yes, I do.

00:20:07.699 --> 00:20:10.903
MATT: (laughs) Okay. You have two more uses of
your holy oil, I believe, right?

00:20:10.968 --> 00:20:17.236
LAURA: Yes. Well, no. Each thing takes three
arrows, so I can do six arrows altogether.

00:20:17.236 --> 00:20:19.237
MATT: You're using it all right now?

00:20:19.237 --> 00:20:21.449
TRAVIS: Will it wear off?

00:20:21.449 --> 00:20:22.938
MATT: It lasts for an hour.

00:20:22.938 --> 00:20:25.506
LAURA: Are we going to get there?

00:20:25.506 --> 00:20:28.239
SAM: I don't know. We could fight them in five
minutes.

00:20:28.239 --> 00:20:31.048
LAURA: I want to do it right before we walk in the
room, Matt.

00:20:31.048 --> 00:20:32.683
MATT: It's up to you. You can hold off.

00:20:32.683 --> 00:20:35.007
LIAM: We don't see a ziggurat yet.

00:20:35.007 --> 00:20:41.185
TALIESIN: Let's start making our way down there,
and I can't believe I'm going to say this, but

00:20:41.185 --> 00:20:43.689
we'll have Vax scout ahead.

00:20:43.689 --> 00:20:47.204
SAM: Don't do anything!

00:20:47.204 --> 00:20:52.104
LAURA: Don't do anything. Look. Don't touch.

00:20:52.104 --> 00:20:55.036
TALIESIN: Vax, we've discussed our new password.
Do you remember the new password?

00:20:55.036 --> 00:20:56.685
SAM: Which is?

00:20:56.685 --> 00:20:58.076
LAURA: Is there something different?

00:20:58.076 --> 00:20:59.670
LIAM: Is it Candyland? No, I don't remember.

00:20:59.670 --> 00:21:03.465
TALIESIN: It's now "Jenga, one one-thousand, two
one-thousand, three one-thousand, four

00:21:03.465 --> 00:21:07.734
"one-thousand, five one-thousand, six one-thousand,
seven one-thousand, eight one-thousand, nine

00:21:07.734 --> 00:21:09.353
"one-thousand, ten."

00:21:09.353 --> 00:21:13.559
LIAM: I just got flicked in the nuts. I'm not
doing that. I'll say jenga.

00:21:13.559 --> 00:21:16.488
LAURA: And then wait.

00:21:16.488 --> 00:21:24.579
LIAM: Yeah, I'll wait. So long as no more of your
siblings are in danger. I did do it for reasons.

00:21:24.579 --> 00:21:25.823
TALIESIN: We know.

00:21:25.823 --> 00:21:29.730
LIAM: You know because I told you.

00:21:29.730 --> 00:21:33.880
TALIESIN: Yes. I consider the matter settled.

00:21:33.880 --> 00:21:37.995
LIAM: I don't know exactly what was going to
happen, but I saw a blade against your sister's

00:21:37.995 --> 00:21:42.288
throat. I would hope you would do the same for my
sister if you were to see the same thing.

00:21:42.288 --> 00:21:43.322
TALIESIN: Yes.

00:21:43.322 --> 00:21:44.616
LAURA: Of course he would.

00:21:44.616 --> 00:21:47.071
TALIESIN: But mostly because I fear her.

00:21:47.071 --> 00:21:51.665
LIAM: Scanlan, back me up. If you were to turn
into some sort of three-horned beast and go

00:21:51.665 --> 00:21:59.360
running into a house full of enemies, we would
give him a similar talking-to, correct?

00:21:59.360 --> 00:22:02.431
SAM: That would never happen. I'm more measured
than all of you.

00:22:02.431 --> 00:22:06.098
TALIESIN: We don't actually believe that he will
listen to sense.

00:22:06.098 --> 00:22:07.942
SAM: I'm Percy.

00:22:07.942 --> 00:22:11.623
(laughter)

00:22:11.623 --> 00:22:15.670
TALIESIN: We just can't waste our breath, really.

00:22:15.670 --> 00:22:17.261
LIAM: Scanlan, shut up.

00:22:17.261 --> 00:22:20.510
TRAVIS: Attunement. How long does that take?

00:22:20.510 --> 00:22:21.817
MATT: A short rest.

00:22:21.817 --> 00:22:24.812
TALIESIN: This is going to be a very complicated
evening.

00:22:24.812 --> 00:22:26.094
TRAVIS: Should we take a short rest?

00:22:26.094 --> 00:22:27.263
TALIESIN: We just did.

00:22:27.263 --> 00:22:28.252
TRAVIS: We did?

00:22:28.252 --> 00:22:29.423
LAURA: Oh, we did!

00:22:29.423 --> 00:22:31.293
MATT: If you wanted to attune to something during
that short rest, you can.

00:22:31.293 --> 00:22:33.743
TRAVIS: Can I attune to Boots of Levitation?

00:22:33.743 --> 00:22:34.933
MATT: If you'd like to, yeah.

00:22:34.933 --> 00:22:36.021
TRAVIS: I would like to.

00:22:36.021 --> 00:22:36.950
MATT: Okay.

00:22:36.950 --> 00:22:39.065
LIAM: We just rested for 30 minutes?

00:22:39.065 --> 00:22:40.472
MATT: Roughly 30 minutes, yeah.

00:22:40.472 --> 00:22:42.754
LIAM: How would everyone feel about another seven
and a half hours?

00:22:42.754 --> 00:22:44.823
LAURA: We can't sleep in this--

00:22:44.823 --> 00:22:51.943
SAM: Our meal is still active, as well. We need
the benefits of that. Plus, there is a rebellion

00:22:51.943 --> 00:22:57.209
going on. It's been, what, an hour? Two hours?
They're probably mostly dead by now.

00:22:57.209 --> 00:22:59.901
MARISHA: That's possibly very true, actually.

00:22:59.901 --> 00:23:00.928
TALIESIN: Cassandra?

00:23:00.928 --> 00:23:02.010
MATT: "Yes?"

00:23:02.010 --> 00:23:05.664
TALIESIN: In your opinion, who's the more
dangerous target?

00:23:05.664 --> 00:23:15.679
MATT: She gets distant for a second, thinking, and
haphazardly pulls the hair over her ear and rubs

00:23:15.679 --> 00:23:22.722
her armor in a nervous way. Looks over out of the
side of her eyes to you and says, "They're both

00:23:22.722 --> 00:23:32.735
"dangerous for different reasons. Separately, Sylas
is dangerous because of his unnatural nature. I've

00:23:32.735 --> 00:23:40.785
"seen him turn arguments and opposing sides into
friendships in but an instant. He has some sort of

00:23:40.785 --> 00:23:46.879
"power over the mind of those he looks to. That in
itself is a danger, not to mention his other

00:23:46.879 --> 00:23:55.330
"capabilities. I've only seen him use it twice, but
that blade he carries is as dark as he is.

00:23:55.330 --> 00:24:04.494
"That being said, Lady Briarwood, Delilah, she
carries magic far more powerful than I've seen.

00:24:04.494 --> 00:24:12.544
"She on her own was able to create, run, and rule
each of these sentries that run about the entire

00:24:12.544 --> 00:24:21.314
"city. She had half of the entire castle staffed
with long-dead individuals. None questioned her.

00:24:21.314 --> 00:24:27.423
"I've never seen her in battle, but I sense there
is far more to her abilities than I've seen.

00:24:27.423 --> 00:24:37.956
"The two of them together are driven-- more so
than the affiliation to this Whispered One they

00:24:37.956 --> 00:24:46.820
"talk of, they're driven by one thing, and that's
their affection for each other. As long as they

00:24:46.820 --> 00:24:53.413
"are together, who knows what they're capable of."

00:24:53.413 --> 00:24:54.700
LAURA: So we split them up?

00:24:54.700 --> 00:24:56.723
TRAVIS: Yeah, we've got to divide and conquer this
shit.

00:24:56.723 --> 00:24:58.225
TALIESIN: If we can.

00:24:58.225 --> 00:25:01.029
TRAVIS: If we can.

00:25:01.029 --> 00:25:02.556
MARISHA: Cassandra.

00:25:02.556 --> 00:25:03.483
MATT: "Yes?"

00:25:03.483 --> 00:25:09.323
MARISHA: Has there been any instance where the two
have separated in the recent months, that you can

00:25:09.323 --> 00:25:12.043
imagine or remember?

00:25:12.125 --> 00:25:21.450
MATT: "Most of the ziggurat construction happens
during the evening, when Sylas is not resting. And

00:25:21.450 --> 00:25:31.690
"for the most part they journey together-- for the
past month, at least. No, I haven't seen them

00:25:31.690 --> 00:25:33.224
"apart, really."

00:25:33.224 --> 00:25:35.666
MARISHA: Can you think of any reason why they
would separate?

00:25:35.666 --> 00:25:41.058
MATT: "Not unless something in the sun required
their attention."

00:25:41.058 --> 00:25:45.478
MARISHA: Something sudden that required their
attention.

00:25:45.478 --> 00:25:46.683
MATT: "In the sun."

00:25:46.683 --> 00:25:48.080
MARISHA: In the sun?

00:25:48.080 --> 00:25:50.977
MATT: "Sylas does not appear to like being
outside."

00:25:50.977 --> 00:26:00.386
TRAVIS: Yeah, one thing. Do we want to take the
battle to them down here? Or do we want to try and

00:26:00.386 --> 00:26:03.056
lure them outside?

00:26:03.056 --> 00:26:07.062
LIAM: I think we would definitely prefer them
outside, but what would draw them out?

00:26:07.062 --> 00:26:08.506
I do not know.

00:26:08.506 --> 00:26:15.921
LAURA: What if we used Seeming and made one of us
seem like Lady Briarwood?

00:26:15.921 --> 00:26:18.411
TALIESIN: I think they would see through that.

00:26:18.411 --> 00:26:19.423
LAURA: Yes?

00:26:19.423 --> 00:26:22.159
TRAVIS: They saw through the disguise at the table
back in Emon.

00:26:22.159 --> 00:26:30.947
SAM: Just to point this out before we go in and
kill ourselves. We have evidence now. We could

00:26:30.947 --> 00:26:35.254
abandon this whole thing. Go back and fight our
day in court.

00:26:35.254 --> 00:26:41.198
TALIESIN: I want to see what they're building down
there. And I worry that it would be dangerous.

00:26:41.198 --> 00:26:46.493
MARISHA: Plus, we'd just abandon this entire
revolution that we caused?

00:26:46.493 --> 00:26:51.163
LIAM: People are putting their lives on the line.
Plus, Uriel is suspect now. He's been corrupted;

00:26:51.163 --> 00:26:54.734
he is not trustworthy. There's no point going back
to him.

00:26:54.734 --> 00:26:59.996
TALIESIN: I can't leave again until this is taken
care of.

00:26:59.996 --> 00:27:05.128
SAM: Right, that was a stupid suggestion,
Keyleth.

00:27:05.128 --> 00:27:10.878
TRAVIS: Keyleth, come on, we've got to stay.

00:27:10.878 --> 00:27:14.584
SAM: We're all Seemed differently; it's very
strange.

00:27:14.584 --> 00:27:18.150
TRAVIS: I'm really disappointed, Keyleth.

00:27:18.150 --> 00:27:28.203
LIAM: Cassandra, I want to say something a little
frank. I'm very happy that we've found you. I'm

00:27:28.203 --> 00:27:34.598
very happy that Percival and you have been
reunited. We have been burned very badly in the

00:27:34.598 --> 00:27:44.203
past by seeming allies. And I am sure you are in
your right mind. But past experience has taught us

00:27:44.203 --> 00:27:53.443
to be very careful. And we are all watching you.
For signs of corruption or control. I want to

00:27:53.443 --> 00:27:59.133
believe you are in control of your faculties. I do
not fully trust you are and I think, just letting

00:27:59.133 --> 00:28:08.312
you know that a knife could hit your back as soon
as the slightest misstep happened, is maybe enough

00:28:08.312 --> 00:28:11.968
to ensure some safety for this group.

00:28:11.968 --> 00:28:22.833
MATT: "Of course. It is true I have been living
here, at least in this castle with them, for the

00:28:22.833 --> 00:28:29.172
"past three years. Not, not of choice, of course.
And were I in your position,

00:28:29.172 --> 00:28:31.704
"would think the same."

00:28:31.704 --> 00:28:38.926
LIAM: According to Percival, they filled you with
arrows. What happened?

00:28:38.926 --> 00:28:52.280
MATT: "Well, I was near death. I was recovered by
the father that runs the temple of Pelor and a few

00:28:52.280 --> 00:29:02.053
"other individuals who had fled the city at the
time. I was as far-- as I was concerned, I was gone.

00:29:02.104 --> 00:29:13.538
"But they nursed me back to health. Slowly. Over
time. I was, for the better part, useless as an

00:29:13.538 --> 00:29:20.531
"individual for about six months. And even to this
day, I have a bit of a wheeze when I expend

