00:57:57.918 --> 00:58:05.237
bronze with bronze bars across to keep all the
various plates that were put up together. It's not

00:58:05.326 --> 00:58:09.016
one solid piece, it's multiple sheets that were
all bolted and put together

00:58:09.080 --> 00:58:10.678
to create solid walls.

00:58:10.678 --> 00:58:12.130
MARISHA: And the floor is bronze?

00:58:12.130 --> 00:58:13.728
MATT: The floor is bronze, as well.

00:58:13.728 --> 00:58:14.675
TALIESIN: The roof?

00:58:14.675 --> 00:58:19.295
MATT: The roof is not bronze. The roof is what
looks like solid whitestone.

00:58:19.295 --> 00:58:21.907
SAM: That don't look good.

00:58:21.907 --> 00:58:26.475
LIAM: Pike, Keyleth, do you make anything of
this?

00:58:26.475 --> 00:58:31.023
TRAVIS: Anyone want to go touch a wall?

00:58:31.023 --> 00:58:32.717
MARISHA: I don't even know.

00:58:32.717 --> 00:58:34.387
LIAM: You have no knowledge of--

00:58:34.387 --> 00:58:42.107
MARISHA: I'm not great with magic. I'm great with
nature, and I'm not great with dungeoneering or

00:58:42.107 --> 00:58:48.781
anything like that, either. Can I do some sort of
nature check to see if this is a quarry that we

00:58:48.781 --> 00:58:50.384
just walked into?

00:58:50.384 --> 00:58:52.471
LAURA: A conductor?

00:58:52.471 --> 00:58:55.990
MARISHA: A conductor, yeah. It's not really a
nature thing, though.

00:58:55.990 --> 00:58:59.733
MATT: Make an intelligence check.

00:58:59.733 --> 00:59:03.623
MARISHA: Okay. Not my forte. Oh, natural 20!

00:59:03.623 --> 00:59:05.913
LAURA: That's a beautiful thing.

00:59:05.913 --> 00:59:10.218
MATT: Okay. This bronze-colored material, and
you're not too familiar with a lot of metals, but

00:59:10.218 --> 00:59:16.997
it appears to be an alloy of some kind. It would
probably be a good conductor of electricity, if

00:59:16.997 --> 00:59:24.245
utilized in a way, for whatever purpose you're
unable to ascertain, but this metal is not

00:59:24.245 --> 00:59:32.450
indigenous to this region, meaning the whole area
of Tal'Dorei. This metal is usually imported from

00:59:32.450 --> 00:59:39.306
distant lands. It is not found or created
naturally in this area, to your knowledge.

00:59:39.306 --> 00:59:45.559
MARISHA: And would I gather any information on the
purpose of this room and what it's used for?

00:59:45.559 --> 00:59:55.602
MATT: Not with your experience, no. Gathering
about, though, as you all gather in this area and

00:59:55.602 --> 01:00:02.951
are looking around, you notice that the stonework
on the ceiling has two discolorations. Across the

01:00:02.951 --> 01:00:08.908
top of the ramp above you, there is a one-inch
discoloration, almost like there's a drawn line

01:00:08.908 --> 01:00:18.764
across the stone. At that height and this lack of
light, can't tell if it's just a marking or an

01:00:18.764 --> 01:00:23.340
actual change in material, and there's one
on the other side of the room across the way at

01:00:23.401 --> 01:00:25.350
the top of the other ramp.

01:00:25.350 --> 01:00:27.191
LAURA: It's a conductor room.

01:00:27.191 --> 01:00:30.752
MARISHA: Oh, we're too far away to see what it's
made out of?

01:00:30.752 --> 01:00:34.008
MATT: At this distance and in this low light, it's
hard to tell. You can see that there's a

01:00:34.008 --> 01:00:37.254
discoloration or change, but it is a consistent
band across the top.

01:00:37.254 --> 01:00:38.630
SAM: Should we send some light up there?

01:00:38.630 --> 01:00:39.667
LAURA: How high are the ceilings?

01:00:39.667 --> 01:00:43.399
TRAVIS: I have darkvision at a range of 60 feet.
