the floor there is a small variation in the color.

01:01:29.736 --> 01:01:38.715
You see what looks like a small almost oval-type
smooth button. Or some sort of a strange object

01:01:38.715 --> 01:01:40.343
that is embedded in the floor.

01:01:40.343 --> 01:01:42.893
LAURA: Should I try to shoot it? When none of us
are in the room?

01:01:42.893 --> 01:01:47.692
SAM: I would just try to-- oh yeah. That's
interesting.

01:01:47.692 --> 01:01:49.436
(laughter)

01:01:49.436 --> 01:01:54.978
LIAM: That will probably tell us what this room is
about. I worry a little about alerting people on

01:01:54.978 --> 01:01:59.738
the other side of the room, but it feels dangerous
to go through here.

01:01:59.738 --> 01:02:03.651
TRAVIS: Oh man.

01:02:03.651 --> 01:02:05.133
LAURA: That's true.

01:02:05.133 --> 01:02:08.305
MARISHA: There's no vents? There's no ventilation
shaft, there's nothing?

01:02:08.305 --> 01:02:12.205
TRAVIS: The roof is flat, or is it coned?

01:02:12.205 --> 01:02:15.619
MATT: The roof is flat from what you can tell.
It's a giant box, it's just the walls

01:02:15.619 --> 01:02:16.705
and the floor.

01:02:16.705 --> 01:02:17.826
TRAVIS: Whitestone ceiling?

01:02:17.826 --> 01:02:21.462
MATT: The whitestone ceiling and the rest of it is
all this bronze material with a ramp that goes

01:02:21.462 --> 01:02:24.855
down towards the bottom and the ramp that goes on
the other end, with the two platforms, where you

01:02:24.855 --> 01:02:26.852
enter and where the other door across the way is.

01:02:26.852 --> 01:02:29.253
LAURA: So, can we clear out and I'll try to shoot
it?

01:02:29.253 --> 01:02:30.373
MARISHA: Sure.

01:02:30.373 --> 01:02:31.454
TALIESIN: See what happens.

01:02:31.518 --> 01:02:34.257
LAURA: Okay. I'll do that.

01:02:34.310 --> 01:02:39.252
MATT: So all of you step back out into the
hallway, your cluster of Percys and Cassandras.

01:02:39.252 --> 01:02:43.815
LIAM: I step one foot behind Cassandra Number
Two.

01:02:43.815 --> 01:02:50.046
MATT: All right. Go ahead and pull your arrow. You
aim carefully from just outside the doorway.

01:02:50.046 --> 01:02:53.289
MARISHA: You've got this.

01:02:53.289 --> 01:02:54.955
LAURA: Do I add my attack to it?

01:02:54.955 --> 01:02:56.649
MATT: Yes, you add your attack bonus.

01:02:56.649 --> 01:02:57.842
LAURA: 27.

01:02:57.842 --> 01:03:06.829
MATT: 27. So you release the arrow. Perfect hit.
On point. It strikes whatever this strange object

01:03:06.829 --> 01:03:11.746
is embedded in the floor. It hits and slightly
ricochets and splinters as an arrow would when it

01:03:11.746 --> 01:03:14.559
hits a hard surface. No seeming reaction.

01:03:14.559 --> 01:03:16.029
LAURA: It did nothing!

01:03:16.029 --> 01:03:22.209
TALIESIN: I'm going to try something. First of
all, does the construct of this at all remind me

01:03:22.209 --> 01:03:23.387
of anything?

01:03:23.387 --> 01:03:29.896
MATT: No, actually. Most of this tunnel structure
did not exist when you lived here. This has all

01:03:29.896 --> 01:03:36.454
been either re-discovered or created since you
left Whitestone.

01:03:36.454 --> 01:03:42.834
TALIESIN: I'm going to take my sword and I'm going
to go into the room and I'm going to lay my sword

01:03:42.834 --> 01:03:51.128
on the ground. Copper is a conductor. I'm having
that thought. I'm going to try and slide my sword

01:03:51.128 --> 01:03:56.918
towards the center of the room and see if I can
cause a short. With the piece of metal and get a

01:03:56.918 --> 01:04:00.821
positive and negative charge to hit and see if I
can get a reaction.

01:04:00.821 --> 01:04:08.626
MATT: All righty. As you step down to the bottom
of the slope as it meets the bottom, and there is

01:04:08.626 --> 01:04:14.983
an open area in the center of the floor now, about
a 20-foot area width between the two ramps. You're

01:04:14.983 --> 01:04:20.692
now at the bottom of the ramp. You take the sword
and you let it scatter across. And there are

01:04:20.692 --> 01:04:25.944
imperfections in the floor so it skips as it moves
and such and eventually slides to a stop. No

01:04:25.944 --> 01:04:31.431
effect. But you do get a better look at what this
thing is embedded in the floor. You not having

01:04:31.431 --> 01:04:34.058
darkvision, though, you would have to have a light
source for this.

01:04:34.058 --> 01:04:35.176
TALIESIN: I had a torch.

01:04:35.176 --> 01:04:39.934
MATT: Yeah. You bring your torch forward and you
look over. It looks like a smooth gem, like an

01:04:39.934 --> 01:04:46.080
opal or some sort of whitish opaque gem that is
embedded in the ground in the center.

01:04:46.080 --> 01:04:49.486
LAURA: The Arkenstone! Definitely.

01:04:49.486 --> 01:04:51.017
(laughter)

01:04:51.017 --> 01:04:55.513
TALIESIN: And it's not translucent? It's like an
opal-like stone?

01:04:55.513 --> 01:05:00.810
MATT: It's an opal-like stone, about that big that
is embedded in the bronze floor. There's actually

01:05:00.810 --> 01:05:07.138
a small, metal bronze band that encases it, wraps
around it that-- It wasn't just pressed into it; it

01:05:07.214 --> 01:05:09.496
was put there intentionally.

01:05:09.496 --> 01:05:11.120
TRAVIS: I say we smash it!

01:05:11.120 --> 01:05:13.511
TALIESIN: I say we remove it, at the very least.
See what happens.

01:05:13.511 --> 01:05:15.389
LAURA: Can you disarm it?

01:05:15.389 --> 01:05:17.196
MARISHA: All of those sound like bad ideas.

01:05:17.196 --> 01:05:18.261
SAM: Terrible.

01:05:18.261 --> 01:05:19.728
TALIESIN: Does anybody have a good idea?

01:05:19.728 --> 01:05:21.024
SAM: Why don't we just walk past it?

01:05:21.115 --> 01:05:22.947
MARISHA: I'm with Scanlan. I say we just go.

01:05:22.947 --> 01:05:28.071
TALIESIN: In the absence of good ideas, bad ideas,
I think, are always reasonable.

01:05:28.071 --> 01:05:31.602
MARISHA: But maybe mine and Scanlan's is a good
idea.

01:05:31.602 --> 01:05:34.928
LAURA: Maybe just try to get through the room.
Some of us stay on one side, some other people go

01:05:34.928 --> 01:05:36.921
through and see what happens to the first person.

01:05:36.921 --> 01:05:43.587
LIAM: So long as you all will pick me up off the
floor, I would like to skirt the entire side of

01:05:43.587 --> 01:05:44.425
the room.

01:05:44.425 --> 01:05:45.626
LAURA: And just go through the other door?

01:05:45.626 --> 01:05:47.038
LIAM: See if I can make it to the other door.

01:05:47.038 --> 01:05:47.943
MATT: All right.

01:05:47.943 --> 01:05:52.184
LIAM: Please help me if I fall down. And I start
along.

01:05:52.184 --> 01:05:53.433
TRAVIS: After a good giggle.

01:05:53.433 --> 01:05:59.458
MATT: As the floor ramps down towards the center,
you follow it along the wall. Making your way

01:05:59.458 --> 01:06:05.982
across, looking. You notice as you go across the
wall, there are three more of these same opal

01:06:05.982 --> 01:06:08.058
stones embedded in the wall about shoulder
height.

01:06:08.058 --> 01:06:09.036
LIAM: In the wall?

01:06:09.036 --> 01:06:10.412
MATT: In the wall as you go across.

01:06:10.412 --> 01:06:12.740
LIAM: Is it one in the middle and then one in the
center of each wall?

01:06:12.740 --> 01:06:14.484
MATT: On just on your wall--

01:06:14.484 --> 01:06:15.664
LIAM: Just on my wall?

01:06:15.664 --> 01:06:19.081
MATT: Just on your wall, there's three along the
way. There's one in the center of the room in line

01:06:19.081 --> 01:06:23.612
with the central opal, and there's two to the
sides of it about four feet from each other.

01:06:23.612 --> 01:06:27.798
LIAM: I've gone into a crouch, so I'm very low,
butt dragging along the floor and just sort of--

01:06:27.798 --> 01:06:30.561
MATT: So you notice that. You skirt underneath.

01:06:30.561 --> 01:06:32.474
LIAM: Leaning my back against the wall.

01:06:32.474 --> 01:06:37.546
MATT: Okay. They pass overhead. As you make your
way underneath the three opals in this part of the

01:06:37.546 --> 01:06:41.090
wall. Making your way up the other ramp to the
other side.

01:06:41.090 --> 01:06:42.360
LIAM: Continued perception check?

01:06:42.360 --> 01:06:43.866
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:06:43.866 --> 01:06:47.390
LIAM: Yeah. 23.

01:06:47.390 --> 01:06:55.665
MATT: Okay. You make your way up this side looking
about on the floor. Nothing seems to happen,

01:06:55.665 --> 01:07:02.059
nothing catches your eye. You get onto this upper
platform, and there is the door there

01:07:02.059 --> 01:07:03.554
in front of you.

01:07:03.554 --> 01:07:08.769
LIAM: I check for traps on the door. That is a
24.

01:07:08.769 --> 01:07:12.916
MATT: The door does not appear to be trapped.

01:07:12.916 --> 01:07:14.008
LIAM: Or locked?

01:07:14.008 --> 01:07:18.965
MATT: Does not appear to be locked. It does not
seem to have a mechanism for opening other than if

01:07:18.965 --> 01:07:20.466
you wanted to try and push.

01:07:20.466 --> 01:07:21.647
TRAVIS: Go through it!

01:07:21.647 --> 01:07:29.850
SAM: No, let's get out of here. They wouldn't
build a huge bronze trap room within their castle.

01:07:29.850 --> 01:07:36.112
No, they've lived here in peace for five years.
What would they need this for? This has some sort

01:07:36.112 --> 01:07:38.633
of use for their magic. This is not a trap room.

01:07:38.633 --> 01:07:42.669
TRAVIS: We should try to remove one of the
stones.

01:07:42.669 --> 01:07:48.685
MARISHA: Question. Are the stones mathematically
adjacent to each other?

01:07:48.685 --> 01:07:51.270
Do they appear to be lined up?

01:07:51.270 --> 01:07:55.548
MATT: Well as you can tell, there's the one in the
center of the middle of the floor. Then there's

01:07:55.548 --> 01:08:03.430
one on the wall that he walked across, and as you
to the other wall, there are another

01:08:03.497 --> 01:08:05.420
matching set of three on both walls.

01:08:05.420 --> 01:08:06.546
MARISHA: And they're all lined up.

01:08:06.546 --> 01:08:08.967
MATT: And they're all lined up. There's the two in
the center of the room that match the one in the

01:08:08.967 --> 01:08:11.829
floor and then there's one to each side of that
about four feet apart.

01:08:11.829 --> 01:08:14.178
MARISHA: Okay. I'm going to walk in a little bit.
Are there any on the ceiling?

01:08:14.178 --> 01:08:19.425
MATT: Looking up. Make a perception check.

01:08:19.641 --> 01:08:21.043
MARISHA: Natural one.

01:08:21.043 --> 01:08:23.928
MATT: You get lost in the beauty of the
structure.

01:08:23.928 --> 01:08:25.361
(laughter)

01:08:25.361 --> 01:08:27.329
TALIESIN: I was going to look to see if there was
one matching the one on the floor.

01:08:27.329 --> 01:08:28.346
MATT: Okay.

01:08:28.346 --> 01:08:30.324
MARISHA: That's good metal! Good craftsmanship,
damn.

01:08:30.324 --> 01:08:33.872
TALIESIN: Yeah, that's good, that's a 27.

01:08:33.961 --> 01:08:43.348
MATT: Looking up, no. The ceiling is just smooth
whitestone. You, pushing the door-- it doesn't

01:08:43.437 --> 01:08:52.617
open. It is solid stone, and as you push and look,
you can see there's no hinges. Looking at where it

01:08:52.617 --> 01:08:58.859
meets the wall, it looks like it slid down into a
groove. It's actually a door that would lift or

01:08:58.859 --> 01:09:03.574
sink. It slides. Some way, shape, or form, it
slides into place.

01:09:03.574 --> 01:09:07.743
LIAM: Grog doesn't have an earring, does he?

01:09:07.743 --> 01:09:08.873
TRAVIS: Yeah, I do.

01:09:08.873 --> 01:09:12.284
MARISHA: I think we all have earrings right now.

01:09:12.284 --> 01:09:13.415
LIAM: Grog?

01:09:13.415 --> 01:09:15.988
LAURA: He's right there! Just fucking talk to
him.

01:09:15.988 --> 01:09:21.948
LIAM: He's across an 80-foot room! I'm not going
to shout down here. There's a big heavy thing.

01:09:21.948 --> 01:09:23.137
TRAVIS: Yeah?

01:09:23.137 --> 01:09:26.422
LIAM: And you're the best you are at what you do.
Do you think you could shimmy along on your tummy,

01:09:26.422 --> 01:09:32.300
along a side wall? Don't stand up because there's
gems in the walls along the way and I don't know

01:09:32.300 --> 01:09:37.287
what they do, so stay low, please? And come meet
me up here.

01:09:37.287 --> 01:09:43.328
TRAVIS: I just kinda want to walk across the room.

01:09:43.392 --> 01:09:44.568
LAURA: Do it.

01:09:44.568 --> 01:09:45.617
TRAVIS: I walk across the room.

01:09:45.617 --> 01:09:52.208
MATT: Okay. So you watch in horror as Grog just
strolls full, upright back, hammer in his arm with

01:09:52.208 --> 01:09:58.475
a big grin on his face. Looking like a really
burly Percy. I have to keep reminding myself. It's

01:09:58.475 --> 01:10:00.574
a very curious visual every time.

01:10:00.574 --> 01:10:02.276
TRAVIS: I adjust my amazing spectacles.

01:10:02.276 --> 01:10:06.102
MATT: Passes right through the center of where
these opals are aligned across from each other.

01:10:06.102 --> 01:10:11.903
Seeming no effect. Makes his way up the ramp to
where you are on the opposite side of the room.

01:10:11.903 --> 01:10:13.727
TALIESIN: I'm going to go get my sword.

01:10:13.727 --> 01:10:22.049
MARISHA: Well, hang on, while Grog goes and lifts
the thing. While Grog does that, do I have any

01:10:22.049 --> 01:10:26.676
idea where we are geographically in the city,
underground?

01:10:26.676 --> 01:10:34.387
MATT: Keeping track best you can, you gather
you're about a quarter-mile from the center of the

01:10:34.387 --> 01:10:39.546
city, from the square where the Sun Tree is. It's
a quarter-mile south of you.

01:10:39.546 --> 01:10:41.311
MARISHA: So probably not under the Sun Tree.

01:10:41.311 --> 01:10:42.399
MATT: Currently, no.

01:10:42.399 --> 01:10:43.348
MARISHA: Okay.

01:10:43.348 --> 01:10:47.455
TRAVIS: Walking up to the door, does it look like
I can get any purchase with my little

01:10:47.455 --> 01:10:48.485
finger-bits?

01:10:48.485 --> 01:10:50.056
MATT: Nope. It is flush with the ground.

01:10:50.056 --> 01:10:52.996
TRAVIS: I have a pickaxe that I picked up before
we left.

01:10:52.996 --> 01:10:54.011
MATT: Okay.

01:10:54.011 --> 01:10:57.844
TRAVIS: Can I swing it at the bottom and try and
find some purchase under the door?

01:10:57.844 --> 01:11:07.406
MATT: You could try. Yeah, go ahead. Go ahead and
roll an athletics check to see if you can manage

01:11:07.406 --> 01:11:09.255
to get anything in there.

01:11:09.255 --> 01:11:12.384
TRAVIS: Okay. 16?

01:11:12.384 --> 01:11:17.752
MATT: 16? Okay, so you take it and you try to get
a few whacks in, it's not really getting in there.

01:11:17.752 --> 01:11:19.425
Make a strength check.

01:11:19.425 --> 01:11:25.573
TRAVIS: Shit. Fuck. Nine?

01:11:25.573 --> 01:11:33.717
MATT: Nine? You swing with the pickaxe downward
for a full angry Grog-swing, and as you hit, you

01:11:33.717 --> 01:11:39.196
feel the pickaxe move further than it did before,
and for a split-second your brain's like, great!

01:11:39.196 --> 01:11:42.462
And then you look down and notice that the actual
handle of the pickaxe has shattered from the

01:11:42.462 --> 01:11:44.372
impact, broken in two.

01:11:44.372 --> 01:11:46.685
TALIESIN: We're not thinking about this clearly.

01:11:46.685 --> 01:11:48.450
TRAVIS: Thinking?

01:11:48.450 --> 01:11:53.604
SAM: We've been beaten by doors before, but
goddamn it, we're not going to be beaten today. I

01:11:53.604 --> 01:11:59.581
go to the center of the room and I find that
little button thing and I'm going to press it.

01:11:59.581 --> 01:12:00.674
TALIESIN: Good.

01:12:00.674 --> 01:12:05.947
MATT: Okay. You go and press your thumb down on
it. It doesn't move, it doesn't shift. It doesn't

01:12:05.947 --> 01:12:11.518
give way at all, it just stays in place. As you
pull your thumb away, though, you notice that the

01:12:11.518 --> 01:12:16.314
gem has a very soft, faint white glow to it, and a
second after you pull your thumb

01:12:16.314 --> 01:12:17.575
away it fades back.

01:12:17.575 --> 01:12:19.870
TALIESIN: I walk over to the wall and touch one of
the other gems.

01:12:19.870 --> 01:12:20.919
LAURA: I touch another one.

01:12:20.919 --> 01:12:22.346
MARISHA: I touch another one!

01:12:22.346 --> 01:12:26.492
MATT: You guys all place your hands against the
opals on the sides, and checking as you pull your

01:12:26.492 --> 01:12:30.240
hand away, the opals glow brightly white again,
and then fade.

01:12:30.240 --> 01:12:31.448
MARISHA: Pike.

01:12:31.448 --> 01:12:33.727
TRAVIS: I am Captain Planet. No.

01:12:33.727 --> 01:12:35.546
LAURA: Touch one of the stones, Grog.

01:12:35.546 --> 01:12:37.028
TRAVIS: I run over and touch a stone.

01:12:37.028 --> 01:12:38.265
LIAM: I touch one, too.

01:12:38.265 --> 01:12:43.883
MATT: (laughs) All right, so that's three on one
side, three on the other, who's got the middle

01:12:43.883 --> 01:12:45.516
one? You got the middle one?

01:12:45.516 --> 01:12:46.666
SAM: I'm in the middle.

01:12:46.666 --> 01:12:47.495
ASHLEY: I got one.

01:12:47.495 --> 01:12:48.525
LAURA: Trinket.

01:12:48.525 --> 01:12:51.978
SAM: Yeah, can Trinket touch a stone? Or
Cassandra. Cassandra, make yourself useful for

01:12:51.978 --> 01:12:53.133
Christ's sake.

01:12:53.133 --> 01:12:54.808
LIAM: Who's Christ?

01:12:54.978 --> 01:12:59.343
SAM: My friend back in Gnomolia, where I'm from.

01:12:59.409 --> 01:13:01.420
MATT: Pike, are you grabbing a stone or not?

01:13:01.574 --> 01:13:02.663
ASHLEY: What was that?

01:13:02.663 --> 01:13:04.074
MATT: Are you touching a stone or not?

01:13:04.074 --> 01:13:05.115
ASHLEY: Yes, I am.

01:13:05.115 --> 01:13:12.409
MATT: Okay. That's seven. So three on one side,
three on the other, Trinket keeping there with

01:13:12.409 --> 01:13:20.046
anticipation up next to you. Pike, you put your
hand on the final stone. A moment passes.

01:13:20.046 --> 01:13:22.929
LAURA: This is totally going to work.

01:13:22.929 --> 01:13:24.214
MARISHA: Come on, guys.

01:13:24.214 --> 01:13:26.151
MATT: Doesn't seem to have an immediate effect.

01:13:26.151 --> 01:13:27.203
SAM: Wait.

01:13:27.203 --> 01:13:31.668
MARISHA: No, maybe if we all think about the
strength of our friendship and bond together.

01:13:31.668 --> 01:13:34.513
LIAM: This is our time now!

01:13:34.513 --> 01:13:39.948
SAM: Hold on, as much as I love Pike, you aren't a
real person right now.

01:13:39.948 --> 01:13:42.308
Maybe we should swap out Pike.

01:13:42.308 --> 01:13:46.685
MATT: Yeah, Pike, as you pull your hand away, the
stone is glowing. And it fades momentarily after

01:13:46.685 --> 01:13:47.634
you put your hand there.

01:13:47.634 --> 01:13:49.410
SAM: Oh, it does work. Never mind, Pike. I love
you.

01:13:49.410 --> 01:13:50.549
ASHLEY: But are there any on the ceiling?

01:13:50.549 --> 01:13:52.012
MATT: Nothing on the ceiling.

01:13:52.012 --> 01:13:53.466
LAURA: Do we see any missing ones?

01:13:53.466 --> 01:13:56.099
MATT: Roll a perception check.

01:13:56.099 --> 01:14:02.621
LAURA: 21.

01:14:02.621 --> 01:14:10.278
MATT: 21. Okay. Looking about, Cassandra actually,
who's up towards the far ramp, seems to notice

01:14:10.278 --> 01:14:14.410
something and walks up to where the door is,
looking at the foot of the door. She moves her

01:14:14.410 --> 01:14:18.608
hand out of the way and presses her hand down on a
hidden eighth opal.

01:14:18.608 --> 01:14:19.952
LAURA: Nice!

01:14:19.952 --> 01:14:25.738
MATT: At which point there's a shift, a sound of
stone shifting loudly, and those bars across the

01:14:25.738 --> 01:14:37.558
ceiling, the green bars? Let loose a bit of dust,
and two large walls of green glass (impact noise)

01:14:37.558 --> 01:14:43.348
slam downward to the front and back of you,
locking all seven of you into the center of this

01:14:43.415 --> 01:14:44.803
bronze room.

01:14:44.803 --> 01:14:46.172
LIAM: Where's Cassandra?

01:14:46.172 --> 01:14:51.071
MATT: Cassandra's on the other side of the green
wall on the far end of the room.

01:14:51.071 --> 01:14:54.838
MARISHA: Can we hear each other through the
glass?

