01:33:54.455 --> 01:33:59.575
each progressive amount of you that is currently
submerged. You strike down, thankfully the liquid

01:33:59.575 --> 01:34:02.819
isn't too thick and you still manage to push
through most of your force, your magical blade

01:34:02.819 --> 01:34:07.502
guiding it down to the gem, and you feel it
(crack) beneath you. Crack and shatter.

01:34:07.502 --> 01:34:08.930
SAM: One down.

01:34:08.930 --> 01:34:10.058
MATT: One down.

01:34:10.058 --> 01:34:11.245
TALIESIN: We have two down.

01:34:11.245 --> 01:34:13.027
MATT: Oh, sorry. Two down, between the two of
you.

01:34:13.027 --> 01:34:15.499
MARISHA: Do there appear to be any weak points in
the metal anywhere?

01:34:15.499 --> 01:34:19.853
MATT: Not that you can tell at a quick glance.
Everything's pretty solid, and it's been used

01:34:19.853 --> 01:34:25.631
multiple times, and you see now that this room is
used, and what they used to melt down all the

01:34:25.631 --> 01:34:30.684
whitestone into the residuum component during
the construction of the ziggurat. Some of the

01:34:30.756 --> 01:34:36.640
notes mentioned it, Ripley mentioned a little bit,
but this-- this is bad.

01:34:36.640 --> 01:34:38.439
SAM: Acid melts whitestone?

01:34:38.439 --> 01:34:40.201
MATT: It appears to, yeah.

01:34:40.201 --> 01:34:42.728
SAM: The whitestone on the ceiling?

01:34:42.728 --> 01:34:49.492
MARISHA: The acid that's filling in melts that?
