01:34:57.684 --> 01:35:05.364
little hard for you to do that in enough of amount
to actually do any serious effect, unfortunately.

01:35:05.364 --> 01:35:07.359
LAURA: Does the acid go through glass?

01:35:07.359 --> 01:35:12.546
TALIESIN: No. Glass is specifically how you
contain acid.

01:35:12.546 --> 01:35:21.202
LAURA: Can I take one of my glass vials that I
have and try to get some acid and put it up on the

01:35:21.202 --> 01:35:22.332
ceiling?

01:35:22.332 --> 01:35:25.061
MATT: You can definitely fill it up, but it's a
ways up.

01:35:25.061 --> 01:35:26.404
LAURA: I'm flying.

01:35:26.404 --> 01:35:27.413
MATT: Oh, yeah!

01:35:27.413 --> 01:35:28.472
SAM: You're flying?

01:35:28.472 --> 01:35:30.470
LAURA: I took a flying potion to get out of the
acid.

01:35:30.470 --> 01:35:36.514
MATT: So you bolt down, and it's still pouring in.
The ice on the other side, by the way, shatters as

01:35:36.514 --> 01:35:40.377
it now continues to pour in from both sides,
doubling the speed at which it's filling.

01:35:40.377 --> 01:35:42.278
TALIESIN: I'm taking my three shots at the next
gem.

01:35:42.278 --> 01:35:43.446
MATT: Go for it.

01:35:43.446 --> 01:35:45.533
LAURA: Am I high enough that I can see where the
pipes are coming in at?

01:35:45.533 --> 01:35:46.456
MATT: Yeah.

01:35:46.456 --> 01:35:50.179
LAURA: So I could potentially grab hold of one of
the pipes on the ceiling and try to move it?

01:35:50.179 --> 01:35:51.225
MATT: You could, yeah.

01:35:51.225 --> 01:35:54.512
LAURA: I want to try to grab hold of one of those
pipes and aim it toward the ceiling,

01:35:54.512 --> 01:35:55.730
if I can move it.

01:35:55.730 --> 01:35:57.343
MATT: Okay. We'll get to that in just a moment.

01:35:57.343 --> 01:36:00.424
TALIESIN: The first one was 21.

01:36:00.424 --> 01:36:01.464
MATT: Okay.

01:36:01.464 --> 01:36:05.840
TALIESIN: And then the second shot-- dear god, it
hits.

01:36:05.922 --> 01:36:07.586
MARISHA: He rolled an 18.

01:36:07.586 --> 01:36:09.361
TALIESIN: 18, 20, 30.

01:36:09.361 --> 01:36:10.503
MATT: All right.

01:36:10.503 --> 01:36:12.529
TALIESIN: Third shot is 26.

01:36:12.529 --> 01:36:15.231
MATT: All right. All three hit. Roll damage for
all of those.

01:36:15.231 --> 01:36:19.830
TALIESIN: That's 14.

01:36:19.830 --> 01:36:21.274
MATT: Okay.

01:36:21.274 --> 01:36:28.950
TALIESIN: 11 for the second shot, and 14 for the
third shot.

01:36:28.950 --> 01:36:34.487
MATT: All right. (three gun blasts) You unload
three bullets in a row. You see, before even the

01:36:34.487 --> 01:36:40.985
last one hits, the opal itself (crash) shatters
off from the final blast, leaving the vacuous hole

01:36:40.985 --> 01:36:47.490
where it once was embedded in the wall. Vex, you
move up and you grab onto it. You begin to try and

01:36:47.490 --> 01:36:51.535
shove it, and even with your Fly spell, you don't
have a lot of weight behind it, so you put

01:36:51.535 --> 01:36:58.003
yourself up against the wall, find some leverage
against one of the metal bars that holds the metal

01:36:58.003 --> 01:37:01.656
plates in place, and you lift. I need you to make
a strength check.

01:37:01.656 --> 01:37:04.422
LAURA: I'm the weakest!

01:37:04.422 --> 01:37:05.821
LIAM: Not this time.

01:37:05.821 --> 01:37:09.503
LAURA: Do I get advantage?

01:37:09.503 --> 01:37:11.915
MATT: Not for this, you don't.

01:37:11.915 --> 01:37:13.339
LAURA: Damn it.

01:37:13.339 --> 01:37:15.280
MARISHA: Can I help her out?

01:37:15.280 --> 01:37:22.380
LAURA: Get those Boots of Levitation. Get them on!
Fly up, because I just rolled a fucking zero.

01:37:22.380 --> 01:37:25.376
Literally a zero.

01:37:25.376 --> 01:37:36.122
MATT: You grab it, and as you're holding onto it,
it's pliable. It's not a very hard metal, but you

01:37:36.122 --> 01:37:39.947
just don't have the strength, physically, in this
one attempt to bend it in any way,

01:37:39.947 --> 01:37:41.085
shape, or form.

01:37:41.085 --> 01:37:43.602
LAURA: Can I use my dagger that I have?

01:37:43.602 --> 01:37:49.846
MARISHA: Hold on. Use your dagger, and seeing what
she's doing, I'm going to cast my Heat Metal spell

01:37:49.846 --> 01:37:52.436
on it, and start heating and melting it.

01:37:52.436 --> 01:37:53.723
LAURA: The pipe?

01:37:53.723 --> 01:37:54.852
MARISHA: Yeah.

01:37:54.852 --> 01:37:59.974
MATT: So you reach over and cast Heat Metal. The
pipe section sticks out about two and a half feet

01:37:59.974 --> 01:38:04.001
from this point, so you can grasp it there. You
look over and see the metal itself beginning to

01:38:04.001 --> 01:38:05.442
heat up, beginning to glow.

01:38:05.442 --> 01:38:07.007
LAURA: Can I try to lift it?

01:38:07.007 --> 01:38:08.343
MATT: You can.

01:38:08.343 --> 01:38:12.059
LAURA: I wrap my hands in cloth, and then I do
it.

01:38:12.059 --> 01:38:15.282
MATT: Okay, so you take your cloak and wrap it up.
Good call. What are you doing?

01:38:15.282 --> 01:38:25.024
SAM: I say to everybody, when Cassandra put her
hand on the hidden gem outside the glass, it

01:38:25.024 --> 01:38:26.580
closed the doors, right?

01:38:26.580 --> 01:38:27.551
LAURA: Yeah.

01:38:27.551 --> 01:38:31.663
SAM: If I put my hands on that while you're
putting your hands on the inside gems, it might

01:38:31.663 --> 01:38:33.279
open the doors, right?

01:38:33.279 --> 01:38:34.638
LAURA: Potentially, but we destroyed them.

01:38:34.638 --> 01:38:35.635
MARISHA: We destroyed two.

01:38:35.635 --> 01:38:38.682
SAM: Yeah, but maybe if we do the other ones, it
would still work? Is it worth a shot?

01:38:38.682 --> 01:38:40.040
LAURA: Can you Dimension Door?

01:38:40.040 --> 01:38:41.453
SAM: I could.

