01:39:20.513 --> 01:39:26.423
SAM: Or I could go outside the stone door and see
if there's any more buttons out there to press.

01:39:26.423 --> 01:39:29.897
MARISHA: I think going outside is a good idea. Go
outside.

01:39:29.897 --> 01:39:31.663
MATT: Grog, do you want to make your strikes?

01:39:31.663 --> 01:39:33.150
SAM: Pike, shall I take you with me?

01:39:33.150 --> 01:39:34.277
ASHLEY: Yes, let's go!

01:39:34.277 --> 01:39:35.618
LAURA: Go.

01:39:35.618 --> 01:39:40.243
SAM: The best thing I've ever heard. You and me
in a room alone together.

01:39:40.269 --> 01:39:45.194
TRAVIS: 13, 17, and 13.

01:39:45.194 --> 01:39:46.773
MATT: First two hit.

01:39:46.773 --> 01:39:51.232
TRAVIS: No, it was 15, 20, and 23 on the hits.
That was the damage.

01:39:51.232 --> 01:39:55.613
MATT: That was for the damage? Oh, got you. So as
you slam into it and slam into it, with each

01:39:55.613 --> 01:40:02.289
progressive hit, you can see the glass itself is
gliding off the blade. You're doing bits of

01:40:02.289 --> 01:40:06.161
damage, but it's going to take you a while. You
