01:42:31.000 --> 01:42:32.010
MATT: You're putting hands on it?

01:42:32.010 --> 01:42:34.112
TALIESIN: I'm going to hands-on and see if
anything happens, and if nothing does, I'm going

01:42:34.112 --> 01:42:35.487
to pull out my sword and start whacking it.

01:42:35.487 --> 01:42:37.163
MATT: Okay. You guys run up and put your hands on
the gems.

01:42:37.163 --> 01:42:38.413
SAM: Can they get two gems each?

01:42:38.413 --> 01:42:40.340
MATT: They've both gotten two gems each, yeah.

01:42:40.340 --> 01:42:41.627
SAM: And my hand is on--

01:42:41.627 --> 01:42:42.874
MATT: On the bottom gem.

01:42:42.874 --> 01:42:44.537
SAM: Come on, work, damn it.

01:42:44.537 --> 01:42:50.299
MATT: You could, yeah. You could probably get one
gem. There's only four gems left.

01:42:50.299 --> 01:42:54.520
SAM: Could Trinket do the other one? Where's
Trinket?

01:42:54.520 --> 01:42:57.563
MATT: Trinket is up against the wall on the sides,
very scared right now.

01:42:57.563 --> 01:42:59.054
SAM and TALIESIN: We need a fourth hand!

01:42:59.054 --> 01:43:02.708
MARISHA: Oh, okay! Still keeping my Heat Metal
spell up.

01:43:02.708 --> 01:43:06.865
MATT: You place all of your hands on the gems? No
apparent effect.

01:43:06.865 --> 01:43:07.949
MARISHA: Fuck!

01:43:07.949 --> 01:43:09.399
TALIESIN: I pull out my sword and start whacking
it.

01:43:09.399 --> 01:43:10.542
TRAVIS: Fuck you, gem!

01:43:10.542 --> 01:43:11.702
MATT: Make another strength check.

01:43:11.702 --> 01:43:14.379
LAURA: Shitballs. We're going to die.

01:43:14.379 --> 01:43:19.260
LIAM: Guys, the Briarwoods' personal quarters are
really plush. They're sick.

01:43:19.260 --> 01:43:20.711
LAURA: (laughs) I rolled a zero!

01:43:20.711 --> 01:43:22.070
MATT: You rolled zero again?

01:43:22.070 --> 01:43:23.729
(laughter)

01:43:23.729 --> 01:43:27.630
MATT: You can't quite move the metal enough this
time. It's still arcing, and it's spattering

01:43:27.630 --> 01:43:32.532
against the glass. No effect on the glass, but
it's starting to hit elements of the ceiling. You

01:43:32.532 --> 01:43:39.024
can see the stone is being eaten away. At this
point, everyone who's currently on the ground

01:43:39.024 --> 01:43:45.343
suffers three points of acid damage, as it's now
beginning to reach up to your shins.

01:43:45.343 --> 01:43:47.443
You take two.

01:43:47.443 --> 01:43:48.663
SAM: No, I'm out!

01:43:48.663 --> 01:43:52.386
MATT: I forgot, you're outside. You're fine. Pike,
you don't, because you and Scanlan are outside of

01:43:52.386 --> 01:43:53.286
the room.

01:43:53.286 --> 01:43:54.239
TRAVIS: And I'm resistant.

01:43:54.239 --> 01:43:55.804
MATT: Yeah, so you take two.

01:43:55.804 --> 01:44:03.705
SAM: Pike, my love. Is there any way you can get
to the other side of this stone wall to see what's

01:44:03.705 --> 01:44:05.034
over there?

01:44:05.034 --> 01:44:07.095
TALIESIN: Break your gem!

01:44:07.095 --> 01:44:08.365
SAM: Break my gem?

01:44:08.365 --> 01:44:10.266
TALIESIN: The outside gem. Break the outside gem!

01:44:10.266 --> 01:44:12.166
MATT: You hear Percy yelling from the other side.

01:44:12.166 --> 01:44:14.168
TALIESIN: (shouting) Break the outside gem!

01:44:14.168 --> 01:44:15.845
SAM: All I hear is, (muffled noises).

01:44:15.845 --> 01:44:18.040
TALIESIN: (muffled) Just fucking break the gem!

01:44:18.040 --> 01:44:19.439
LAURA: Break the outside gem!

01:44:19.439 --> 01:44:22.293
SAM: I think Percy wants us to kiss, Pike.

01:44:22.293 --> 01:44:25.873
TALIESIN: (muffled) Kiss?! No, I just want you to
break the goddamn thing!

01:44:25.873 --> 01:44:27.864
SAM: He said the power of love will inspire him?

01:44:27.864 --> 01:44:29.565
TALIESIN: (muffled) Fuck the power of love!

01:44:29.565 --> 01:44:32.820
(laughter)

01:44:32.820 --> 01:44:38.089
ASHLEY: I take my hand and I Guiding Bolt the top
of the gem.

01:44:38.089 --> 01:44:45.181
MATT: Okay. Roll a spell attack-- or for Guiding
Bolt is it a saving throw?

01:44:45.181 --> 01:44:47.246
ASHLEY: One more time? Sorry, I can't hear you
very well.

01:44:47.246 --> 01:44:49.536
MATT: I can't remember if it's a saving throw or
not for Guiding Bolt. Let me check.

01:44:49.536 --> 01:44:51.399
LAURA: Maybe you could hit it with a mace, Pike.

01:44:51.399 --> 01:44:56.505
MATT: Guiding Bolt-- yeah, make a ranged spell
attack. With advantage, because it's right in

01:44:56.505 --> 01:44:57.595
front of your hand.

01:44:57.595 --> 01:44:58.908
ASHLEY: Okay.

01:44:58.908 --> 01:45:03.144
MATT: So roll two d20s, take the higher of the
two, and add your spell attack modifier.

01:45:03.144 --> 01:45:04.773
LIAM: Cold as ice, Mercer.

01:45:04.773 --> 01:45:06.993
TALIESIN: (laughs)

01:45:06.993 --> 01:45:09.787
TRAVIS: We're hitting gems, too.

01:45:09.787 --> 01:45:11.797
ASHLEY: 16.

01:45:11.797 --> 01:45:13.552
SAM: What did you say, Ashley?

01:45:13.552 --> 01:45:14.616
ASHLEY: 16.

01:45:14.616 --> 01:45:16.224
SAM: She said 16.

01:45:16.224 --> 01:45:19.932
MATT: 16. Yeah, that's easy enough. Roll your
damage for your Guiding Bolt. It's 4d6 radiant

01:45:19.932 --> 01:45:21.006
damage.

01:45:21.006 --> 01:45:22.070
LAURA: 4d6.

01:45:22.070 --> 01:45:23.019
ASHLEY: Okay.

01:45:23.019 --> 01:45:24.388
TALIESIN: I'm hitting my gem, too.

01:45:24.388 --> 01:45:26.186
MATT: Okay. Roll damage.

01:45:26.186 --> 01:45:31.902
LAURA: I'm trying really hard to lift this pipe
with my scrawny little arms.

01:45:31.902 --> 01:45:33.513
MATT: Make another strength check.

01:45:33.513 --> 01:45:34.676
TRAVIS: 17.

01:45:34.676 --> 01:45:35.917
LAURA: Oh no.

01:45:35.917 --> 01:45:37.401
MATT: (glass breaking noise) Your gem shatters.

01:45:37.401 --> 01:45:39.577
TALIESIN: I rolled a 30 to hit.

01:45:39.577 --> 01:45:40.727
MATT: Yeah, that hits.

01:45:40.727 --> 01:45:41.752
LAURA: 12 for strength.

01:45:41.752 --> 01:45:47.989
MATT: 12 for strength? You manage to move it to
the side. You take two points of fire damage as

01:45:48.081 --> 01:45:52.093
the heat from the actual metal itself is starting
to push through the leather, and you can feel it

01:45:52.093 --> 01:45:53.568
burning the edge of your skin.

01:45:53.568 --> 01:45:54.520
LAURA: Okay.

01:45:54.520 --> 01:45:59.340
MATT: But you do arc it over a little further, and
it's now (splatter noise) pouring onto the ceiling

01:45:59.340 --> 01:46:07.941
and splashing over and down over the glass wall.
You can see, the stonework is melting through and

01:46:07.941 --> 01:46:13.488
after a few seconds of this, you begin to see the
top of where the glass wall ends.

01:46:13.488 --> 01:46:15.015
SAM: Get over it!

01:46:15.015 --> 01:46:22.972
MATT: As the wall dissipates and the acid begins
to push through the rest of the whitestone, you

01:46:22.972 --> 01:46:29.523
guys look up and you can see the ceiling above you
begin to turn dark for a second before part begins

01:46:29.523 --> 01:46:32.664
to (dripping noises) drip acid into the small
chamber that the two of you

01:46:32.664 --> 01:46:34.477
currently are standing in.

01:46:34.477 --> 01:46:38.009
ASHLEY: Total of 20.

01:46:38.009 --> 01:46:43.245
MATT: Total of 20 damage? Yeah, the gem on the
ground before you (glass breaking noise) shatters

01:46:43.245 --> 01:46:45.526
with a blast of radiant energy.

01:46:45.526 --> 01:46:47.895
SAM: And does the stone door behind us open?

01:46:47.895 --> 01:46:51.026
MATT: You still have one more gem left. It's the
one you were touching.

01:46:51.026 --> 01:46:52.665
LAURA: Oh! We have another gem. Hit it!

01:46:52.665 --> 01:46:53.915
MARISHA: The one I was touching?

01:46:53.915 --> 01:46:55.685
MATT: What are you doing, Keyleth?

01:46:55.685 --> 01:47:00.577
MARISHA: I'm going to put my hand on it and do--

01:47:00.577 --> 01:47:02.337
SAM: Squeeze Gem.

01:47:02.337 --> 01:47:10.176
MARISHA: I'm going to do another Thunderwave. Bam!
See if I can Thunderwave crack it.

01:47:10.176 --> 01:47:11.721
TALIESIN: These things are really easy to kill.

01:47:11.721 --> 01:47:13.563
LAURA: Yeah, that's a lot of energy.

01:47:13.563 --> 01:47:15.912
MATT: Roll damage on the Thunderwave.

01:47:15.912 --> 01:47:18.080
MARISHA: They get killed by not a lot, or a lot?

01:47:18.080 --> 01:47:20.348
TALIESIN: They get killed by hitting them with
your fist.

01:47:20.348 --> 01:47:21.688
TRAVIS: Or your staff.

01:47:21.688 --> 01:47:24.477
MARISHA: 11 points of damage.

01:47:24.477 --> 01:47:27.920
MATT: 11 points of damage? Okay. Thunderwave
(explosion noise) resounds off, and you see the

01:47:27.920 --> 01:47:30.979
gem crack in place, but it's still held in its
current position in the wall.

01:47:30.979 --> 01:47:32.163
TRAVIS: Hit it!

01:47:32.163 --> 01:47:33.369
LAURA: Hit it with your staff!

01:47:33.369 --> 01:47:38.399
MATT: At this point in time, as you guys finish
this, the ceiling begins to open into a tunnel

01:47:38.460 --> 01:47:41.497
above you, and acid begins to fill the room that
both of you guys are in.

01:47:41.558 --> 01:47:43.018
SAM: Me and Pike?

01:47:43.018 --> 01:47:44.369
MATT: Yeah, both of you guys.

01:47:44.369 --> 01:47:46.493
TALIESIN: Did I finish killing my gem?

01:47:46.493 --> 01:47:47.623
MATT: You did, yes.

01:47:47.623 --> 01:47:54.676
TALIESIN: Okay, I'm going to take a shot, if I
have anything else to do. Can I take a shot at the

01:47:54.676 --> 01:47:56.105
gem that she just cracked?

01:47:56.105 --> 01:47:57.008
MATT: Yep.

01:47:57.008 --> 01:47:58.801
LAURA: Does it look like a big enough tunnel now
that I can move the pipe?

01:47:58.801 --> 01:48:03.712
MATT: Right now, a person could climb through over
top of the green wall.

01:48:03.712 --> 01:48:04.929
SAM: A goliath?

01:48:04.929 --> 01:48:06.102
LAURA: And a bear?

01:48:06.102 --> 01:48:09.244
MATT: At this point, the way you've been leaning
over and it is slopping over, you could probably

01:48:09.244 --> 01:48:12.757
squeeze them through. A bear, you'd have to push
Winnie the Pooh-style, but it's doable.

01:48:12.757 --> 01:48:14.919
TALIESIN: 18?

01:48:14.919 --> 01:48:16.119
MATT: 18 hits, yeah.

01:48:16.119 --> 01:48:18.293
TALIESIN: That's 16 points of damage.

01:48:18.293 --> 01:48:22.497
MATT: (shattering noise) The last gem shatters
from the blast of the gun. Pieces of the opal

01:48:22.497 --> 01:48:32.042
scatter across your face, Keyleth. Not enough to
cut you. At which point, the green stone wall

01:48:32.042 --> 01:48:38.920
behind you, (scraping noise) lifts up, revealing
the room behind you. The one in front of you tries

01:48:38.920 --> 01:48:44.230
to lift up, and is caught because currently, part
of the stone that lifts it up has been dissolved.

01:48:44.230 --> 01:48:47.616
SAM: (laughs) We're smart.

01:48:47.616 --> 01:48:56.011
MATT: Pike and Scanlan, you guys currently, in
that room, suffer three points of acid damage as

01:48:56.011 --> 01:48:58.255
your side of the room is now filling up with
acid.

01:48:58.255 --> 01:48:59.569
LAURA: Dimension Door out, again!

01:48:59.569 --> 01:49:02.635
SAM: Three points? Mine's halved, right, so it's
two?

01:49:02.635 --> 01:49:03.791
MATT: Yeah.

01:49:03.791 --> 01:49:10.289
MARISHA: Okay, out of frustration, I see this, can
I do a wall of stone from underneath the glass to

01:49:10.289 --> 01:49:12.258
try and lift it up?

01:49:12.258 --> 01:49:21.553
MATT: Yeah. Okay. Go ahead and roll a d20 and add
your wisdom check.

01:49:21.553 --> 01:49:28.985
MARISHA: Not great. Oh! I get advantage on wisdom,
right?

01:49:28.985 --> 01:49:31.103
MATT: It's not a wisdom save.

01:49:31.103 --> 01:49:35.142
MARISHA: Fucking shit. Balls. Wisdom. Just
wisdom?

01:49:35.142 --> 01:49:36.514
MATT: Just wisdom.

01:49:36.514 --> 01:49:37.696
MARISHA: Eight.

01:49:37.696 --> 01:49:43.441
MATT: Eight? You use your Wall of Stone spell. You
feel there is the stone surface beneath the

01:49:43.441 --> 01:49:48.436
bronze. You can sense, as the stone begins to push
up from the whitestone beneath the bronze plates,

01:49:48.436 --> 01:49:52.852
and it (impact noise) hits, and it's not strong
enough to force its way through. Both the bronze

01:49:52.852 --> 01:49:55.072
plating, and the wall itself.

01:49:55.072 --> 01:49:58.305
MARISHA: Bye, 5th-level spell.

01:49:58.305 --> 01:50:01.258
TRAVIS: Can we lower a rope and get over the glass
now that there's a little space?

01:50:01.258 --> 01:50:02.474
LAURA: Yeah.

01:50:02.474 --> 01:50:06.163
MATT: Roll a strength check to try to bend it
away, if you want to.

01:50:06.163 --> 01:50:09.119
MARISHA: I've still got that Heat Metal up.

01:50:09.119 --> 01:50:10.250
LAURA: Nine.

01:50:10.250 --> 01:50:11.705
MATT: With the Heat Metal?

01:50:11.705 --> 01:50:13.277
MARISHA: It's still up. It's a concentration
spell, yeah.

01:50:13.277 --> 01:50:15.930
MATT: You start moving it away.

01:50:15.930 --> 01:50:18.123
LAURA: I kick it with my foot to move it out of
the way.

01:50:18.123 --> 01:50:22.301
MATT: You're pushing as hard as you can. It's
shifting, but it's going to take you another round

01:50:22.301 --> 01:50:26.761
to move it over. Pike and Scanlan--

01:50:26.761 --> 01:50:30.851
LAURA: I'm like Chun Lee, my legs are so strong.

01:50:30.851 --> 01:50:39.015
MATT: You are, technically. That's only one point
of acid damage to both of you because these d6 are

01:50:39.015 --> 01:50:42.743
rolling crap. But this is the second round because
it's filling up, so it's two of those. And I

01:50:42.743 --> 01:50:46.818
rolled a one! So two points of acid, but you take
one because you're halved. So two points of acid

01:50:46.818 --> 01:50:51.210
damage to you, Pike. You're now up to about waist
high in this acid that's beginning to burn through

01:50:51.210 --> 01:50:52.382
and dissolve.

01:50:52.382 --> 01:51:00.263
Who's doing what now? Anything? Anyone else, or
are you just waiting on these guys to finish with

01:51:00.263 --> 01:51:01.858
their actions?

01:51:01.955 --> 01:51:03.845
SAM: Should I get out of here and try to start
working on the stone?

01:51:03.845 --> 01:51:06.705
LAURA: Go on the other side so you can open up the
door that leads out.

01:51:06.705 --> 01:51:14.491
TALIESIN: Wait, I'm so sorry, how far out is the
acid room from where we are right now?

01:51:14.491 --> 01:51:17.366
MATT: You mean the room they're in?

01:51:17.366 --> 01:51:19.596
TALIESIN: No, the room that the acid is stored
in.

01:51:19.596 --> 01:51:22.622
MATT: You don't know, actually. Oh, you mean the
one that was way back?

01:51:22.622 --> 01:51:23.356
TALIESIN: Yeah.

01:51:23.356 --> 01:51:24.458
MATT: That was quite a ways away.

01:51:24.458 --> 01:51:25.427
TALIESIN: Oh, damn it. Okay.

01:51:25.427 --> 01:51:26.524
MATT: It's probably a mile behind you.

01:51:26.524 --> 01:51:30.734
SAM: Pike, is there any way you can get through
this stone wall to the other side

01:51:30.734 --> 01:51:31.934
to see what's there?

01:51:31.934 --> 01:51:35.298
LAURA: Oh, yeah! You're made of jelly. Can you do
it?

01:51:35.298 --> 01:51:38.948
SAM: Oh no, we can't hear you.

01:51:38.948 --> 01:51:40.879
MATT: Hold on, we can't hear you.

01:51:40.879 --> 01:51:42.849
SAM: The darkness is consuming her.

01:51:42.849 --> 01:51:47.266
LIAM: Oh no, she's muted. Hanging up and calling
you back.

01:51:47.266 --> 01:51:50.446
MATT: Roll a perception check.

01:51:50.446 --> 01:51:52.250
SAM: Who, me?

01:51:52.250 --> 01:51:55.798
MATT: Yes.

01:51:55.798 --> 01:52:00.582
LIAM: I am having some fabulous dark chocolate
right now. It is so good.

01:52:00.582 --> 01:52:01.967
They're feeding it to me.

01:52:01.967 --> 01:52:04.594
MATT: Can we hear you, Ashley? There we go.

01:52:04.594 --> 01:52:05.751
SAM: Four.

01:52:05.751 --> 01:52:06.821
MATT: Okay.

01:52:06.891 --> 01:52:08.065
ASHLEY: Okay.

01:52:08.065 --> 01:52:10.584
MATT: Pike, roll a perception check.

01:52:10.796 --> 01:52:14.877
ASHLEY: Okay. Sorry, guys! I don't know what's
going on.

01:52:14.877 --> 01:52:16.281
SAM: It's the evil.

01:52:16.281 --> 01:52:20.444
ASHLEY: I know, it's the evil! It's so strong! I
rolled a 19.

01:52:20.444 --> 01:52:25.369
MATT: Okay. As the acid's pouring and you're
looking about, you notice that the acid level

01:52:25.369 --> 01:52:31.733
raised to a certain point, and doesn't seem to be
continuing. Actually, glancing over, you see the

01:52:31.733 --> 01:52:37.087
door that the Briarwoods left out of, behind you,
is made of whitestone, and the acid that has

01:52:37.087 --> 01:52:40.732
filled this chamber, which is usually sealed off by
the glass wall that has now spilled over through

01:52:40.732 --> 01:52:48.099
the ceiling, has actually dissolved through the
bottom of the door. At this time, it's begun to

01:52:48.099 --> 01:52:53.220
subside, almost like the liquid that's coming
through is not keeping up with the amount that is

01:52:53.220 --> 01:52:54.969
pouring into the hallway behind you.

01:52:54.969 --> 01:52:56.456
LAURA: That's awesome.

01:52:56.456 --> 01:52:58.148
ASHLEY: Good news, guys! We're not going to
drown.

01:52:58.148 --> 01:53:00.516
MATT: Laura, make another strength check.

01:53:00.516 --> 01:53:06.100
LAURA: Okay. This is the best. Oh, four.

01:53:06.100 --> 01:53:14.237
MATT: Okay. You just can't move it. At this point,
the Heat Metal has burned your arms enough to the

01:53:14.237 --> 01:53:17.303
point where you're finding a hard time managing to
keep your muscles together to move it.

01:53:17.303 --> 01:53:19.205
LAURA: It's made of metal, guys.

01:53:19.205 --> 01:53:26.072
MATT: The doorway that's right there, about
waist-high to you, has completely dissolved on the

01:53:26.072 --> 01:53:27.039
bottom.

01:53:27.039 --> 01:53:28.196
SAM: Oh, so we can swim through?

01:53:28.196 --> 01:53:29.156
MATT: If you want to try, yeah.

01:53:29.156 --> 01:53:31.437
SAM: I'm going to do that. I'm going to take a
snorkel.

01:53:31.437 --> 01:53:37.352
MATT: Okay. In doing so, Scanlan, you take eight
points of acid damage, reduced to four because of

01:53:37.352 --> 01:53:44.609
your resistance. You go through and pop out on the
other side in the hallway. It's a stone hallway,

01:53:44.609 --> 01:53:50.988
and the acid is currently dissolving the ground
below, and it's sinking into the ground, China

01:53:50.988 --> 01:53:52.267
Syndrome-style.

01:53:52.267 --> 01:53:53.749
SAM: Are there any buttons, knobs, levers?

01:53:53.749 --> 01:53:58.944
MATT: Looking up, you do see immediately to your
right in the hallway, there is a stone square with

01:53:58.944 --> 01:54:00.176
a push plate.

01:54:00.176 --> 01:54:01.416
LIAM: Motherfucker.

01:54:01.416 --> 01:54:02.628
LAURA: That's what he pushed. Push it!

01:54:02.628 --> 01:54:05.841
SAM: Did I see Vax push that?

01:54:05.841 --> 01:54:10.242
MATT: You saw Vax appear behind them and push
something in that direction.

01:54:10.242 --> 01:54:11.688
SAM: Okay, so I will push that.

01:54:11.688 --> 01:54:18.725
MATT: Okay, you push it. As it clicks inward, you
hear the grinding of gears and stone, and all of a

01:54:18.725 --> 01:54:23.226
sudden the tube that you're holding shudders for a
second. The fluid begins to stop spewing forth.

01:54:23.226 --> 01:54:28.307
The rest of it begins to glide out, eventually
coming to a stop as the acid stops pouring into

01:54:28.307 --> 01:54:35.485
the room. The door that you swam under lifts up.

01:54:35.485 --> 01:54:49.606
SAM: Guess I could have done that before. Sorry. I
wanted to wait until they were gone. That's what

01:54:49.606 --> 01:54:52.427
it was. I was waiting until they were gone.

01:54:52.427 --> 01:55:00.222
MATT: At this point in time, you see where the
opals were on the sides, the portions that keep

01:55:00.222 --> 01:55:05.447
them housed? Slowly move into the wall, leaving
these holes behind them, and the one in the ground

01:55:05.447 --> 01:55:11.444
depresses and disappears. As it does, the acid
that's in the room begins to slowly drain out.

01:55:11.444 --> 01:55:14.028
TRAVIS: Yes.

01:55:14.028 --> 01:55:16.998
MARISHA: Scanlan, what do you see on the other
side of where you are?

01:55:16.998 --> 01:55:25.215
SAM: I see stone, acid, a very handsome gnome-- oh
wait, that's me. And a big button that I just

01:55:25.215 --> 01:55:26.163
pressed.

01:55:26.163 --> 01:55:27.605
TALIESIN: We can see you now, can't we?

01:55:27.605 --> 01:55:29.396
SAM: Oh, hi. See you guys, you look green.

01:55:29.396 --> 01:55:31.804
LAURA: Unless it's still blocking the way because
the door won't open, so we have to go up and over

01:55:31.804 --> 01:55:33.826
the fucking door. So that's what we have to do.

01:55:33.826 --> 01:55:35.636
TRAVIS: Up and over the wall?

01:55:35.636 --> 01:55:38.975
LAURA: The glass door that is partially destroyed
that won't lower.

01:55:38.975 --> 01:55:40.494
MARISHA: We can't open the door.

01:55:40.494 --> 01:55:43.434
SAM: None, no more buttons or levers out there?
Nothing else?

01:55:43.434 --> 01:55:46.741
MATT: Not currently. You guys smashed everything
that was in the vicinity.

01:55:46.741 --> 01:55:51.390
LAURA: We jammed the door. It won't open. So.
There's a tunnel; we can go up and over.

01:55:51.390 --> 01:55:52.774
SAM: All right, do that.

01:55:52.774 --> 01:55:54.513
TALIESIN: We have a rope.

01:55:54.513 --> 01:55:56.022
MARISHA: Throw a rope over to get over.

01:55:56.022 --> 01:55:59.568
MATT: You wait a few moments for the level to
descend a little bit to the point where you can

01:55:59.568 --> 01:56:03.750
stand comfortably without taking any acid damage.
As it drains over, there is that portion of

01:56:03.750 --> 01:56:08.042
ceiling now where it's pockmarked and destroyed,
close to where the glass wall hits the ceiling--

01:56:08.042 --> 01:56:14.083
LAURA: I use the earring and I go, Vax! Vax,
please! That acid is filling the room! We're all

01:56:14.083 --> 01:56:16.635
dying. I don't know what to do.

01:56:16.635 --> 01:56:24.314
MATT: As you're walking alongside the Briarwoods
into a new chamber, you hear the words hit your

01:56:24.314 --> 01:56:31.588
ear and you can feel the back of your throat
choking up as a part of you is urging you to run

01:56:31.588 --> 01:56:37.216
back. And as you stop instinctively in your step,
the rest of the group walks ahead about ten feet

01:56:37.216 --> 01:56:43.956
before Sylas looks over his shoulder and says,
"Keep up, please. There's work to be done." At

01:56:43.956 --> 01:56:47.431
which point, you feel yourself just continue
stepping forward and catching up to him, because

01:56:47.431 --> 01:56:49.841
you wouldn't want to make Sylas angry.

01:56:49.841 --> 01:56:52.044
TRAVIS: Purple Man.

01:56:52.044 --> 01:56:54.826
MARISHA: Yeah, I was just going to say. Fucking
fuck you, David Tennant.

01:56:54.826 --> 01:56:57.150
(laughter)

01:56:57.150 --> 01:56:59.463
TRAVIS: We've got to get out of this room.

01:56:59.463 --> 01:57:01.556
LAURA: Yeah. Up and over, let's go.

01:57:01.556 --> 01:57:04.201
MATT: All right. How are you guys getting over,
through?

01:57:04.201 --> 01:57:05.678
TALIESIN and MARISHA: Rope.

01:57:05.678 --> 01:57:07.742
LAURA: I have the robe of infinite rope-ness.

01:57:07.742 --> 01:57:13.841
MATT: Okay, so you take a few times. You want to
just throw the rope over? You could, however you

01:57:13.841 --> 01:57:16.291
want to get the rope up and over the area, it
takes a few tries but you get it

01:57:16.291 --> 01:57:17.802
on the other side.

01:57:17.802 --> 01:57:19.008
LAURA: I'm flying.

01:57:19.008 --> 01:57:24.083
MATT: Oh yeah, you're flying, you just drop it
over. It's fine. We'll say for the sake of

01:57:24.083 --> 01:57:27.798
brevity, a few minutes pass. You guys manage to
get each one of you over, Trinket being the

01:57:27.798 --> 01:57:29.088
hardest point.

01:57:29.088 --> 01:57:31.672
LAURA: I tie him and then Grog lifts him like a
pulley.

01:57:31.672 --> 01:57:34.611
TALIESIN: Very uncomfortable for everyone
involved.

01:57:34.611 --> 01:57:38.732
MATT: Which, when Trinket reaches the top, it's
like trying to fit an oblong

01:57:38.732 --> 01:57:40.057
object through a hole.

01:57:40.057 --> 01:57:44.935
LAURA: I'm flying so I get underneath him and try
and wedge him, help him get into the hole.

01:57:44.935 --> 01:57:47.926
MATT: We'll say it takes an additional ten
minutes, but you manage

01:57:47.926 --> 01:57:49.353
to finally get Trinket through.

01:57:49.353 --> 01:57:51.765
LIAM: Oh, I have a rumbly in my tumbly.

01:57:51.765 --> 01:57:59.913
MATT: That was straight-up Winnie the Pooh. I'm
really happy about that. On the other side of the

01:57:59.976 --> 01:58:06.687
now pretty much ruined acid distillery, the
residuum factory that was constructed here by the

01:58:06.687 --> 01:58:12.074
Briarwoods, you can see in the tunnel before you
that most of the stone before you has dissolved,

01:58:12.074 --> 01:58:19.142
and there's certain levels of eroded stonework
that descends about 30 feet before rockily

01:58:19.142 --> 01:58:27.066
climbing back up to the original height it was. It
can be traversed, climbed with mild difficulty,

01:58:27.066 --> 01:58:34.579
but you gather yourselves to continue pushing
forward and to both complete this journey and to

01:58:34.579 --> 01:58:39.535
retrieve your ally who is now currently under the
gaze of your enemy.

01:58:39.535 --> 01:58:44.371
And with that, we're going to take a quick
bathroom break. Quick break.

01:58:44.371 --> 01:58:46.037
Want to get back into this.

01:58:46.037 --> 01:58:48.818
TRAVIS: We'll be right back, Ashley.

01:58:48.818 --> 01:58:50.968
MATT: See you guys in a second.

01:58:50.968 --> 02:07:17.957
[break]

02:07:18.021 --> 02:07:23.975
MATT: And welcome back, everyone. So. As you all
take a moment to regather yourselves after this

02:07:23.975 --> 02:07:29.528
circumstance, you climb your way through this
acid-scarred portion of the hallway ahead of you,

02:07:29.528 --> 02:07:34.949
this like small tunnel up to the other side. As
you're on your way there, Percy, you notice a

02:07:34.949 --> 02:07:42.945
flash of purple and black energy course up the
front of your Pepperbox. You glance down at the

02:07:42.945 --> 02:07:47.945
six o'clock, previously empty barrel, and a new
name now is emblazoned across it. It says,

02:07:47.945 --> 02:07:49.363
"Cassandra de Rolo."

02:07:49.363 --> 02:07:50.464
ALL: Oh!

02:07:50.464 --> 02:07:52.507
TRAVIS: Oh. My. God.

02:07:52.507 --> 02:07:59.290
MARISHA: Wait, that was on that empty barrel?

02:07:59.290 --> 02:08:01.939
ASHLEY: What?

02:08:01.939 --> 02:08:05.362
LAURA: Oh my god. I thought--

02:08:05.362 --> 02:08:07.963
MARISHA: He didn't know who it was for.

02:08:07.963 --> 02:08:09.257
LAURA: Oh my god.

02:08:09.257 --> 02:08:13.833
SAM: Wow.

02:08:13.833 --> 02:08:15.770
TRAVIS: Does any of us see this besides him?

02:08:15.770 --> 02:08:19.463
MATT: You guys all come up to the top, you look
down and you see Percy still down, looking at his

02:08:19.463 --> 02:08:24.086
gun in a wide-eyed, spacey expression on his
face.

02:08:24.086 --> 02:08:25.601
LAURA: Percival?

02:08:25.601 --> 02:08:26.728
TRAVIS: You all right?

02:08:26.728 --> 02:08:29.763
TALIESIN: No. No, I'm not.

02:08:29.763 --> 02:08:41.100
SAM: Is your bangy thing okay? Is it your sister?

02:08:41.100 --> 02:08:43.874
TALIESIN: We'll see what this means.

02:08:43.874 --> 02:08:45.981
MARISHA: Oh, Percy.

02:08:45.981 --> 02:08:49.612
TALIESIN: Let's go take care of this.

02:08:49.612 --> 02:08:54.291
TRAVIS: Yeah. Let's. But you always have a
choice.

02:08:54.291 --> 02:08:56.530
TALIESIN: We'll see.

02:08:56.530 --> 02:09:02.514
MATT: You climb up and out, you guys make your way
down this tunnel, no more than 60 feet from where

02:09:02.514 --> 02:09:12.619
you are, before the chamber opens up before you
into what is a large underground cavern. Mostly

02:09:12.619 --> 02:09:15.565
cleared out, it looks like portions of it are, you
know, both the tunnel and this area--

02:09:15.565 --> 02:09:17.032
LAURA: Can we stealth?

02:09:17.032 --> 02:09:18.144
MATT: You can if you'd like.

02:09:18.144 --> 02:09:22.023
LAURA: I think we should, because as far as they
know, we're dead now. They don't know we got out

02:09:22.023 --> 02:09:22.848
of there.

02:09:22.848 --> 02:09:23.941
MARISHA: It's true.

02:09:23.941 --> 02:09:25.668
MATT: Okay. So everyone go ahead and roll
stealth.

02:09:25.668 --> 02:09:29.314
MARISHA: Oh my god.

02:09:29.314 --> 02:09:32.840
LAURA: Yeah, I'm going to cast Pass Without a
Trace on us.

02:09:32.840 --> 02:09:35.229
MARISHA: I still critical failed.

02:09:35.229 --> 02:09:39.241
LAURA: Wait, can't you roll again now that I told
you we were casting--

02:09:39.241 --> 02:09:42.472
MATT: (laughs) Nah. It stays, unfortunately.

02:09:42.554 --> 02:09:44.018
LAURA: Doesn't work that way?

02:09:44.018 --> 02:09:47.405
MATT: All right, so, stealth rolls, plus ten to
everyone's stealth. What was it?

02:09:47.498 --> 02:09:48.301
TRAVIS: 26.

02:09:48.301 --> 02:09:49.363
MATT: 26. Vex?

02:09:49.363 --> 02:09:51.943
ASHLEY: 16.

02:09:51.943 --> 02:09:55.914
LAURA: Nice. 35.

02:09:55.914 --> 02:09:57.743
SAM: 27.

02:09:57.743 --> 02:09:59.913
TALIESIN: 24.

02:09:59.913 --> 02:10:05.843
MATT: Okay. As a median, the group does really
well, so that helps overtake for your misstep.

02:10:05.928 --> 02:10:09.134
MARISHA: God, it's cold in here! Jesus.

02:10:09.134 --> 02:10:14.829
MATT: Looking around, you can see the boards and
pieces of wood and stone that are keeping this

02:10:14.829 --> 02:10:24.105
hallway up, and as you step into this large
chamber, it's dark and mostly freshly carved

02:10:24.158 --> 02:10:28.152
earth. Elements of earth have been taken out, and
you can see to the right and left of you as you

02:10:28.152 --> 02:10:32.826
enter this chamber there are more and more chunks
of that broken stone and large piles of moved

02:10:32.826 --> 02:10:38.975
earth that are in some levels of being left there
or going to be moved out, or eventually were put

02:10:38.975 --> 02:10:42.361
to a point where it was no longer necessary to
have to clear the area.

02:10:42.361 --> 02:10:52.047
You do see, on the sides of you, there are these
iron carts, wheeled carts that have handles on

02:10:52.047 --> 02:10:59.222
them. Some have means of being pulled along
separately. These carts were used, you can gather,

02:10:59.222 --> 02:11:02.585
for moving a lot of the materials back and forth.
It's probably what the ramps in the previous rooms

02:11:02.585 --> 02:11:10.018
were also to collect. You can see there's a
residuum dust coating on a lot of these carts, as

02:11:10.018 --> 02:11:12.102
well as broken pieces of whitestone.

02:11:12.102 --> 02:11:16.534
TRAVIS: The broken pieces of whitestone, are there
any that are the size of two hands?

02:11:16.534 --> 02:11:19.282
MATT: There's a few you could probably grab,
yeah.

02:11:19.282 --> 02:11:22.368
TRAVIS: Can I grab a big, two-handed piece and put
it in the Bag of Holding?

02:11:22.368 --> 02:11:23.380
MATT: Sure.

02:11:23.380 --> 02:11:26.496
LAURA: Can I take some of it and rub it on some of
my arrows?

02:11:26.496 --> 02:11:37.358
MATT: Okay. Sure. You rub it on. Most of it falls
off, as it's metallic arrow point to dust, but

02:11:37.358 --> 02:11:43.473
some of it does manage to stay on for the time
being. Your holy oil is still active, those that

02:11:43.473 --> 02:11:48.098
you dipped your arrows in. However, as you look
past the darkness, you can see in the center of

02:11:48.098 --> 02:11:59.867
this room a monolithic structure not unlike a
large pyramid-type platformed element, and

02:11:59.867 --> 02:12:05.616
immediately upon looking at it, you can see this
has to be the ziggurat that everyone's been

02:12:05.616 --> 02:12:08.471
talking about in Whitestone.

02:12:08.471 --> 02:12:15.253
You can see that the base of it is white, and is
very much the same texture and color as all of the

02:12:15.253 --> 02:12:19.056
whitestone you've seen used in the construction
and all of the mining materials here within the

02:12:19.056 --> 02:12:24.736
city, but from what little light you have in the
room-- and there is a little bit of ambient light

02:12:24.736 --> 02:12:29.366
from torches set at different points, and those
who can see decently at a distance, and there is

02:12:29.366 --> 02:12:36.729
an ominous glow to the structure itself-- it
gradually turns to a greenish color. Hard to see

02:12:36.729 --> 02:12:41.617
exactly why this transition is, but it goes from
white to a green towards the top, and it levels

02:12:41.617 --> 02:12:47.311
off. You can see what looks to be a small separate
structure at the very top. There are long

02:12:47.311 --> 02:12:52.907
stairways that are visible on the two sides you
can see before you: long stairways.

02:12:52.907 --> 02:12:55.079
Everyone make a perception check.

02:12:55.079 --> 02:12:58.744
LAURA: I'm scared of all of my dice right now.

02:12:58.744 --> 02:13:00.898
MARISHA: Yeah, mine are failing me.

02:13:00.898 --> 02:13:01.954
SAM: One.

02:13:01.954 --> 02:13:02.969
MARISHA: Fucking shit.

02:13:02.969 --> 02:13:05.113
LAURA: 18.

02:13:05.113 --> 02:13:06.358
ASHLEY: 14.

02:13:06.358 --> 02:13:07.387
TRAVIS: Ten.

02:13:07.387 --> 02:13:08.915
TALIESIN: 24.

02:13:08.915 --> 02:13:09.997
MARISHA: 16.

02:13:09.997 --> 02:13:17.532
MATT: Okay. Vex and Percy: as you begin to step
out along the wall, and as you guys are moving

02:13:17.532 --> 02:13:22.584
towards the ziggurat, you can see through the
darkness, there is a bit of low light along the

02:13:22.584 --> 02:13:29.275
edge of the pyramid, and you can see, halfway up
the staircase, four individuals stepping up the

02:13:29.275 --> 02:13:30.801
stairs at a distance.

02:13:30.801 --> 02:13:35.144
SAM: Is this Egyptian pyramid-sized big?

02:13:35.144 --> 02:13:38.522
MATT: It's more Aztec. It's not quite gargantuan.

02:13:38.522 --> 02:13:41.251
SAM: There's 200 stairs?

02:13:41.251 --> 02:13:46.906
MATT: Approximately. I'd say the whole structure
from bottom to high is maybe 200 feet tall. It's

02:13:46.906 --> 02:13:48.577
not extremely large.

02:13:48.577 --> 02:13:50.563
TALIESIN: What's the roof look like above it?

02:13:50.563 --> 02:13:54.883
MATT: It's hard to see at this distance,
especially with the very little light here. You

02:13:54.883 --> 02:13:58.182
can tell just enough, though, that there is some
sort of roof, but you can't make any details out

02:13:58.182 --> 02:13:59.479
from this distance.

02:13:59.479 --> 02:14:03.396
MARISHA: Do I have any geographical idea of where
we are in the city? Is this located

02:14:03.396 --> 02:14:04.799
under the Sun Tree?

02:14:04.799 --> 02:14:07.350
MATT: This would be pretty close to where the Sun
Tree is located, yeah.

02:14:07.350 --> 02:14:13.266
SAM: Before we go stomping in there, should we
take a short rest and heal up? Is anyone besides

02:14:13.266 --> 02:14:15.215
me and Pike damaged at all?

02:14:15.215 --> 02:14:16.823
LAURA: I'm damaged a little.

02:14:16.823 --> 02:14:18.024
MARISHA: I'm damaged, but--

02:14:18.024 --> 02:14:20.666
LAURA: I don't know how long I want to wait when
Vax is--

02:14:20.666 --> 02:14:22.981
SAM: We don't want to start traipsing up. They'll
see us coming.

02:14:22.981 --> 02:14:25.009
TRAVIS: Is there cover? Can they see us if we can
see them?

02:14:25.009 --> 02:14:31.673
MATT: Where you're currently standing, there's
very little to no light. If you're careful, you

02:14:31.673 --> 02:14:34.313
could possibly slip by their detection.

02:14:34.379 --> 02:14:37.574
SAM: Or we could wait until they get up there and
then go.

02:14:37.678 --> 02:14:39.557
TALIESIN: Except what happens when they get up
there?

02:14:39.557 --> 02:14:44.682
LIAM: Quick question: while I'm with my new
friends, in any moments that they're not telling

02:14:44.682 --> 02:14:48.423
me to go somewhere or walk somewhere, can I just
look at the symbol on my hand?

02:14:48.423 --> 02:14:50.021
MATT: Yeah.

02:14:50.021 --> 02:14:54.580
LIAM: That's it. Just stare at it whenever I can,
when they're not paying attention.

02:14:54.580 --> 02:15:01.204
MATT: Okay. You glance at it. It doesn't seem to
have any particular glow or connection. Especially

02:15:01.204 --> 02:15:06.844
since Pike made her arrival, it seems to be the
energy of connection that was briefly housed in

02:15:06.844 --> 02:15:10.626
that symbol by her has transitioned to her form
here.

02:15:10.626 --> 02:15:15.208
TRAVIS: Will anybody gain something back from a
short rest that we really need, or do we need to

02:15:15.208 --> 02:15:16.412
go after them?

02:15:16.412 --> 02:15:19.037
MARISHA: I'm afraid they're marching him to his
death.

02:15:19.037 --> 02:15:20.984
LAURA: To sacrifice him.

02:15:20.984 --> 02:15:22.319
TRAVIS: What about you?

02:15:22.319 --> 02:15:26.603
SAM: I'd gain a few hit points, but it's nothing
bad. I can take a potion.

02:15:26.690 --> 02:15:29.731
MARISHA: We'll have to heal in battle, if we need
to.

02:15:29.731 --> 02:15:33.614
ASHLEY: I can do a healing spell, you know.

02:15:33.614 --> 02:15:36.336
SAM: Thanks, Sarah Palin.

02:15:36.336 --> 02:15:39.866
MATT: If you'd like to.

02:15:39.866 --> 02:15:45.583
ASHLEY: Where's everybody at?

02:15:45.583 --> 02:15:48.211
LAURA: That Vasselheim accent is rubbing off on
you, Pike.

02:15:48.211 --> 02:15:51.577
MATT: Who's looking hurt?

02:15:51.577 --> 02:15:54.478
ASHLEY: Are you guys all pretty low?

02:15:54.545 --> 02:15:55.794
TALIESIN: I'm all right.

02:15:55.794 --> 02:15:57.197
SAM: Not really.

02:15:57.197 --> 02:15:59.164
LAURA: I think save your spells, Pike.

02:15:59.164 --> 02:16:04.120
MARISHA: What's the plan?

02:16:04.120 --> 02:16:05.683
TRAVIS: Let's go.

02:16:05.683 --> 02:16:10.075
LAURA: I don't know. Stealth as much as we can and
then take them out? I don't know.

02:16:10.075 --> 02:16:13.716
TRAVIS: We're at the bottom of this pyramid.
They're walking up to the top.

02:16:13.716 --> 02:16:16.561
MATT: At this time, they're close to the top.

02:16:16.561 --> 02:16:18.219
TALIESIN: Let's start making our way.

02:16:18.219 --> 02:16:21.173
MATT: It's just stairs. Pretty steep stairs, but
stairs nonetheless.

02:16:21.173 --> 02:16:24.635
TALIESIN: We're going to have to Ghostbusters
this.

02:16:24.635 --> 02:16:27.303
LAURA: How high up can I fly? Is it all dark up?

02:16:27.303 --> 02:16:31.913
MATT: It is. There's a very little bit of light
that's part of the ziggurat itself.

02:16:31.913 --> 02:16:33.415
LAURA: I keep raising up.

02:16:33.415 --> 02:16:34.892
TRAVIS: Four sides to the pyramid?

02:16:34.892 --> 02:16:36.456
MATT: Four sides. You can only see two.

02:16:36.456 --> 02:16:39.135
LAURA: I want to keep raising up so I can get a
better view of what's happening.

02:16:39.135 --> 02:16:47.453
MARISHA: I tell Pike real quick, Pike, we are
right under the Sun Tree, which was dedicated to

02:16:47.453 --> 02:16:54.992
the god Pelor. This tree might end up being our
best friend in this fight. Keep that in mind going

02:16:54.992 --> 02:16:55.852
forward.

02:16:55.852 --> 02:16:58.045
LAURA: Are Sarenrae and Pelor good buddies?

02:16:58.045 --> 02:16:59.858
MARISHA: Yeah, are they on good terms?

02:16:59.858 --> 02:17:01.242
ASHLEY: Well, let's hope so.

02:17:01.242 --> 02:17:03.024
(laughter)

02:17:03.024 --> 02:17:04.290
LAURA: Would you know?

02:17:04.290 --> 02:17:11.213
MATT: You would know that Sarenrae and Pelor are
adjacent deities in this realm. They have many

02:17:11.213 --> 02:17:23.055
overlapping interests and both strive to light, to
healing-- many spheres of overlap in those

02:17:23.055 --> 02:17:24.636
regards, so yes.

02:17:24.636 --> 02:17:29.167
ASHLEY: Now that I'm thinking about it, I think
they are pretty good friends.

02:17:29.237 --> 02:17:32.441
SAM: How far away are the four figures from us
right now?

02:17:32.441 --> 02:17:40.007
MATT: Oh, man. They're probably a good 500 to 600
feet from you.

02:17:40.007 --> 02:17:41.512
MARISHA: Should we flank and go?

02:17:41.512 --> 02:17:42.979
SAM: Do you want to just hit them hard?

02:17:42.979 --> 02:17:44.641
LAURA: Or should we get on each side?

02:17:44.641 --> 02:17:46.142
MARISHA: How many feet? 50 to 60 feet?

02:17:46.142 --> 02:17:47.225
SAM: 600.

02:17:47.225 --> 02:17:50.168
MATT: They're at the top of the ziggurat now.
Actually, at this time, they're just now cresting

02:17:50.168 --> 02:17:51.745
over and vanishing over the lip.

02:17:51.745 --> 02:17:55.852
TRAVIS: From the base of the pyramid, what would
you say the base circumference of this ziggurat

02:17:55.852 --> 02:17:58.559
is? Is it half a mile around?

02:17:58.559 --> 02:18:02.152
MATT: No, it's smaller than that. I'd say it's
about--

02:18:02.152 --> 02:18:06.648
LAURA: 200 feet square? One on each side?

02:18:06.648 --> 02:18:08.659
TRAVIS: Yeah, should we come up on different
sides?

02:18:08.659 --> 02:18:10.770
LAURA: Percy, what do you think?

02:18:10.770 --> 02:18:13.407
MARISHA and TALIESIN: Flank them.

02:18:13.407 --> 02:18:16.012
SAM: They're going to be inside, though, before we
get halfway up.

02:18:16.012 --> 02:18:17.565
TALIESIN: There's no inside. It's just on top.

02:18:17.565 --> 02:18:19.255
TRAVIS: We don't know what's up there.

02:18:19.255 --> 02:18:20.904
LAURA: Can I see? I raised up.

02:18:20.904 --> 02:18:22.115
MATT: You raised up and you look--

02:18:22.115 --> 02:18:24.206
SAM: It's for grain storage.

02:18:24.206 --> 02:18:27.564
(laughter)

02:18:27.564 --> 02:18:32.141
MATT: What little source of light you can see,
where the stairs stop, there's a level platform,

02:18:32.141 --> 02:18:37.719
there's some pillars, and there appears to be a
secondary structure, a deep green, almost dark

02:18:37.719 --> 02:18:43.218
jade-type structure that is built. A square
structure right there at the very top.

02:18:43.218 --> 02:18:45.508
MARISHA: Probably out of the same glass bullshit.

02:18:45.508 --> 02:18:48.101
LAURA: Vax will hear me if I whisper down to
everybody.

02:18:48.101 --> 02:18:49.641
TRAVIS: Oh, fuck. That's right.

02:18:49.641 --> 02:18:52.421
MARISHA: See if he can stall. Tell him to stall.

02:18:52.421 --> 02:18:55.490
LAURA: (whispering) Vax. Vax!

02:18:55.490 --> 02:19:03.712
MATT: You can still respond, if you wish. You
still have your mind about you; you just consider

02:19:03.712 --> 02:19:07.182
the Briarwoods right now your closest allies, and
they have to be protected.

02:19:07.182 --> 02:19:09.811
LIAM: Where are you?

02:19:09.811 --> 02:19:14.639
SAM: No. Stop it.

02:19:14.639 --> 02:19:23.807
LAURA: (whispering) I don't know where we are.
Acid everywhere. Vax, please. Isn't there anything

02:19:23.807 --> 02:19:26.284
you can do?

02:19:26.284 --> 02:19:29.267
LIAM: We should all be together. You should join
me here.

02:19:29.267 --> 02:19:32.387
LAURA: (whispering) I would love to, but I don't
know where you are.

02:19:32.387 --> 02:19:43.265
LIAM: I'm on the top of a thing. I can see very
far. Everybody is very attractive up here. I think

02:19:43.265 --> 02:19:48.133
something nice is about to happen. I'm afraid to
ask questions, though; I don't want to seem--

02:19:48.133 --> 02:19:50.605
MATT: "Who are you talking to, lovely boy?"

02:19:50.605 --> 02:19:52.095
LAURA: (whispering) Please, Vax. Please.

02:19:52.095 --> 02:19:54.104
LIAM: To Sarenrae.

02:19:54.104 --> 02:19:59.342
MATT: Make a wisdom check.

02:19:59.342 --> 02:20:06.689
LIAM: With no advantage? I'm still a half-elf.

02:20:06.689 --> 02:20:07.963
MATT: I know.

02:20:07.963 --> 02:20:12.268
LAURA: Isn't he supposed to not be able to get
charmed?

02:20:12.268 --> 02:20:13.759
LIAM: 13. No, I have advantage.

02:20:13.759 --> 02:20:15.044
TALIESIN: Feast.

02:20:15.044 --> 02:20:17.459
MATT: This isn't a saving throw.

02:20:17.459 --> 02:20:19.015
LIAM: Advantage for half-elf, advantage for
feast.

02:20:19.015 --> 02:20:20.465
MATT: What did you roll?

02:20:20.465 --> 02:20:21.403
LIAM: Total of 13.

02:20:21.403 --> 02:20:27.195
MATT: 13? Okay. You continue with the deception.
You pushed through enough to guard the answer, as

02:20:27.195 --> 02:20:34.803
opposed to spilling the truth to your ally. She
gives a, "That's not very welcome here. I would

02:20:34.803 --> 02:20:36.483
"not recommend that. Put it away."

02:20:36.483 --> 02:20:37.568
LIAM: What is that?

02:20:37.568 --> 02:20:39.315
MATT: "Put it away. That's not welcome here."

02:20:39.315 --> 02:20:43.395
LIAM: Yes. You're still very pretty.

02:20:43.395 --> 02:20:47.170
MATT: "I'm taken, my darling."

02:20:47.170 --> 02:20:49.106
LAURA: I'm stalling so that everyone can walk
around.

02:20:49.189 --> 02:20:50.246
LIAM: Me too.

02:20:50.246 --> 02:20:51.941
TALIESIN: I'm starting to make my way up.

02:20:52.009 --> 02:20:54.143
MARISHA: We're flanking on the far side.

02:20:54.143 --> 02:20:56.487
ASHLEY: Can I go up to Vax and--

02:20:56.487 --> 02:20:57.760
LAURA: Oh, he's not here!

02:20:57.760 --> 02:21:02.467
MATT: Vax isn't with you guys. Vax is with the
Briarwoods at the top of the ziggurat.

02:21:02.467 --> 02:21:03.652
LIAM: Earring talk.

02:21:03.652 --> 02:21:08.622
ASHLEY: Shit. Okay, sorry. That must have been
when I got disconnected. I know

02:21:08.622 --> 02:21:09.893
what's going on now.

02:21:09.893 --> 02:21:13.201
MATT: So while they're having this discussion, you
guys begin to ascend the steps as a group?

02:21:13.201 --> 02:21:16.827
TRAVIS: There are four sides. Who wants to come on
my side?

02:21:16.827 --> 02:21:18.125
SAM: Me and Pike.

02:21:18.125 --> 02:21:19.265
TRAVIS: Okay.

02:21:19.265 --> 02:21:20.446
MARISHA: I'll go with Grog.

02:21:20.446 --> 02:21:21.555
LAURA: Wait.

02:21:21.555 --> 02:21:23.167
TALIESIN: And you can join me.

02:21:23.167 --> 02:21:24.260
LAURA: I'm flying up.

02:21:24.260 --> 02:21:26.272
TALIESIN: So I'm just walking up the center.

02:21:26.272 --> 02:21:27.452
LAURA: Trinket's going--

02:21:27.452 --> 02:21:28.438
TALIESIN: With me.

02:21:28.438 --> 02:21:29.240
LAURA: Sure.

02:21:29.240 --> 02:21:30.225
TALIESIN: Trinket's with me.

02:21:30.225 --> 02:21:35.169
MARISHA: Guys, thought for a second: what if Percy
goes as a distraction? Percy goes first.

02:21:35.169 --> 02:21:36.527
SAM: We all look like Percy.

02:21:36.527 --> 02:21:42.295
MARISHA: But they might be able to see through
that. Use Percy as bait while

02:21:42.295 --> 02:21:43.539
the rest of us go up.

02:21:43.539 --> 02:21:46.426
LAURA: Vax looks like Percy right now! They know
we're up to something.

02:21:46.426 --> 02:21:48.571
MARISHA: That's why I said send in the real
Percy.

02:21:48.571 --> 02:21:49.690
LAURA: Send in the real Percy?

02:21:49.690 --> 02:21:52.829
MATT: So, how many groups are you breaking into?

02:21:52.829 --> 02:21:54.308
TALIESIN and TRAVIS: Three.

02:21:54.308 --> 02:21:59.343
MATT: Three groups. Okay. Gnomes in one, Percy and
Trinket in one, Grog and who else?

02:21:59.343 --> 02:22:00.431
TRAVIS: Keyleth.

02:22:00.431 --> 02:22:02.410
MATT: Keyleth, and you're floating above
somewhere.

02:22:02.410 --> 02:22:04.138
LAURA: I'm floating above, keeping an eye.

02:22:04.138 --> 02:22:05.137
MATT: Okay.

02:22:05.137 --> 02:22:07.142
LAURA: (laughing) Oh no, this is so stupid.

02:22:07.142 --> 02:22:08.542
MARISHA: My heart is pounding.

02:22:08.542 --> 02:22:15.198
MATT: As you all separate, the closest stairway to
you, you would probably get there sooner. Who's

02:22:15.198 --> 02:22:16.259
taking that stairway?

02:22:16.259 --> 02:22:19.017
SAM: The gnomes. We're slow.

02:22:19.017 --> 02:22:24.472
LAURA: And I'm sneaking into the dark as much as I
can, but I want to raise up and be where I can be

02:22:24.472 --> 02:22:26.054
above them and shoot down.

02:22:26.054 --> 02:22:27.758
MATT: All right, and you three are going on this
side?

02:22:27.758 --> 02:22:28.722
TRAVIS: Sure.

02:22:28.722 --> 02:22:30.480
MATT: Okay, we'll say you're on this side.

02:22:30.480 --> 02:22:35.418
SAM: Maybe we should split the party further.

02:22:35.418 --> 02:22:37.681
MATT: You could. It's not a bad idea.

02:22:37.681 --> 02:22:40.399
LAURA: This is so brilliant.

02:22:40.399 --> 02:22:41.816
MARISHA: We've got this.

02:22:41.816 --> 02:22:45.916
MATT: All right.

02:22:45.916 --> 02:22:47.370
LAURA: Oh god.

02:22:47.370 --> 02:22:53.479
MATT: As you begin to ascend the steps, a couple
of things. One, you notice the structure is very

02:22:53.479 --> 02:23:02.415
old at its base. The whitestone itself is cracked
and worn, weathered, and most of it is indeed made

02:23:02.415 --> 02:23:07.226
from the whitestone from the surrounding mountains
of the Alabaster Sierras, mined ages and ages ago.

02:23:07.226 --> 02:23:12.769
As you get further up, you begin to see sections
of it that are newer stone, areas that have been

02:23:12.769 --> 02:23:20.677
renovated and rebuilt and made to complete this
apparently once-sundered structure.

02:23:20.677 --> 02:23:28.426
As you all begin to creep up past the midpoint,
you begin to notice the color change. The

02:23:28.426 --> 02:23:36.509
whitestone begins to fade away as you begin to see
clusters of that same green residuum glass is now

02:23:36.509 --> 02:23:42.940
set across, smooth, almost like the limestone of a
pyramid, like a top layer to it. As you begin to

02:23:42.940 --> 02:23:47.683
get further to the top, eventually the entirety of
the stone and the stairs are coated in this

02:23:47.683 --> 02:23:53.192
material to the point where there's even a little
bit of slickness in certain places from the

02:23:53.192 --> 02:23:59.063
smoothness. It's like chipped obsidian, how it's
flaked away and has those divots in it. There is

02:23:59.063 --> 02:24:01.504
that smoothness, that glass-like texture to it.

02:24:01.504 --> 02:24:08.868
As you begin to get towards the very top of the
stairway, each of you carefully keeping in line,

02:24:08.868 --> 02:24:14.207
talking to each other quietly, you begin to see
the central structure at the top of the platform

02:24:14.207 --> 02:24:22.617
begin to appear. It is a simple, four-walled
structure made purely of this dark jade glass

02:24:22.617 --> 02:24:30.812
material. There's a slight overhang with a few
platforms that seem to hold this, for lack of a

02:24:30.812 --> 02:24:36.485
better term, awning-type platform that hangs over
the entrance to this.

02:24:36.485 --> 02:24:41.914
You guys are about to reach the lip. Is there any
preparation you want to do?

02:24:41.914 --> 02:24:43.997
TRAVIS: (quietly) I would like to rage.

02:24:43.997 --> 02:24:46.638
(laughter)

02:24:46.722 --> 02:24:51.676
MARISHA: Does the building seem-- is it completely
encased?

02:24:51.676 --> 02:24:55.297
MATT: The building is entirely encased in this
material.

02:24:55.297 --> 02:24:57.078
MARISHA: And they're already inside?

02:24:57.078 --> 02:24:59.552
MATT: You haven't gotten to the very top of the
lip yet.

02:24:59.552 --> 02:25:02.029
LAURA: Can I see? I'm raised above, right?

02:25:02.029 --> 02:25:09.939
MATT: You see, as they're having this
conversation, they talk a bit with Vax, speak with

02:25:09.939 --> 02:25:20.075
Cassandra, then they step forward and begin to
open the two doors to the central chamber.

02:25:20.075 --> 02:25:27.902
LIAM: Can I ask a clarification question? The mojo
they have on me: do I think they're my best

02:25:27.986 --> 02:25:33.265
friends in the world, or is it more Kilgrave; I do
whatever they say, but have my own opinion trapped

02:25:33.265 --> 02:25:34.258
away?

02:25:34.258 --> 02:25:37.713
MATT: You have your own opinion, you just trust
them implicitly. They have to be protected.

02:25:37.713 --> 02:25:41.404
LIAM: All right. It's a little of both, it seems
like.

02:25:41.404 --> 02:25:46.914
MATT: Like any close friend who would ask
something of you and say, "please come with me,"

02:25:46.914 --> 02:25:49.198
there is an essence that you're compelled--

02:25:49.198 --> 02:25:50.452
LIAM: I trust them.

02:25:50.452 --> 02:25:51.981
MATT: You trust them, yeah.

02:25:51.981 --> 02:25:55.665
ASHLEY: Am I close to Percy at all? Or did we
already separate?

02:25:55.665 --> 02:25:57.170
MATT: No, you guys have already separated.

02:25:57.170 --> 02:25:58.315
ASHLEY: Dang it.

02:25:58.315 --> 02:26:03.668
MARISHA: We have to stop them before they close
these doors. If they close the doors, it's over.

02:26:03.668 --> 02:26:05.157
SAM: Do we see them closing the doors?

02:26:05.157 --> 02:26:07.957
MATT: They've just opened the doors and are
beginning to enter.

02:26:07.957 --> 02:26:10.099
MARISHA: Percy, go. Get their attention. Percy!

02:26:10.099 --> 02:26:12.756
TALIESIN: I'm heading up.

02:26:12.756 --> 02:26:19.163
LAURA: I'm going to stay hidden as my-- oh, god--
and I'm going to dip the rest of

02:26:19.163 --> 02:26:20.252
my arrows in holy oil.

02:26:20.252 --> 02:26:21.594
MATT: Okay, as you're stepping up.

02:26:21.594 --> 02:26:23.865
SAM: I inspire Pike real quick, just before the
battle.

02:26:23.865 --> 02:26:26.264
MATT: Okay, what do you do to inspire her?

02:26:26.264 --> 02:26:34.195
SAM: I just look at her and I say, roses are red,
violets are blue, we're both gnomes, and you are

02:26:34.195 --> 02:26:35.976
so foxy!

02:26:35.976 --> 02:26:37.837
(laughter)

02:26:37.837 --> 02:26:40.109
SAM: That's it.

02:26:40.109 --> 02:26:41.391
MATT: All right.

02:26:41.391 --> 02:26:44.833
MARISHA: When I look up, can I see the ceiling
now?

02:26:44.833 --> 02:26:53.429
MATT: Looking up, you can see the roof is carved
earth. There is no loose stone; it looks like this

02:26:53.429 --> 02:26:56.609
chamber has been carefully hollowed out over
time.

02:26:56.609 --> 02:27:01.581
MARISHA: Can I see a root system of a really
deep-running tree?

02:27:01.581 --> 02:27:03.541
MATT: Currently? No, you cannot.

02:27:03.541 --> 02:27:04.894
MARISHA: Fuck. Okay.

02:27:04.894 --> 02:27:07.168
MATT: Percy, what are you doing?

02:27:07.168 --> 02:27:10.649
TALIESIN: I'm walking up the steps. I'm putting
the mask on.

02:27:10.649 --> 02:27:17.161
MATT: As you put the mask on and you begin to
ascend, you can feel the nerves tickle your belly

02:27:17.161 --> 02:27:23.383
and you know what you're about to encounter, and
