02:27:23.383 --> 02:27:29.640
your neck, and as you do, (whoosh) the smoke
begins to billow out from under your collar and

02:27:29.640 --> 02:27:31.204
out of your sleeves.

02:27:31.204 --> 02:27:34.584
TALIESIN: I make my way to the top of the stairs.

02:27:34.584 --> 02:27:40.711
MATT: Trinket coming slowly behind you. They open
the doors and they're beginning to step into the

02:27:40.711 --> 02:27:41.840
chamber.

02:27:41.840 --> 02:27:43.536
TALIESIN: Sylas!

02:27:43.536 --> 02:27:47.265
MATT: They stop. Both Lord and Lady Briarwood look
over their shoulder.

02:27:47.265 --> 02:27:49.633
TALIESIN: A moment of your time.

02:27:49.633 --> 02:27:59.111
MATT: They look at each other, (sighs) close the
chamber door. Sylas reaches out and grabs

02:27:59.111 --> 02:28:06.524
something or pushes something that's out of sight,
and then they both turn and begin to step forward

02:28:06.524 --> 02:28:12.609
a little bit, with Vax and Cassandra flanking
them, stopping right outside of the doors.

02:28:12.609 --> 02:28:21.979
MARISHA: Okay, as he's distracting them, get in
position? Try and stealth behind these

02:28:22.056 --> 02:28:23.181
buildings?

02:28:23.181 --> 02:28:27.158
MATT: So you guys are on technically that side and
that side of the pyramid right now.

02:28:27.158 --> 02:28:32.912
MARISHA: Yeah. It looks like there's pillars and
shit?

02:28:32.912 --> 02:28:37.544
MATT: Yeah, the pillars are evenly spread around
the entire chamber.

02:28:37.544 --> 02:28:39.918
MARISHA: Yeah, let's come in from the back. I
don't know what the gnomes are doing.

02:28:39.918 --> 02:28:45.018
MATT: You guys would have to have come around the
corner, and this is the walkway here, so you'd be

02:28:45.018 --> 02:28:46.387
coming in from this side.

02:28:46.387 --> 02:28:49.920
SAM: Stay out of sight, but get as close as we
can.

02:28:49.987 --> 02:28:51.969
LAURA: I float closer in the darkness.

02:28:51.969 --> 02:28:54.022
MATT: Okay, over here?

02:28:54.022 --> 02:28:55.222
LAURA: Up. Up.

02:28:55.222 --> 02:28:59.813
MATT: Up, up? My platforms seem to have gone
missing for the preparation of this game, but

02:28:59.813 --> 02:29:03.857
we'll say for the time being, you are up here.

02:29:03.857 --> 02:29:17.049
TALIESIN: My hands are on a device which I have
made that's on my hip that I'm ready to begin

02:29:17.049 --> 02:29:18.911
using at a moment's notice.

02:29:18.911 --> 02:29:20.574
SAM: It's a French tickler.

02:29:20.574 --> 02:29:25.348
TALIESIN: It's the most ticklish French tickler
you've ever seen, baby.

02:29:25.348 --> 02:29:29.521
LAURA: I don't have something planned. I'm just
going to go.

02:29:29.521 --> 02:29:34.707
SAM: What's this? What's going on?

02:29:34.707 --> 02:29:38.430
TALIESIN: We have debts to settle, Sylas.

02:29:38.430 --> 02:29:51.908
MATT: "And apparently, you and your friends are
obnoxious enough to not stay dead."

02:29:51.908 --> 02:29:56.896
TALIESIN: They were kind enough to make sure that
I made my way here to face you.

02:29:56.896 --> 02:30:06.713
MATT: (chuckles) "Well, perhaps this evening won't
be so boring after all, will it?" And Sylas looks

02:30:06.713 --> 02:30:08.594
over to Delilah.

02:30:08.594 --> 02:30:11.675
Delilah gives him a look, too, and says, "Very
well."

02:30:11.743 --> 02:30:26.692
TALIESIN: The darkness demands your soul, Sylas.
I'm going to cast Hex on Lady Briarwood and pull

02:30:26.692 --> 02:30:31.192
my smoke bomb at the exact same second and throw
it at them.

