beginning, but I thought I was going to hide

03:15:52.132 --> 03:15:54.067
again. What a waste.

03:15:54.067 --> 03:16:00.936
MATT: All righty. So that ends your turn. Percy,
you're up. Actually, at the end of your turn,

03:16:00.936 --> 03:16:04.922
Sylas is going to use another one of his legendary
actions to make another attack on Percy.

03:16:04.922 --> 03:16:06.700
TALIESIN: God-fucking-damn it.

03:16:06.700 --> 03:16:08.506
MARISHA: How many of those fuckers does he have?

03:16:08.506 --> 03:16:09.996
MATT: Oh, he gets three every turn.

03:16:09.996 --> 03:16:11.366
MARISHA: He gets three every turn?!

03:16:11.366 --> 03:16:12.413
TRAVIS: Every round.

03:16:12.413 --> 03:16:20.635
MATT: After every round, I mean. That will be-- he
has disadvantage, so he doesn't crit. (laughs) But

03:16:20.635 --> 03:16:22.614
that is still a 30.

03:16:22.614 --> 03:16:24.964
SAM and TALIESIN: 30?!

03:16:24.964 --> 03:16:30.375
MATT: He rolled a 19 and a 20. My rolls for him
have been pretty good these past few rounds. So

03:16:30.375 --> 03:16:34.083
that's another 13 points of slashing damage
against you.

03:16:34.083 --> 03:16:35.150
TALIESIN: All right!

03:16:35.150 --> 03:16:36.333
MATT: And make a constitution saving throw.

03:16:36.333 --> 03:16:37.619
TALIESIN: And make another constitution saving
throw.

03:16:37.619 --> 03:16:39.078
MARISHA: How are you?

03:16:39.078 --> 03:16:42.107
SAM: Pike helped.

03:16:42.107 --> 03:16:44.511
TALIESIN: 13 points of damage?

03:16:44.511 --> 03:16:46.532
MATT: Yep! And then roll another constitution--

03:16:46.532 --> 03:16:49.801
TALIESIN: Saving throw. That's 18.

03:16:49.801 --> 03:16:52.877
MATT: 18? You're fine. Okay. Continue with your
turn?

03:16:52.877 --> 03:17:02.465
TALIESIN: Still, he keeps getting in my shit.
There's just no getting the fuck away from him, is

03:17:02.465 --> 03:17:09.973
there? That's fine. Well he's in the 30-foot
radius of light right now, so do my attacks have

03:17:09.973 --> 03:17:11.061
an advantage against him?

03:17:11.061 --> 03:17:13.337
MATT: No, he just has disadvantage on attack rolls
and ability checks.

03:17:13.337 --> 03:17:18.945
TALIESIN: Okay. There's just no backing away from
him right now. I'm going to have to wait for him

03:17:18.945 --> 03:17:21.135
to try and break off from me through Grog.

03:17:21.135 --> 03:17:25.016
MARISHA: He wants you. He wants your bod.

03:17:25.016 --> 03:17:31.002
TALIESIN: Yeah, I get it. So, everyone wants my
bod. I'm going to take three slashes with the

03:17:31.002 --> 03:17:33.550
sword again since I'm too close to use the
guns.

03:17:33.550 --> 03:17:35.351
MATT: Okay.

03:17:35.441 --> 03:17:38.016
TALIESIN: 25?

03:17:38.016 --> 03:17:40.394
MATT: 25? Hits.

03:17:40.394 --> 03:17:42.891
TALIESIN: 14?

03:17:42.891 --> 03:17:44.189
MATT: 14 misses.

03:17:44.189 --> 03:17:45.667
SAM: You got inspiration!

03:17:45.667 --> 03:17:48.954
TALIESIN: I know, but I don't want to waste it on
this. And 13.

03:17:48.954 --> 03:17:53.743
MATT: Only one strike hits. Twice you pierce, he's
just too fast, on one side strikes off his armor

03:17:53.827 --> 03:17:59.448
harmlessly. One strike does manage to get over the
collarbone of his armor and pierce into his chest.

03:17:59.448 --> 03:18:01.754
He goes (groan) from the pain. Go ahead and roll
damage.

03:18:01.754 --> 03:18:05.179
MARISHA: He's got more where that came from
though. He's a very inspiring person.

03:18:05.179 --> 03:18:09.814
TALIESIN: I want you to inspire other people. 12.

03:18:09.814 --> 03:18:15.622
MATT: 12 damage, all right. That ends your go.

03:18:15.622 --> 03:18:18.291
TALIESIN: Save it for a shot.

03:18:18.291 --> 03:18:33.736
MATT: Cassandra is going to-- actually, she's
going to move alongside, still staying next to

03:18:33.736 --> 03:18:37.515
Grog. And moves up with her blade out towards
you.

03:18:37.515 --> 03:18:38.784
TALIESIN: Goddamn it.

03:18:38.784 --> 03:18:54.639
MATT: Looks over at Sylas, and Sylas is nudging
with his eyes. And she looks at you. And she drops

03:18:54.639 --> 03:19:00.364
her blade for a second. And just stands there for
a second, looking at the scenario. And her turn is

03:19:00.364 --> 03:19:01.826
spent there.

03:19:01.826 --> 03:19:03.299
TALIESIN: Yeah!

03:19:03.299 --> 03:19:05.230
LAURA: She's trying! She's trying to fight it!

03:19:05.230 --> 03:19:08.866
MATT: Keyleth, you're up.

03:19:08.866 --> 03:19:11.278
MARISHA: Knock her out. Me?

03:19:11.278 --> 03:19:12.348
MATT: Yeah.

03:19:12.348 --> 03:19:14.536
MARISHA: Okay. How close am I to Sylas?

03:19:14.536 --> 03:19:17.847
MATT: You are currently 25 feet from him.

03:19:17.847 --> 03:19:33.343
MARISHA: Okay. Here's what I'm going to do. Seeing
that Sylas is distracted, I'm going to run up, and

03:19:33.343 --> 03:19:39.400
I'm going to put my hands on his back, and I'm
going to cast Sunbeam through him and try and hit

03:19:39.400 --> 03:19:41.158
Lady Briarwood as well.

03:19:41.158 --> 03:19:44.968
MATT: There is a pillar between the two of them,
so it won't go through the pillar, unfortunately.

03:19:44.968 --> 03:19:51.787
MARISHA: Then I just hug him, and I'm like,
(sings) Let the sunshine in!

03:19:51.787 --> 03:19:58.377
MARISHA, LAURA, TRAVIS, and SAM: (sing) Let the
sunshine in. The sun shine in!

03:19:58.377 --> 03:20:02.612
TALIESIN: Really? You're going to kill him with
hugs. This is the most Keyleth

03:20:02.612 --> 03:20:03.781
thing I've ever heard.

03:20:03.781 --> 03:20:06.807
MARISHA: I'm trying to do a concentrated Sunbeam.
I don't know if it's going to help.

03:20:06.807 --> 03:20:09.832
MATT: Go ahead and roll damage.

03:20:09.832 --> 03:20:13.139
MARISHA: Balls, fuck, shit. Ten.

03:20:13.139 --> 03:20:16.629
MATT: He's going to use his second legendary
action to automatically succeed the saving throw.

03:20:16.629 --> 03:20:21.074
MARISHA: 25, total.

03:20:21.074 --> 03:20:25.486
MATT: 25, okay. So that's 13. This time, as you
blast into his back you see the light burns

03:20:25.486 --> 03:20:28.929
through parts of his shoulder and chunks of his
flesh are actually blown through his armor. His

03:20:28.929 --> 03:20:33.320
armor streaks open for a second. He's like,
(pained grunt). Smoke is now sizzling up around

03:20:33.320 --> 03:20:35.965
him and he looks over his shoulder with this angry
red gaze--

03:20:35.965 --> 03:20:39.591
MARISHA: And I take my nails and dig them in a
little bit.

03:20:39.591 --> 03:20:47.177
MATT: At the end of your turn, he uses another
legendary action to then try and shove you off and

03:20:47.177 --> 03:20:53.051
arc upwards with his sword across the front of
your chest. Even with disadvantage, that's still

03:20:53.051 --> 03:20:54.223
19.

03:20:54.223 --> 03:20:55.322
MARISHA: Hits.

03:20:55.322 --> 03:21:02.718
MATT: All right. You take 16 points of slashing
damage, then make a constitution saving throw.

03:21:02.718 --> 03:21:19.467
MARISHA: Oh, wait. Hang on. Okay, has to be over
12, right? A saving throw? 17.

03:21:19.565 --> 03:21:26.919
MATT: 17? Okay, you resist the effect of the
sword. That ends your turn. Back at the top. Sylas

03:21:26.919 --> 03:21:35.655
right now is like (panting). He's looking pretty
rough. Lady Delilah runs up around the side and

03:21:35.655 --> 03:21:42.267
goes, "My love, we're not ready, but the
timetable's been pushed. We have no choice." And

03:21:42.267 --> 03:21:44.302
she wraps her arms around them and they both--

03:21:44.302 --> 03:21:48.584
SAM: I cast Counterspell as a reaction.

03:21:48.584 --> 03:21:50.710
MATT: What's the range on Counterspell?

03:21:50.710 --> 03:21:52.559
LIAM: Not again!

03:21:52.559 --> 03:21:54.676
SAM: 60 feet. Am I close enough?

03:21:54.676 --> 03:21:56.836
TRAVIS: I don't think you are.

03:21:56.836 --> 03:22:04.146
MATT: 60 feet. (counting)

03:22:04.146 --> 03:22:06.392
She is in range! All right.

03:22:06.392 --> 03:22:09.111
(cheering)

03:22:09.111 --> 03:22:16.303
SAM: I say-- shit. Do I know what she's casting?
Am I familiar with it?

03:22:16.303 --> 03:22:19.710
MATT: You're familiar with the actions about it,
so you'd have an idea, yes.

03:22:19.710 --> 03:22:21.464
SAM: Do I know what level it is?

03:22:21.464 --> 03:22:22.990
MATT: You don't know what level, no.

03:22:22.990 --> 03:22:31.621
SAM: Okay, so I'll say, (sings) Huh! That's the
sound of the gnome, fucking with your spell!

03:22:31.621 --> 03:22:36.422
Yeah. And I'll cast it at level four.

03:22:36.422 --> 03:22:43.736
MATT: At level four? All right. So I need you to
roll--

03:22:43.736 --> 03:22:45.432
SAM: Fuck, so it's higher than that.

03:22:45.432 --> 03:22:46.958
MATT: She's casting it at 5th-level.

03:22:46.958 --> 03:22:49.241
SAM: What do I roll?

03:22:49.241 --> 03:22:55.609
MATT: For this, roll a d20 and add your charisma
bonus to it. So plus five.

03:22:55.609 --> 03:22:56.992
SAM: I'm a charismatic guy.

03:22:56.992 --> 03:22:58.116
MATT: You are.

03:22:58.116 --> 03:23:00.066
SAM: 23.

03:23:00.066 --> 03:23:05.305
MATT: And with that, she grasps him. The Door
begins to open, and then flickers.

03:23:05.305 --> 03:23:07.453
(cheering)

03:23:07.453 --> 03:23:09.621
SAM: Stay.

03:23:09.621 --> 03:23:27.413
MATT: She whips around, (growls). Okay. Yeah,
that's going to end her turn. All right. With

03:23:27.413 --> 03:23:31.107
this, that ends her turn. Scanlan, you're up.

03:23:31.107 --> 03:23:39.017
SAM: Grog? I hold my turn.

03:23:39.017 --> 03:23:41.139
MATT: Okay.

03:23:41.139 --> 03:23:51.642
SAM: I'm sorry, I hold my action and my movement.
And instead I will inspire Grog with a little

03:23:51.642 --> 03:23:57.770
harmonica ditty. (harmonica)

03:23:57.770 --> 03:23:59.147
TALIESIN: Jaunty!

03:23:59.147 --> 03:24:01.160
MATT: Okay. All righty.

03:24:01.160 --> 03:24:03.892
SAM: Oh, is it his turn now, next?

03:24:03.892 --> 03:24:07.215
MATT: No, it is not. You hold the rest of your
turn?

03:24:07.215 --> 03:24:08.121
SAM: I hold.

03:24:08.121 --> 03:24:12.731
MATT: All right. Vax. Still left there, staring
into space.

03:24:12.731 --> 03:24:14.362
LIAM: Constitution save at this point?

03:24:14.362 --> 03:24:16.417
MATT: This would be a constitution saving throw
again, yeah.

03:24:16.417 --> 03:24:18.836
LAURA: If only Scanlan had inspired you.

03:24:18.836 --> 03:24:20.820
LIAM: If only. No.

03:24:20.820 --> 03:24:25.614
MATT: Still left there. Useless. Staring in the
distance.

03:24:25.614 --> 03:24:28.653
LIAM: Thinking of IKEA instructions.

03:24:28.653 --> 03:24:33.346
LAURA: Well, I thought Trinket would be able to
help you, but you're not doing anything.

03:24:33.346 --> 03:24:35.032
MATT: Grog, now you're up.

03:24:35.032 --> 03:24:37.057
TRAVIS: So for the Boots of Levitation--

03:24:37.057 --> 03:24:38.406
MATT: Actually, before that happens.

03:24:38.406 --> 03:24:39.740
TALIESIN: Goddamn it.

03:24:39.740 --> 03:24:44.485
MATT: At the end of your turn, he's going to use
his third legendary action in this round to,

03:24:44.485 --> 03:24:48.365
without any attacks of opportunity, move.

03:24:48.365 --> 03:24:56.845
TRAVIS: Is that Lord Briarwood?

03:24:56.845 --> 03:25:04.275
MATT: Yes. He pulls away, still trying to get out
of the range of the sunlight.

03:25:04.275 --> 03:25:12.587
TRAVIS: Okay. The Boots of Levitation. It says it
requires an action to levitate?

03:25:12.587 --> 03:25:13.578
MATT: Correct.

03:25:13.578 --> 03:25:16.826
TRAVIS: Could I do three attacks? Or just two, and
then have the action left over?

03:25:16.826 --> 03:25:19.930
MATT: You could action and then you'd have your
one bonus strike as a frenzied rage.

03:25:19.930 --> 03:25:25.857
SAM: Can you put on the boots as a bonus action?

03:25:25.857 --> 03:25:28.178
TRAVIS: I'm already wearing them.

03:25:28.178 --> 03:25:29.798
LAURA: Just set it up.

03:25:29.798 --> 03:25:32.944
TRAVIS: Set it up?

03:25:32.944 --> 03:25:35.078
LAURA: You could do it on this move. Then on the
next move--

03:25:35.078 --> 03:25:36.386
SAM: It's too long.

03:25:36.386 --> 03:25:40.628
TRAVIS: Yeah, fuck it. I'll take all three strikes
at Lady Briarwood.

03:25:40.628 --> 03:25:47.074
MATT: Okay! So you move in, to there. Go ahead and
make your attacks.

03:25:47.074 --> 03:25:49.698
TRAVIS: That's good. 25?

03:25:49.698 --> 03:25:53.949
MATT: You have disadvantage on these strikes, as
her cloak has now kicked back in.

03:25:53.949 --> 03:25:56.196
TRAVIS: 17?

03:25:56.196 --> 03:26:02.556
MATT: 17 misses. First blow passes through her
form harmlessly.

03:26:02.556 --> 03:26:04.200
SAM: You're inspired!

03:26:04.200 --> 03:26:06.892
TRAVIS: I'll use that inspiration on that one. No,
not on that one.

03:26:06.892 --> 03:26:10.110
MATT: So the first one missed, the second one
missed?

03:26:10.110 --> 03:26:13.368
TRAVIS: The first and the second one missed.

03:26:13.368 --> 03:26:16.137
MATT: The first strike, with disadvantage.

03:26:16.137 --> 03:26:25.210
TRAVIS: Jesus Christ. 20.

03:26:25.210 --> 03:26:33.560
MATT: 20 hits. As this one actually finds purchase
on her torso, the shimmering effect vanishes once

03:26:33.560 --> 03:26:35.704
again, the cloak falling limp to her side.

03:26:35.704 --> 03:26:38.127
TRAVIS: 19.

03:26:38.127 --> 03:26:45.671
MATT: 19. Okay. The hammer slams into the front of
her chest, and she goes, (panting).

03:26:45.671 --> 03:26:50.526
She's starting to get almost feral in her
frustration.

03:26:50.526 --> 03:26:53.689
MARISHA: Feral?

03:26:53.689 --> 03:26:56.284
MATT: (growls) She's angry.

03:26:56.284 --> 03:26:57.313
MARISHA: Okay.

03:26:57.313 --> 03:27:07.534
SAM: I will take my move now. And I will (singing)
Bigby's Hand! (speaking) And I will raise up the

03:27:07.534 --> 03:27:11.559
hand somewhere between Sylas and Lady.

03:27:11.559 --> 03:27:19.009
(cheering)

03:27:19.009 --> 03:27:21.250
MARISHA: Look at that sexy hand!

03:27:21.250 --> 03:27:23.325
SAM: Mister is injured, right?

03:27:23.325 --> 03:27:25.246
LIAM: He's looking rough!

03:27:25.246 --> 03:27:29.462
SAM: And she is not flickering anymore, so I can
get a good hit on her, as well?

03:27:29.462 --> 03:27:32.394
MATT: Correct. Yeah, the disadvantage on attacks
against her has faded.

03:27:32.394 --> 03:27:37.460
SAM: I will go on her. I don't like her, so I'll
punch her in the face.

03:27:37.460 --> 03:27:43.842
MATT: Okay! Goes forward. Go ahead and roll for
your spell attack against her.

03:27:43.842 --> 03:27:47.391
SAM: Oh, okay. Is this through the cone?

03:27:47.391 --> 03:27:52.399
MATT: There isn't a cone aspect to it.

03:27:52.399 --> 03:27:54.980
SAM: Oh, so do I just roll to hit?

03:27:54.980 --> 03:27:59.208
MATT: Here you go, I'll pull it up right here. All
right, this is the clenched fist? You make a melee

03:27:59.208 --> 03:28:01.270
spell attack. Roll a d20 and add your spell attack
bonus.

03:28:01.270 --> 03:28:07.329
SAM: Okay. (giggles) Spell attack. 16?

03:28:07.329 --> 03:28:12.395
MATT: 16. As the fist (whoosh) towards her, she
ducks and it slams into the pillar, cracking the

03:28:12.395 --> 03:28:14.205
stone slightly.

03:28:14.205 --> 03:28:20.654
SAM: Shit. How far away am I from both of them?

03:28:20.654 --> 03:28:28.206
MATT: From both of them? You are about 45 feet
from Sylas and about 65 feet from her.

03:28:28.206 --> 03:28:32.939
SAM: I get ten feet closer to her.

03:28:32.939 --> 03:28:35.264
LAURA: (quietly) Can you inspire Vax?

03:28:35.264 --> 03:28:39.680
SAM: This is the rest of my turn. I already used
it to inspire Grog.

03:28:39.680 --> 03:28:49.007
MATT: All right, so that's the end of Grog's turn?
All right. It is now Sylas's turn. Sylas is going

03:28:49.007 --> 03:28:56.126
to step off to the side here, stepping off to the
stairs to get out of the range of the sunlight.

03:28:56.126 --> 03:29:01.573
Just outside of the radius of it. And, glancing
over at you, after you just unleashed that swing

03:29:01.573 --> 03:29:08.807
of attacks towards his wife, he goes, "You. Help
us." Make a wisdom saving throw with advantage.

03:29:08.807 --> 03:29:10.140
TRAVIS: With advantage?

03:29:10.140 --> 03:29:11.448
MATT: With advantage.

03:29:11.448 --> 03:29:13.132
LIAM: Roll. High.

03:29:13.132 --> 03:29:15.535
MARISHA: Roll like you're Percy!

03:29:15.535 --> 03:29:18.700
MATT: What did you roll?

03:29:18.700 --> 03:29:21.882
TRAVIS: A four.

03:29:21.882 --> 03:29:23.850
MATT: With advantage?

03:29:23.850 --> 03:29:25.140
TRAVIS: Yeah.

03:29:25.140 --> 03:29:30.938
MATT: Wow. With that, Grog, now you realize you've
been on the wrong side of this battlefield the

03:29:30.938 --> 03:29:36.615
whole time. And your allies are being assaulted by
individuals that claim to be your friends but

03:29:36.690 --> 03:29:42.166
might be completely against this whole
circumstance. Your allegiance switches for now to

03:29:42.166 --> 03:29:49.048
defend them at all costs. That's going to end his
turn. Pike!

03:29:49.048 --> 03:29:53.821
TRAVIS: Wait. I'm raging. Can I be charmed?

03:29:53.821 --> 03:29:57.535
(cheering)

03:29:57.535 --> 03:30:06.524
MATT: That's a good notification to make. The
charm effect hits your mind. This is why you read

03:30:06.524 --> 03:30:09.954
your abilities, guys. I don't remember all the
details.

03:30:09.954 --> 03:30:12.307
SAM: Best question of the night!

03:30:12.307 --> 03:30:14.952
LIAM: Oh my god!

03:30:14.952 --> 03:30:17.770
TRAVIS: Intelligence of six. It takes a second!

03:30:17.770 --> 03:30:24.945
MATT: As you see this look, you feel the influence
begin to pry. But it isn't enough to push through

03:30:24.945 --> 03:30:26.686
the red and blazing anger--

03:30:26.686 --> 03:30:28.254
TALIESIN: Yeah!

03:30:28.254 --> 03:30:32.145
LIAM: That was the thin red line, Travis.

03:30:32.145 --> 03:30:40.498
MATT: With that, you see the expression of intent
and some worry on Sylas's face, ending his turn.

03:30:40.498 --> 03:30:42.005
Pike, what are you doing?

03:30:42.005 --> 03:30:51.201
ASHLEY: My turn? Okay, so I would like to Channel
Divinity and Destroy Undead?

03:30:51.201 --> 03:30:52.377
MARISHA: Yes!

03:30:52.377 --> 03:30:54.735
SAM: This is what we hired you for!

03:30:54.735 --> 03:31:02.119
MATT: Just as a heads up, Destroy Undead, for the
most part, is only effective against lower-level

03:31:02.214 --> 03:31:07.977
undead. Knowing that Sylas is a vampire, it might
not have the desired effect that you're thinking

03:31:07.977 --> 03:31:09.214
it might.

03:31:09.214 --> 03:31:10.121
ASHLEY: Okay.

03:31:10.121 --> 03:31:16.056
MATT: Just as a heads up. You can still Turn
Undead and it may make him afraid of you.

03:31:16.056 --> 03:31:18.187
But that is--

03:31:18.187 --> 03:31:19.579
ASHLEY: Let's give it a try!

03:31:19.579 --> 03:31:20.854
TRAVIS: I like it!

03:31:20.854 --> 03:31:22.925
MATT: All right. We're bringing this up here real
fast.

03:31:22.925 --> 03:31:24.970
ASHLEY: How close am I to him?

03:31:24.970 --> 03:31:26.125
LAURA: Pretty close.

03:31:26.125 --> 03:31:28.152
LIAM: Pretty close. 20 feet.

03:31:28.152 --> 03:31:34.450
ASHLEY: You know what, I feel like I want to hit
him with my Mace of Disruption.

03:31:34.450 --> 03:31:35.844
MATT: If you want to!

03:31:35.844 --> 03:31:37.810
LIAM: He's rough.

03:31:37.810 --> 03:31:44.530
MATT: So instead you run up, charging towards him,
shield up in front of you. Pike, her blazing

03:31:44.530 --> 03:31:49.188
radiant form, the energy rippling off from behind
her. You pull back your mace, and as it swings

03:31:49.188 --> 03:31:54.080
through the air, a quick flicker of angelic wings
appear at your back as your mace swings down

03:31:54.080 --> 03:31:55.745
towards him. Go ahead and roll your attack.

03:31:55.745 --> 03:32:05.916
ASHLEY: Come on. Okay, 16. But I'm going to use
War God's Blessing and add ten.

03:32:05.916 --> 03:32:07.328
MATT: Yes, you can do that.

03:32:07.328 --> 03:32:10.205
TRAVIS: War God's Blessing?

03:32:10.205 --> 03:32:14.832
MATT: Okay. War God's Blessing.

03:32:14.832 --> 03:32:18.574
TRAVIS: She has inspiration from you too, right?

03:32:18.574 --> 03:32:21.382
SAM: But has she rolled yet?

03:32:21.382 --> 03:32:24.655
MATT: Yep, when any creature within 30 feet makes
an attack roll you can use your reaction to grant

03:32:24.655 --> 03:32:36.812
that creature-- usually it's against other
creatures. Okay. War God's Blessing you can only

03:32:36.812 --> 03:32:41.403
use on other creatures, but you do have Channel
Divinity: Guided Strike, which you can use on

03:32:41.403 --> 03:32:45.145
yourself. It's essentially the same thing. You
give yourself plus ten bonus to the roll.

03:32:45.145 --> 03:32:46.506
ASHLEY: Okay.

03:32:46.506 --> 03:32:48.647
MATT: So you use your Channel Divinity: Guided
Strike instead?

03:32:48.647 --> 03:32:49.663
ASHLEY: Got it.

03:32:49.663 --> 03:32:52.068
MATT: Okay. So that would bring you to 26? That
would hit.

03:32:52.068 --> 03:32:53.114
ASHLEY: Okay.

03:32:53.114 --> 03:33:01.232
MATT: Okay. All right, so you slam down onto Sylas
with your Mace of Disruption. Go ahead and roll

03:33:01.232 --> 03:33:03.227
damage on that. He is considered an undead.

03:33:03.227 --> 03:33:04.374
LAURA: Kill him!

03:33:04.374 --> 03:33:05.516
LIAM: A thousand pieces.

03:33:05.516 --> 03:33:07.474
ASHLEY: How many times do I roll?

03:33:07.474 --> 03:33:12.064
MATT: Well you roll your damage, and it does an
additional 2d6 radiant damage.

03:33:12.064 --> 03:33:13.460
TALIESIN: Damn!

03:33:13.460 --> 03:33:16.792
LIAM: The mace damage--

03:33:16.792 --> 03:33:20.350
ASHLEY: Okay, got it. Sorry guys, sorry. I'm
back.

03:33:20.350 --> 03:33:29.811
LIAM: Break into a million pieces.

03:33:29.811 --> 03:33:34.302
LAURA: I love you, too. Your headset looks really
pretty!

03:33:34.302 --> 03:33:35.974
ASHLEY: Thanks!

03:33:35.974 --> 03:33:41.559
TALIESIN: It's like looking at the Technicolor
logo.

03:33:41.559 --> 03:33:44.564
TRAVIS: Everybody get their heads down, like
Ashley.

03:33:44.564 --> 03:33:45.974
ASHLEY: Okay, 21!

03:33:46.045 --> 03:33:47.476
MATT: 21 points of damage?

03:33:47.476 --> 03:33:48.690
ASHLEY: Yeah.

03:33:48.690 --> 03:33:54.962
MATT: Okay, as per the effect of the spell, he now
has to make a wisdom saving throw, which he does

03:33:54.962 --> 03:34:00.751
succeed. If he failed, he would have been
destroyed. However, on a success, he is still

03:34:00.751 --> 03:34:06.910
afraid of you. So he is now considered afraid of
Pike. Disadvantage on all attack rolls.

03:34:06.910 --> 03:34:10.154
TRAVIS: Fuck yeah, he is! Let them know, Pike!

03:34:10.154 --> 03:34:14.809
MATT: Until the end of your next turn. Awesome,
Pike! Anything else you want to do on your turn,

03:34:14.809 --> 03:34:16.207
or is that it?

03:34:16.207 --> 03:34:21.407
ASHLEY: I would love to go up to Vax, but I don't
think I can, right?

03:34:21.407 --> 03:34:22.532
MATT: No.

03:34:22.532 --> 03:34:25.754
ASHLEY: Okay. Then I'll stay, I'll stay.

03:34:25.754 --> 03:34:28.416
MATT: Okay, that ends your turn Pike. Vex, you're
up.

03:34:28.416 --> 03:34:30.208
LAURA: Awesome, I'm going to shoot him.

03:34:30.208 --> 03:34:31.581
MATT: You're going to shoot Sylas?

03:34:31.581 --> 03:34:33.001
LAURA: Yeah, with holy arrows.

03:34:33.001 --> 03:34:37.208
MATT: Okay.

03:34:37.208 --> 03:34:41.094
LAURA: That does not hit him. Come on. 19?

03:34:41.094 --> 03:34:44.701
MATT: 19 hits. Just barely.

03:34:44.701 --> 03:34:52.442
LAURA: 17, plus two holy damage.

03:34:52.442 --> 03:34:54.910
MATT: So the first attack missed?

03:34:54.910 --> 03:34:55.915
LAURA: Yeah.

03:34:55.915 --> 03:34:56.972
MATT: And the second one hit?

03:34:56.972 --> 03:34:58.029
LAURA: Yeah. 19.

03:34:58.029 --> 03:35:02.340
MATT: 19 damage, all right. As the arrows (thud,
thud), one hits the armor and streaks off and

03:35:02.340 --> 03:35:07.117
shatters against the green glass stonework of the
top of the ziggurat. The second one strikes him in

03:35:07.117 --> 03:35:11.448
the back of the neck. You see a blast of radiant
energy crosses his throat. He reaches up and tries

03:35:11.448 --> 03:35:16.100
to grab for the arrow, but the arrow itself is
disintegrated by the blast of holy energy, leaving

03:35:16.100 --> 03:35:21.444
a gaping wound in the back of his neck. He's still
standing, but you can see his form is now falling

03:35:21.444 --> 03:35:26.300
apart. Parts of ash are beginning to pour off his
flesh. He's looking really rough.

03:35:26.300 --> 03:35:32.427
All right. That finishes Vex's turn. Unless you
want to move? Stay where you are?

03:35:32.427 --> 03:35:40.232
LAURA: I'm afraid my flying potion's going to
start to wear off soon, so I'm going to move. Is

03:35:40.232 --> 03:35:43.608
there a roof? On that middle compound building?

03:35:43.608 --> 03:35:45.509
MATT: From what you can see, no. It is open.

03:35:45.589 --> 03:35:46.357
LAURA: Oh, really?

03:35:46.357 --> 03:35:47.205
MATT: Yeah.

03:35:47.205 --> 03:35:48.811
LAURA: Can I land on top of the pillar?

03:35:48.811 --> 03:35:51.050
MATT: The pillar holds a slight overhang, so you
can land on top of the overhang if you want.

03:35:51.050 --> 03:35:52.012
LAURA: Yeah!

03:35:52.012 --> 03:35:56.208
MATT: All right, so you land on top of the
overhang, stopping there. Which blocks all view

03:35:56.208 --> 03:35:58.028
from beneath this line, there, but--

03:35:58.028 --> 03:35:59.184
LAURA: But I can still see--

03:35:59.184 --> 03:36:00.486
MATT: You could peek around if you want.

03:36:00.486 --> 03:36:01.432
LAURA: Yeah, okay.

03:36:01.432 --> 03:36:02.781
MATT: Okay. Percy, you're up.

03:36:02.781 --> 03:36:13.689
TALIESIN: Okay. First thing I'm going to do is I'm
going to pull out the Pepperbox. And I'm going to

03:36:13.689 --> 03:36:17.397
take a shot at Sylas, and I'm going to get him to
drop his sword.

03:36:17.397 --> 03:36:19.471
MATT: Okay.

03:36:19.471 --> 03:36:24.513
TALIESIN: So, let's see.

03:36:24.513 --> 03:36:25.742
SAM: You're not going to kill him?

03:36:25.742 --> 03:36:29.041
TALIESIN: Nope! Not yet. Just in case things go
bad-- and I also just want to make sure-- that's a

03:36:29.041 --> 03:36:30.405
26?

03:36:30.405 --> 03:36:37.517
MATT: Hits. No damage, but he drops his weapon?

03:36:37.517 --> 03:36:38.645
TALIESIN: But he drops his weapon.

03:36:38.645 --> 03:36:43.014
MATT: So with that, (bullet impact) the blade he
was holding clatters to the ground before him, the

03:36:43.014 --> 03:36:46.054
onyx blade shining in what low light there is
around this temple.

03:36:46.054 --> 03:36:54.059
TALIESIN: Now I'm going to take a shot at him.
That's a 29.

03:36:54.059 --> 03:36:55.403
MATT: Hits.

03:36:55.403 --> 03:37:06.740
TALIESIN: That does... ten points of damage?

03:37:06.740 --> 03:37:14.925
MATT: Ten points of damage? As that bullet hits
him (soft impact) you see he begins to dissipate.

03:37:14.925 --> 03:37:25.279
And then turns into a mist form in the space where
he is. He is currently now a form of mist.

03:37:25.279 --> 03:37:28.835
LAURA: So he can go heal himself unless we can get
him.

03:37:28.835 --> 03:37:40.985
TALIESIN: She's going to take care of this. How
close am I to Lady Briarwood?

03:37:40.985 --> 03:37:42.526
MATT: You're ten feet from her.

03:37:42.526 --> 03:37:56.903
TALIESIN: Ten feet? That's close enough, I guess.
I'm going to take a couple of steps back, and I'm

03:37:56.903 --> 03:38:02.535
going to do a fire shot and an ice shot with my
last two shots.

03:38:02.535 --> 03:38:04.655
MATT: Well, you've already done two shots.

03:38:04.655 --> 03:38:12.097
TALIESIN: Oh, yeah. I'll fire shot with my next
shot. Does she currently have advantage or no?

03:38:12.097 --> 03:38:14.082
MATT: No, because it has not come back to her.

03:38:14.082 --> 03:38:16.098
TALIESIN: Okay, so I'm going to also put
sharpshooter on that.

03:38:16.098 --> 03:38:17.530
MATT: Okay.

03:38:17.530 --> 03:38:23.146
TALIESIN: Yay. (counting) 26 to hit?

03:38:23.146 --> 03:38:24.194
MATT: That hits.

03:38:24.194 --> 03:38:32.121
TALIESIN: So that's-- plus--

03:38:32.121 --> 03:38:35.069
SAM: Is that her right there? No that's
Cassandra.

03:38:35.069 --> 03:38:36.983
MATT: That's Cassandra. That's Briarwood, right
there.

03:38:36.983 --> 03:38:53.599
TALIESIN: Oh, and plus the Hex! So that's
(counting) 24 points of damage plus two points of

03:38:53.599 --> 03:38:54.709
fire damage.

03:38:54.709 --> 03:39:00.423
MATT: Whew, nice. The shot (bang) blasts into the
side of her face. You can see part of her jawbone

03:39:00.423 --> 03:39:06.826
is cracked as part of this, and her ear is blown
off to one side of her face, (choked groan) and

03:39:06.826 --> 03:39:08.993
she cradles it to her side as (grunts).

03:39:08.993 --> 03:39:10.519
LAURA: Like a ketchup packet!

03:39:10.519 --> 03:39:12.865
TALIESIN: Let's spend an action surge and keep
enjoying this!

03:39:12.865 --> 03:39:14.915
LIAM: Our cleric giggles from Vasselheim.

03:39:14.915 --> 03:39:18.689
TALIESIN: Why don't we take a--

03:39:18.689 --> 03:39:23.890
LIAM: If there's a time to blow your wad, it's
now.

03:39:23.890 --> 03:39:32.958
TALIESIN: Yeah, let's take a... violent shot on
top of that.

03:39:32.958 --> 03:39:34.247
LAURA: Violent shot?

03:39:34.247 --> 03:39:42.773
TALIESIN: I use the violent shot action with the
ice damage. Let's see what that does. Natural 20!

03:39:42.773 --> 03:39:45.281
This is going to be ugly as fuck.

03:39:45.281 --> 03:39:48.448
TRAVIS: (laughing) Of course it is!

03:39:48.448 --> 03:39:50.958
MARISHA: Of course.

03:39:50.958 --> 03:39:54.862
MATT: And this is all piercing damage, right?

03:39:54.862 --> 03:40:03.456
TALIESIN: Oh my god. This is so fucking bad, is
what this is about to be. Oh my god, this is going

03:40:03.456 --> 03:40:15.608
to be so-- let me get these additional dice. Okay,
so let's start doing this. Do all of the dice

03:40:15.608 --> 03:40:17.224
rolls get doubled?

03:40:17.224 --> 03:40:19.598
MATT: All of the dice for this roll.

03:40:19.598 --> 03:40:21.579
TALIESIN: All of the dice for this roll. Oh boy.

03:40:21.579 --> 03:40:23.430
MATT: Roll the dice and then double it.

03:40:23.430 --> 03:40:24.462
TALIESIN: Okay.

03:40:24.462 --> 03:40:33.232
MARISHA: High rolls. Big money, no whammies. It
could be worse.

03:40:33.232 --> 03:40:46.826
TALIESIN: (counts quietly) 42 points of damage
plus eight points of ice damage.

03:40:46.826 --> 03:40:56.914
MATT: Okay. This blast hits her in the side of the
shoulder, and the cloak catches fire for a moment

03:40:56.914 --> 03:41:00.971
before dispersing, and you can see the impact.
There's blood now seeping into her robe. She's

03:41:00.971 --> 03:41:06.242
looking rough, but you've noticed with each of
these shots, the impact you're used to doing with

03:41:06.242 --> 03:41:10.557
these shots is not doing the full impact you would
expect, especially with the force of these blows.

03:41:10.557 --> 03:41:16.674
Every shot you've taken on her in particular. That
ends your turn?

03:41:16.674 --> 03:41:25.112
TALIESIN: No, I've still got two more shots.
Actually, I get my grit point back from that

03:41:25.112 --> 03:41:28.846
because that was a natural 20, so that was a free
shot.

03:41:28.846 --> 03:41:32.243
MATT: When do you reload, by the way?

03:41:32.243 --> 03:41:37.150
TALIESIN: I have two more shots, and then I have
to reload. I'm keeping track. I'm being good.

03:41:37.150 --> 03:41:49.409
Let's hit her in the legs.

03:41:49.409 --> 03:41:51.496
MATT: Okay.

03:41:51.496 --> 03:41:59.410
TALIESIN: That's 20 to hit?

03:41:59.410 --> 03:42:04.549
MATT: 20 to hit. This is with your minus five? Are
you taking a sharpshooter shot on this?

03:42:04.549 --> 03:42:06.033
TALIESIN: Yeah. 20 to hit?

03:42:06.033 --> 03:42:08.054
MATT: You rolled a what?

03:42:08.054 --> 03:42:10.281
TALIESIN: No, 20 total to hit.

03:42:10.281 --> 03:42:11.868
MATT: Right. Okay.

03:42:11.868 --> 03:42:13.372
TALIESIN: I rolled a 13.

03:42:13.372 --> 03:42:15.376
MATT: Yeah. Okay, so that does hit, yes.

03:42:15.376 --> 03:42:24.707
TALIESIN: Because she has her disadvantage. She
needs to make a constitution saving throw.

03:42:24.707 --> 03:42:27.012
MATT: 22?

03:42:27.012 --> 03:42:31.970
TALIESIN: DC equals eight plus my proficiency mod
plus my dexterity mod.

03:42:31.970 --> 03:42:35.039
MATT: Plus ten, so 18.

03:42:35.039 --> 03:42:39.023
TALIESIN: She made it. She didn't fall, but she
still takes some damage, so let's see what she

03:42:39.023 --> 03:42:50.833
does. Ten, 12, 22, 28 points of damage.

03:42:50.833 --> 03:42:52.216
MATT: All righty.

03:42:52.216 --> 03:43:02.612
TALIESIN: And because this is really annoying me,
I'm going to give her a gut shot. Torso shot. Same

03:43:02.612 --> 03:43:04.512
thing, sharpshooter.

03:43:04.512 --> 03:43:07.417
LIAM: I'm seeing this all in slow motion.

03:43:07.417 --> 03:43:12.649
MARISHA: Throwing bullets.

03:43:12.649 --> 03:43:27.532
TALIESIN: 27 points of damage. And she has a
disadvantage on strength and dexterity checks for

03:43:27.532 --> 03:43:29.612
the rest of the round. For one full round.

03:43:29.612 --> 03:43:31.039
MATT: Good to know.

03:43:31.039 --> 03:43:34.622
TALIESIN: I'm going to back up a little bit, for
the rest of my--

03:43:34.622 --> 03:43:35.800
MATT: Over here?

03:43:35.800 --> 03:43:37.026
TALIESIN: Yeah, that way.

03:43:37.026 --> 03:43:38.971
LAURA: Get out of her view?

03:43:38.971 --> 03:43:42.387
MATT: Sure. That ends your turn, Percy?

03:43:42.387 --> 03:43:44.285
TALIESIN: (laughs) Yeah.

03:43:44.285 --> 03:43:51.191
MATT: Cassandra, seeing all this go down and
having this crisis moment, picks up her sword,

03:43:51.191 --> 03:44:02.405
rushes over, and uses her action to pull out one
of the potions that you gave her, the greater

03:44:02.405 --> 03:44:07.187
healing potion, and feed it to the ailing
Briarwood.

03:44:07.187 --> 03:44:08.494
TALIESIN: Damn it, girl!

03:44:08.494 --> 03:44:11.971
SAM: I gave her one. I gave her a greater.

03:44:11.971 --> 03:44:14.778
LAURA: A greater? We wasted a greater?!

03:44:14.778 --> 03:44:21.867
SAM: I'm a nice guy! I can't resist the charm of a
woman, especially one who looks identical to you.

03:44:21.867 --> 03:44:28.006
MATT: Her wounds close up a little bit. The ear
wound heals over a little bit, and she wipes her

03:44:28.006 --> 03:44:32.401
mouth. "Thank you, dear. Sylas! To the ritual!"

03:44:32.401 --> 03:44:35.177
LAURA: He's a mist.

03:44:35.177 --> 03:44:37.788
MATT: Keyleth, it's your turn.

03:44:37.788 --> 03:44:40.398
TALIESIN: Do it. Do it, girl!

03:44:40.398 --> 03:44:41.660
LIAM: Burn him.

03:44:41.660 --> 03:44:46.201
MARISHA: Okay, so I turn and I start shouting to
the mist and I say, what's the matter, Sylas?

03:44:46.201 --> 03:44:52.685
Afraid of a little gnome and a druid? And I blast
him with Sunbeam.

03:44:52.685 --> 03:44:53.777
TRAVIS: Good line.

03:44:53.777 --> 03:44:55.231
LAURA: (laughing) That was the lamest thing.

03:44:55.231 --> 03:45:00.701
MARISHA: Thanks! I'm not good with lines.
Keyleth isn't good with lines. Are you afraid of

03:45:00.701 --> 03:45:04.916
us? I heard Percy try to do lines, and I'm like,
that's what badasses do.

03:45:04.916 --> 03:45:12.410
MATT: I guess in this particular instance I want
to ask you:

03:45:12.410 --> 03:45:13.718
How do you want to do this?

03:45:13.718 --> 03:45:19.908
(cheering)

03:45:19.908 --> 03:45:21.432
LIAM: Sorry, cursed gun!

03:45:21.432 --> 03:45:29.047
MATT: There's still a semi-visible form of his
body, but in a mist form. It's trying to slowly

03:45:29.047 --> 03:45:31.536
escape off the top of this structure.

03:45:31.536 --> 03:45:33.234
MARISHA: Okay. Pike is standing right next to
him?

03:45:33.234 --> 03:45:34.225
MATT: Correct.

03:45:34.225 --> 03:45:42.659
MARISHA: I'm going to use Pike and use the light
that I have off Pike and combine it to do a joint

03:45:42.659 --> 03:45:49.466
Sunbeam, holy bomb.

03:45:49.466 --> 03:45:50.334
MATT: Okay.

03:45:50.334 --> 03:45:51.768
MARISHA: Boom.

03:45:51.768 --> 03:45:52.492
MATT: Great.

03:45:52.492 --> 03:45:58.500
LIAM: He's going to eat a bag of holy dicks is
what you're saying, right?

03:45:58.583 --> 03:46:02.657
MARISHA: Yeah, I want him to eat a bag of holy
dicks. Now explain that, please.

03:46:02.657 --> 03:46:04.937
Make it sound great.

03:46:04.937 --> 03:46:12.401
MATT: So. Looking over at Pike, already ready with
her mace up in the air and the mist recoiling from

03:46:12.401 --> 03:46:16.936
her. You glance at each other, have that
connective point, and as Pike brings up her

03:46:16.936 --> 03:46:22.538
shield, you bring back your Sunbeam and throw it
towards the shield, arcing it in his direction as

03:46:22.538 --> 03:46:26.844
she ricochets the reflection of the actual
sunlight back at him at the same time.

03:46:26.844 --> 03:46:28.452
LAURA: That was way cooler than what you said.

03:46:28.452 --> 03:46:30.655
MARISHA: Yeah, way cooler! I knew he'd bring it
through.

03:46:30.655 --> 03:46:35.782
MATT: As it sprays across, the beams themselves
seem to form nearly phallic rays.

03:46:35.782 --> 03:46:40.862
(laughter)

03:46:40.862 --> 03:46:44.906
MATT: Tearing through the mist, and with an
echoing scream, you hear Sylas's voice ring out,

03:46:44.906 --> 03:46:50.936
(screams) as the mist is immediately dissipated
and disintegrated and his form is no more.

03:46:50.936 --> 03:46:56.084
(cheering)

03:46:56.084 --> 03:46:58.324
MARISHA: High five, Pike!

03:46:58.324 --> 03:47:02.629
LAURA: How does it feel, Lady Briarwood?

03:47:02.629 --> 03:47:08.798
MATT: She, looking over her shoulder, still
looking at him as she's called to him to go join

03:47:08.798 --> 03:47:14.246
in the altar room, the ritual room, looks over and
sees his mist form. In slow motion, from her

03:47:14.246 --> 03:47:20.921
perspective, she sees Keyleth step forward, wind
blowing around her, releasing this beam and

03:47:20.921 --> 03:47:29.183
watching him be disintegrated. Immediately, her
eyes open wide and she screams out, "No! Sylas!"

03:47:29.183 --> 03:47:35.722
and you can see her whole body shaking now. The
horror of seeing her partner, the love of her

03:47:35.722 --> 03:47:43.086
life, disintegrated before her. Tears immediately
burst down her face, and her hands are shaking

03:47:43.086 --> 03:47:50.328
there as she screams out, "You can't! I broke the
world for us! No."

03:47:50.328 --> 03:47:52.594
That's the end of your turn?

03:47:52.594 --> 03:47:54.695
LIAM: May I ask a question?

03:47:54.695 --> 03:47:55.742
MATT: Yes.

03:47:55.742 --> 03:47:58.815
LIAM: Does Cassandra's charm come from Sylas or
Lady Briarwood?

03:47:58.815 --> 03:48:04.313
MATT: At this point, you have no idea.

03:48:04.313 --> 03:48:06.077
LAURA: What about yours?

03:48:06.077 --> 03:48:08.018
LIAM: From Lady Briarwood, yeah.

03:48:08.018 --> 03:48:09.174
SAM: The lady.

03:48:09.174 --> 03:48:10.286
LAURA: The lady.

03:48:10.286 --> 03:48:14.114
MATT: Yours is fine. All right, does that end your
turn, Keyleth?

03:48:14.114 --> 03:48:17.407
MARISHA: Yeah.

03:48:17.407 --> 03:48:25.490
MATT: All righty. So, with that, it brings us to
the top of the initiative round. It is now Lady

03:48:25.490 --> 03:48:36.310
Delilah Briarwood's turn. Looking around, heaving
with anger and frustration, she looks around her

03:48:36.310 --> 03:48:40.959
area and the tears streak down her face, blood
streaking down one side of her head. She looks at

03:48:40.959 --> 03:48:47.668
Cassandra, who right now is faltering. Seeing
everything closing around her, she goes, "It's too

03:48:47.668 --> 03:48:55.732
"soon, but it's our only chance." And with that,
she is going to step around here.

03:48:55.732 --> 03:48:58.871
LIAM: Somebody hit her. Hit her!

03:48:58.871 --> 03:49:01.850
MATT: She's still in combat with you, so you don't
get an attack of opportunity. Keyleth, you do, if

03:49:01.850 --> 03:49:03.743
you want to try and swing towards her.

03:49:03.743 --> 03:49:05.593
MARISHA: Can I use my sunlight that I have up?

03:49:05.593 --> 03:49:07.376
MATT: No, you have to make a combat strike.

03:49:07.376 --> 03:49:08.410
MARISHA: My staff?

03:49:08.410 --> 03:49:09.378
LAURA: Trip her!

03:49:09.378 --> 03:49:10.829
MARISHA: Can I go for a trip?

03:49:10.829 --> 03:49:14.979
MATT: No, this is just a melee attack.

03:49:14.979 --> 03:49:17.282
MARISHA: Fine, I'm going to bean her in the head.
Natural 20!

03:49:17.282 --> 03:49:22.052
MATT: Okay! Roll damage.

03:49:22.052 --> 03:49:24.213
LIAM: We've got the MVP over here.

03:49:24.213 --> 03:49:29.927
MARISHA: 12 damage! Bam!

03:49:29.927 --> 03:49:34.699
MATT: Crack! You hit her in the back of the head
as she stumbles forward and looks about the rest

03:49:34.699 --> 03:49:42.702
of you. She is using her last 5th-level spell to
attempt to cast another Dimension Door, out of the

03:49:42.702 --> 03:49:45.551
sight of the one who previously dispelled it.

03:49:45.551 --> 03:49:49.014
SAM: Can I Counterspell that?

03:49:49.014 --> 03:49:53.869
MATT: You have no visual on her. She is behind the
pillar. This time, she knew where you were and was

03:49:53.869 --> 03:49:57.502
not about to let that happen again. She disappears
behind the pillar, and you guys watch her step

03:49:57.502 --> 03:49:58.960
into the doorway and vanish from sight.

03:49:58.960 --> 03:49:59.755
LAURA: Seriously?

03:49:59.755 --> 03:50:01.029
MATT: She's still Hunter's Marked.

03:50:01.029 --> 03:50:02.108
LAURA: She's Hunter's Marked!

03:50:02.108 --> 03:50:03.822
MATT: You still have Hex on her, for as long as
that lasts.

03:50:03.822 --> 03:50:04.992
TALIESIN: That lasts a while.

03:50:04.992 --> 03:50:08.861
LAURA: Is he under the thing, still? Or did it
break?

03:50:08.861 --> 03:50:15.470
MATT: The flight lasts for an hour. The potion
lasts for an hour, and it's probably been about--

03:50:15.470 --> 03:50:17.017
LIAM: No, she's asking if I'm still--

03:50:17.017 --> 03:50:21.540
MATT: You currently? Yes. Make another
constitution saving throw.

03:50:21.540 --> 03:50:27.036
LIAM: Come on. Big roll. 13 plus nothing is 13.

03:50:27.036 --> 03:50:34.132
MATT: All right, so as you guys all look around
yourselves, Sylas disintegrated, Cassandra still

03:50:34.132 --> 03:50:38.588
holding the blades and looking around and is going
from a fight position, almost like a cornered

03:50:38.588 --> 03:50:44.685
creature, to looking at the sundering of her
brother and is looking completely frazzled and

03:50:44.685 --> 03:50:49.732
confused. She's on the verge of tears or a rage of
her own.

03:50:49.732 --> 03:50:54.382
You look over and see your brother down below and
is just standing there, his daggers dropped to the

03:50:54.382 --> 03:50:56.882
ground in front of him, and has been staring into
space this entire time.

03:50:56.882 --> 03:51:00.486
LAURA: I float down in front of him and slap him
across the face.

03:51:00.486 --> 03:51:04.218
MATT: Like that? Okay. Make another saving throw.

03:51:04.218 --> 03:51:07.407
LIAM: Nope.

03:51:07.407 --> 03:51:11.151
MATT: Okay. You slap, slap. He's taking it.

03:51:11.151 --> 03:51:13.366
ASHLEY: Can I go over to Vax?

03:51:13.366 --> 03:51:17.236
TRAVIS: Cassandra's still up, right?

03:51:17.236 --> 03:51:18.347
MATT: Cassandra is.

03:51:18.347 --> 03:51:22.269
ASHLEY: I'm going to Remove Curse on him.

03:51:22.269 --> 03:51:43.024
MATT: Okay. You cast Remove Curse. Let me see.
This is not considered a curse, so as the spell

03:51:43.024 --> 03:51:48.157
alleviates its energy into Vax, he still stands
there, staring into space.

03:51:48.157 --> 03:51:49.409
LAURA: Oh god.

03:51:49.409 --> 03:51:52.356
TRAVIS: Oh, wait, are we slapping Vax? Let me
try.

03:51:52.356 --> 03:51:55.363
LIAM: Yeah. You said something about a minute
before, though, didn't you?

03:51:55.363 --> 03:52:00.443
MATT: Yeah, so a little time goes by and then
eventually it wears off.

03:52:00.443 --> 03:52:02.922
TALIESIN: I'm going to start looking at that
door.

03:52:02.922 --> 03:52:04.760
TRAVIS: Is Cassandra still there?

03:52:04.760 --> 03:52:05.987
MATT: Yes, she is.

03:52:05.987 --> 03:52:08.540
TRAVIS: Can I grab her by the neck and walk her to
the edge of the pyramid?

03:52:08.633 --> 03:52:12.583
MATT: Yeah. You grab her, lift her. (choking
noise)

03:52:12.583 --> 03:52:13.813
TALIESIN: No, no! No.

03:52:13.813 --> 03:52:15.718
MATT: Drops her weapons as Grog takes her to the
edge.

03:52:15.718 --> 03:52:18.301
TALIESIN: No, let's not. Let's not.

03:52:18.301 --> 03:52:20.970
TRAVIS: Why not?

03:52:20.970 --> 03:52:31.103
LIAM: I walk up to Grog and her, and I face Percy
and repeat what Grog said. Why not?

03:52:31.103 --> 03:52:34.771
SAM: Is he still under her spell?

03:52:34.771 --> 03:52:43.117
TALIESIN: She's been here a very long time. Let's
just knock her unconscious and let her be.

03:52:43.117 --> 03:52:46.969
LIAM: I turn towards her, and I punch her across
the jaw as hard as I can.

03:52:46.969 --> 03:52:51.393
MATT: At this point, with the damage she's taken
and the mental shock she's in and the current

03:52:51.393 --> 03:52:55.065
circumstance, the one hit (whack) clocks her, and
she goes unconscious in his grip. Limp.

03:52:55.065 --> 03:52:57.178
LAURA: You can handcuff her behind her back.

03:52:57.178 --> 03:52:58.535
TRAVIS: We do have manacles.

03:52:58.535 --> 03:52:59.443
LAURA: Yeah.

03:52:59.443 --> 03:53:01.640
SAM: Put her in the Bag of Holding.

03:53:01.640 --> 03:53:03.509
OTHERS: No.

03:53:03.509 --> 03:53:04.854
TALIESIN: Thank you.

03:53:04.854 --> 03:53:09.032
LAURA: Maybe Greater Restoration her.

03:53:09.032 --> 03:53:11.884
ASHLEY: Yeah, can I Greater Restoration on her?

03:53:11.884 --> 03:53:15.034
MATT: Do you have another level of that spell?

03:53:15.034 --> 03:53:20.384
ASHLEY: No.

03:53:20.384 --> 03:53:23.154
MATT: Then you cannot. It's a 5th-level spell.

03:53:23.154 --> 03:53:25.535
TALIESIN: We can save it for later.

03:53:25.535 --> 03:53:26.975
ASHLEY: Keyleth?

03:53:26.975 --> 03:53:29.908
TRAVIS: I take some of the manacles, and I manacle
her hands behind her back.

03:53:29.908 --> 03:53:31.043
MATT: Okay.

03:53:31.043 --> 03:53:32.562
MARISHA: What's up, Pike?

03:53:32.562 --> 03:53:34.579
ASHLEY: Do you have Greater Restoration?

03:53:34.579 --> 03:53:37.705
MARISHA: Not on me. Not today.

03:53:37.705 --> 03:53:39.615
TALIESIN: I'm going to start working with that
door.

03:53:39.615 --> 03:53:45.508
TRAVIS: And to be super shitty, I grab a length of
rope and wrap it around her ankles and tie it back

03:53:45.508 --> 03:53:47.615
to her hands so she can't stand up.

03:53:47.615 --> 03:53:50.554
LAURA: Oh. Sorry, Cassandra. That's going to
suck.

03:53:50.554 --> 03:53:52.026
TRAVIS: She's got to stay there when she wakes
up.

03:53:52.026 --> 03:53:58.849
MATT: All right. Bigby's Hand does last a minute,
if you want to keep it maintained. The minute has

03:53:58.849 --> 03:54:00.683
passed at this time. It's probably going to pass.

03:54:00.683 --> 03:54:06.628
SAM: All right, before it passes, it gives me a
quick deep-tissue massage.

03:54:06.628 --> 03:54:07.907
MATT: Okay.

03:54:07.907 --> 03:54:11.179
TRAVIS: Can I pick up Sylas's onyx sword?

03:54:11.179 --> 03:54:12.811
MATT: You can, yeah.

03:54:12.811 --> 03:54:15.812
TALIESIN: What does a common healing potion do, by
the way?

03:54:15.812 --> 03:54:21.538
MATT: It'll require a short rest to attune and get
the nature of it, but it is a very beautiful new

03:54:21.538 --> 03:54:22.705
weapon.

03:54:22.705 --> 03:54:24.278
TRAVIS: Okay. I'll put it in the Bag of Holding.

03:54:24.278 --> 03:54:28.532
TALIESIN: You picked up his sword? Good. That's
why I had him drop it.

03:54:28.532 --> 03:54:29.899
TRAVIS: Yeah, I noticed.

03:54:29.899 --> 03:54:31.754
MARISHA: So he wouldn't disintegrate with it?

03:54:31.754 --> 03:54:35.683
TALIESIN: Yeah, and so one of us, possibly me,
could use it.

03:54:35.683 --> 03:54:37.719
SAM: Have a better sword than your piece of shit?

03:54:37.719 --> 03:54:39.770
TRAVIS: Do you want it?

03:54:39.770 --> 03:54:41.295
MARISHA: We have to find her. She's somewhere
close.

03:54:41.295 --> 03:54:43.171
TRAVIS: I'll give him the sword. He's got the onyx
sword.

03:54:43.171 --> 03:54:46.247
MATT: There is a brooch also left on the ground
from the ashes left behind.

03:54:46.247 --> 03:54:49.187
SAM: I'll pick it up and look at it.

03:54:49.187 --> 03:54:53.309
MATT: Okay. These items will take a little time to
look over.

03:54:53.309 --> 03:54:55.292
SAM: I'll look at it for a whole ten seconds.

03:54:55.292 --> 03:54:56.458
MATT: Okay.

03:54:56.458 --> 03:55:00.349
TALIESIN: Do I get my strength back, by the way?
I'm just down?

03:55:00.349 --> 03:55:01.375
MATT: Just down.

03:55:01.375 --> 03:55:06.118
LAURA: Can I see, from being on the roof, what's
inside the building? You said there's no roof to

03:55:06.118 --> 03:55:09.217
that temple I was up on top of.

03:55:09.217 --> 03:55:19.331
MATT: Correct. If you're looking inside of it
right now? You glance over. It's an open-roofed

03:55:19.331 --> 03:55:25.240
square construct. There are two hallways that lead
to the inside on both sides. The walls have a

03:55:25.240 --> 03:55:29.591
strange icy texture to them; it's hard to make out
the details from what little light is in there.

03:55:29.591 --> 03:55:34.253
There is a central platform that rises up in the
middle. There is a stairway on the opposite side

03:55:34.253 --> 03:55:39.672
of the room that leads up to that platform, and
there are a series of grooves in the ground that

03:55:39.672 --> 03:55:44.065
form some sort of shape that you can't make out
from this viewpoint. You do see Lady Briarwood

03:55:44.113 --> 03:55:46.004
atop that platform right now.

03:55:46.004 --> 03:55:47.417
SAM: How far?

03:55:47.417 --> 03:55:48.772
LAURA: She's inside the temple.

03:55:48.772 --> 03:55:53.670
TALIESIN: Let's go in. I took a minor healing
potion. Is that 2d8?

03:55:53.670 --> 03:55:57.251
MATT: A minor? A regular one is 2d4 plus two.

03:55:57.251 --> 03:56:06.499
SAM: Here, I'll trade you one. I trade him a
greater for a common. I take the common.

03:56:06.499 --> 03:56:08.258
TALIESIN: What's the greater do?

03:56:08.258 --> 03:56:10.237
SAM: Greater is 4d4 plus four.

03:56:10.237 --> 03:56:13.361
LAURA: Can I drop the rope down from the roof
where I'm at, so everybody can get up in?

03:56:13.361 --> 03:56:16.693
MATT: Get up and over? Yeah, you can do that.

03:56:16.693 --> 03:56:17.810
LAURA: Okay. I'm going to do that.

03:56:17.810 --> 03:56:22.125
MATT: Okay. It'll take you a while to do that. As
you drop the rope--

03:56:22.125 --> 03:56:25.275
LAURA: I don't know if you want to try the doors,
but I just thought we could get in.

03:56:25.275 --> 03:56:29.099
MATT: Okay, you lower the rope.

03:56:29.099 --> 03:56:37.691
LIAM: I'm going to walk up to my sister and take
her hand and squeeze it as hard as I can, and just

03:56:37.691 --> 03:56:39.595
walk forward with her.

03:56:39.595 --> 03:56:43.856
MATT: She's up on top of the roof. She lowers the
rope and starts taking you guys up one by one.

03:56:43.856 --> 03:56:49.038
Vex, you do notice out of the corner of your eye
as you lower the rope, there is a flash of

03:56:49.038 --> 03:56:54.563
greenish light from the center platform, and from
the distance, you can see Delilah is up on the

03:56:54.563 --> 03:56:56.684
platform reading from some sort of scroll.

03:56:56.684 --> 03:56:58.360
LIAM: How far away is she?

03:56:58.360 --> 03:57:03.896
MATT: She's about 80 feet from you.

03:57:03.896 --> 03:57:05.749
TALIESIN: I pull out Bad News.

03:57:05.749 --> 03:57:10.352
MATT: None of you guys can see her. Only she sees
her. You guys are still on the ground. She's on

03:57:10.352 --> 03:57:11.174
the roof.

03:57:11.174 --> 03:57:12.895
LAURA: I lowered the rope so you guys can start
climbing up.

03:57:12.895 --> 03:57:13.842
TALIESIN: I'm climbing up.

03:57:13.842 --> 03:57:15.883
LIAM: Can I see her, if I've gone up to her?

03:57:15.883 --> 03:57:19.530
MATT: You're the first one to climb up. She just
lowered the rope, so you're finding your way up

03:57:19.530 --> 03:57:20.633
now. You haven't even seen her yet.

03:57:20.633 --> 03:57:22.074
LIAM: All right.

03:57:22.074 --> 03:57:28.780
MATT: You notice all the ice on the walls shatters
and clinks to the ground. You can hear the sound

03:57:28.780 --> 03:57:33.572
of a million little shards of ice clinking onto
the ground and you can see the walls almost seem

03:57:33.572 --> 03:57:35.421
like they're moving or writhing slightly.

03:57:35.421 --> 03:57:36.776
LAURA: Ugh. Can I shoot at her?

03:57:36.776 --> 03:57:37.951
MATT: If you'd like to, yeah.

03:57:37.951 --> 03:57:38.895
LAURA: I want to.

03:57:38.895 --> 03:57:39.740
MATT: Okay.

03:57:39.740 --> 03:57:40.622
LAURA: Okay.

03:57:40.622 --> 03:57:41.855
TRAVIS: Percy, get up the fucking rope.

03:57:41.855 --> 03:57:43.378
TALIESIN: I'm heading straight up there.

03:57:43.378 --> 03:57:45.603
MATT: What's your range increment for your
longbow?

03:57:45.657 --> 03:57:47.334
LAURA: I don't see it.

03:57:47.334 --> 03:57:50.240
MATT: I'll look it up under the equipment section
in the book.

03:57:50.240 --> 03:57:51.768
LAURA: It doesn't say on the--

03:57:51.768 --> 03:57:55.806
LIAM: I'm going to start throwing as soon as I'm
near my sister.

03:57:55.806 --> 03:57:58.080
SAM: Oh, Vax. Hi.

03:57:58.080 --> 03:57:59.063
LIAM: Hi.

03:57:59.063 --> 03:58:00.437
LAURA: You can't throw 80 feet.

03:58:00.437 --> 03:58:01.656
LIAM: No, but I could get closer.

03:58:01.656 --> 03:58:04.066
LAURA: No, you can't. We're on the roof around
it.

03:58:04.066 --> 03:58:08.243
TRAVIS: A real man could throw 80 feet.

03:58:08.243 --> 03:58:11.387
LIAM: That's true, Grog. That's true. That's a
good point.

03:58:11.387 --> 03:58:12.912
LAURA: I feel like it's 120 feet.

03:58:12.912 --> 03:58:18.940
MATT: It's 150 feet, so yeah. There's no serious
issue there. You can go ahead. You have

03:58:18.940 --> 03:58:20.079
disadvantage on the strike.

03:58:20.079 --> 03:58:20.967
LAURA: Oh, I do?

03:58:20.967 --> 03:58:23.920
MATT: Because her image is still shimmering.

03:58:23.920 --> 03:58:25.866
LAURA: That's great, then 13.

03:58:25.931 --> 03:58:27.823
MATT: 13. Arrow (whoosh) disappears into the
darkness.

03:58:27.823 --> 03:58:29.035
LAURA: Can I hit her again?

03:58:29.035 --> 03:58:30.119
MATT: Go for it.

03:58:30.119 --> 03:58:34.727
LIAM: What is the relationship to her, if I've
just gotten next to her?

03:58:34.727 --> 03:58:36.978
SAM: She was married to Sylas.

03:58:36.978 --> 03:58:39.763
LIAM: No, shut up, you. Where are we, and where is
she?

03:58:39.763 --> 03:58:43.828
MATT: Okay, so if you want to come up to the top
and start looking.

03:58:43.828 --> 03:58:48.351
SAM: Oh god! That looks like a big hand.

03:58:48.351 --> 03:58:49.974
LAURA: It's a Bigby Hand!

03:58:49.974 --> 03:58:53.951
SAM: You know what they say about guys with Bigby
Hands?

03:58:53.951 --> 03:58:56.959
MARISHA: Bigby Gloves?

03:58:56.959 --> 03:58:59.282
LAURA: 20 was the second arrow that I shot at
her.

03:58:59.282 --> 03:59:02.286
MATT: 20? 20 would hit.

03:59:02.286 --> 03:59:09.635
TRAVIS: Percy, are you up there yet?

03:59:09.635 --> 03:59:14.210
LIAM: Are we on the edge of a ledge or a wall?

03:59:14.210 --> 03:59:19.251
MATT: There's a ledge that goes around the entire
wall that encases this, but there's no roof. It's

03:59:19.251 --> 03:59:25.400
just an open square area. So you would get up to
there.

03:59:25.400 --> 03:59:27.038
MARISHA: Can I go up next?

03:59:27.038 --> 03:59:30.059
LAURA: Can I maybe go through the piece of paper
that she's reading?

03:59:30.059 --> 03:59:35.649
MATT: That would've been something to call before
you shot her. Next attack you can, if you want.

03:59:35.649 --> 03:59:38.086
LIAM: So you said Jennifer Lopez is 80 feet from
us?

03:59:38.086 --> 03:59:41.420
MATT: Roughly, yeah.

03:59:41.420 --> 03:59:43.449
TALIESIN: I head up, as well.

03:59:43.449 --> 03:59:46.804
LAURA: 19 damage to her is what I rolled.

03:59:46.804 --> 03:59:54.791
MATT: 19 damage? Okay. Strikes her. The arrow hits
and gleans off her. The damage, much like Percy's,

03:59:54.791 --> 03:59:59.109
is not quite having the full damage you want it
to.

03:59:59.109 --> 04:00:04.910
However, as that hits, she reaches into her
pocket and pulls something out. Percy, you get to

04:00:04.962 --> 04:00:07.987
the top there. Who's up next?

04:00:07.987 --> 04:00:09.237
MARISHA: I'll go.

04:00:09.237 --> 04:00:10.383
ASHLEY: I'll go.

04:00:10.383 --> 04:00:12.719
SAM: I'm always behind Pike.

04:00:12.719 --> 04:00:17.744
MATT: All right, the rest of you gather at the
bottom here. Trinket's going to have a hard time

04:00:17.744 --> 04:00:18.721
getting up there.

04:00:18.721 --> 04:00:20.555
TALIESIN: I'm going to take 80 feet--

04:00:20.555 --> 04:00:24.279
MATT: Well, before that happens, as a reaction to
that, she pulls something out of her hand. There's

04:00:24.347 --> 04:00:29.187
a streak of red light that arcs upward, and
there's a slight shrieking sound as a familiar

04:00:29.187 --> 04:00:36.008
arcane blast hits, a Fireball bursts on the
roof area around all of you. (explosion noise) I

04:00:36.078 --> 04:00:38.742
need a dexterity saving throw from all three of
you guys up there.

04:00:38.742 --> 04:00:43.484
MARISHA: Who's up there right now?

04:00:43.536 --> 04:00:45.299
LAURA: Do we get advantage on it at all?

04:00:45.299 --> 04:00:46.585
MATT: Nope.

04:00:46.585 --> 04:00:51.245
LIAM: 15. Can I use Uncanny Dodge at this moment?

04:00:51.245 --> 04:00:55.867
MATT: You mean to lower that damage by half?

04:00:55.867 --> 04:00:56.595
LIAM: Yeah.

04:00:56.595 --> 04:00:57.645
MATT: You can, yeah.

04:00:57.645 --> 04:00:59.294
LIAM: What, is she casting a spell?

04:00:59.294 --> 04:01:00.188
MATT: Yeah.

04:01:00.188 --> 04:01:03.558
LIAM: I can also use Evasion.

04:01:03.640 --> 04:01:04.761
MATT: You failed the save.

04:01:04.761 --> 04:01:12.747
LIAM: Right, but depending on what it is. Those
both do different things. Okay, they do the same

04:01:12.747 --> 04:01:13.821
thing. Sorry.

04:01:13.821 --> 04:01:16.654
MATT: It's okay. All right, so saving throws for
Percy?

04:01:16.654 --> 04:01:17.735
TALIESIN: 25.

04:01:17.735 --> 04:01:19.775
MATT: 25 for your dex?

04:01:19.775 --> 04:01:20.817
TALIESIN: I rolled a 19.

04:01:20.817 --> 04:01:21.774
MATT: That's great.

04:01:21.774 --> 04:01:22.615
LAURA: 16.

04:01:22.615 --> 04:01:23.475
MATT: 16.

04:01:23.475 --> 04:01:26.579
LIAM: It was a 15, so half damage.

04:01:26.579 --> 04:01:37.356
MATT: All right, so you take half damage. That is
36 points of fire damage to you. That would be 18

04:01:37.356 --> 04:01:44.942
to both of you guys. 18 points of fire damage.

04:01:44.942 --> 04:01:48.146
LAURA: Another 18 points of fire damage?

04:01:48.146 --> 04:01:50.599
MATT: No, just to them. You took full damage.

04:01:50.599 --> 04:01:51.558
LAURA: Oh, okay.

04:01:51.558 --> 04:01:53.701
MATT: Okay, next person at the rope?

04:01:53.701 --> 04:01:54.820
MARISHA: Me.

04:01:54.820 --> 04:01:56.521
MATT: All right. Keyleth, you make your way up to
the top.

04:01:56.521 --> 04:01:57.902
TALIESIN: Can I fire now?

04:01:57.902 --> 04:01:59.274
MATT: Yeah.

04:01:59.274 --> 04:02:07.881
TALIESIN: It's 80 feet? It's within the Pepperbox
range. I'm going to shoot

04:02:07.881 --> 04:02:10.460
for the scroll with fire.

04:02:10.460 --> 04:02:12.173
MATT: Okay.

04:02:12.173 --> 04:02:18.005
MARISHA: Yeah, good call.

04:02:18.005 --> 04:02:22.906
TALIESIN: That rolled really low. I can use that
bonus die. I rolled within my--

04:02:22.906 --> 04:02:25.933
MATT: Misfire?

04:02:25.933 --> 04:02:27.563
TALIESIN: Can I use the--

04:02:27.563 --> 04:02:29.704
MATT: The natural roll is still what counts for
misfire, unfortunately.

04:02:29.704 --> 04:02:32.526
LAURA: Oh no.

04:02:32.526 --> 04:02:35.762
TALIESIN: I'm going to try and fix it.

04:02:35.762 --> 04:02:36.848
MATT: Okay.

04:02:36.848 --> 04:02:41.347
TALIESIN: No.

04:02:41.347 --> 04:02:43.522
MATT: Pepperbox is broken.

04:02:43.522 --> 04:02:49.248
LAURA: Have I recovered at all to shoot again?
Have I recovered enough to shoot at her again?

04:02:49.248 --> 04:02:50.568
MATT: You will in a second.

04:02:50.568 --> 04:02:53.490
TALIESIN: Pepperbox is completely broken.

04:02:53.490 --> 04:02:55.213
MATT: Yeah, unusable.

04:02:55.213 --> 04:02:57.053
SAM: Oh no, if only we had another gun.

04:02:57.053 --> 04:02:57.954
LAURA: I know.

04:02:57.954 --> 04:02:59.382
SAM: Oh, wait. We do.

04:02:59.382 --> 04:03:00.385
LAURA: Bad News.

04:03:00.385 --> 04:03:01.681
SAM: No, we have another gun.

04:03:01.681 --> 04:03:02.557
TALIESIN: We have two more guns.

04:03:02.557 --> 04:03:04.430
MARISHA: We have Ripley's gun.

04:03:04.430 --> 04:03:05.456
SAM: Give it to me.

04:03:05.456 --> 04:03:06.472
LAURA: Are you up on top?

04:03:06.472 --> 04:03:07.289
SAM: No.

04:03:07.289 --> 04:03:08.480
LAURA: I can't give it to you.

04:03:08.480 --> 04:03:10.969
TALIESIN: Do I still have-- are we still--

04:03:10.969 --> 04:03:12.682
MATT: You have one more attack.

04:03:12.682 --> 04:03:14.218
TALIESIN: Bad News.

04:03:14.218 --> 04:03:19.245
MATT: You'll get Bad News out. That's it. All
right, with that--

04:03:19.245 --> 04:03:20.513
LIAM: Matthew.

04:03:20.513 --> 04:03:21.606
MATT: Yes?

04:03:21.606 --> 04:03:23.496
LIAM: You're very good at this.

04:03:23.496 --> 04:03:24.903
MATT: What do you want to do?

04:03:24.903 --> 04:03:26.847
LIAM: That's it. I just want to say you're very
good at this.

04:03:26.847 --> 04:03:33.066
MATT: (giggles, sighs) We're running a little
late. Trying to get through this climactic moment,

04:03:33.155 --> 04:03:34.299
guys. Apologies.

04:03:34.299 --> 04:03:35.683
MARISHA: Are we running late?

04:03:35.683 --> 04:03:36.764
TALIESIN: Don't look.

04:03:36.764 --> 04:03:37.703
MARISHA: It's fine.

04:03:37.703 --> 04:03:39.046
MATT: Sorry, guys.

04:03:39.046 --> 04:03:41.641
MARISHA: Crew hates us.

04:03:41.641 --> 04:03:48.058
MATT: I know. It's okay. I'll make it up to them.
At this point, the scroll (fluttering noise)

04:03:48.058 --> 04:04:01.402
vanishes. She, as a bonus action at the top of
this turn, gashes across her wrist and spreads her

04:04:01.402 --> 04:04:06.180
own life's blood across what looks to be this dark
orb, about a foot in diameter, that's resting in

04:04:06.180 --> 04:04:08.185
the center of this upper platform.

04:04:08.185 --> 04:04:09.957
LAURA: Can I take a potion really fast?

04:04:09.957 --> 04:04:12.691
MATT: At the top of your turn, you can, as a bonus
action.

04:04:12.691 --> 04:04:15.447
MARISHA: The orb is floating?

04:04:15.447 --> 04:04:18.936
MATT: The dark orb in the center of the platform
that she's currently on in the center of this

04:04:18.936 --> 04:04:23.760
room. It's half-embedded in the ground, and she
scatters her blood across it. You can see her

04:04:23.760 --> 04:04:26.682
shaking with fear and trepidation during this
whole circumstance.

04:04:26.682 --> 04:04:30.980
MARISHA: She splatters her blood on the dark
sphere?

04:04:30.980 --> 04:04:34.326
MATT: Make a perception check, those who are up
top, by the way. Who's up next?

04:04:34.326 --> 04:04:37.293
TALIESIN: Jesus Christ. 16.

04:04:37.293 --> 04:04:39.816
MARISHA: One.

04:04:39.816 --> 04:04:40.793
LAURA: What are we trying to do?

04:04:40.793 --> 04:04:42.640
MATT: Perception. Scanlan gets up.

04:04:42.640 --> 04:04:45.088
SAM: Hey. Hi, guys! What's going-- oh.

04:04:45.088 --> 04:04:46.440
LIAM: 20.

04:04:46.440 --> 04:04:48.043
SAM: She's bleeding all over that thing?

04:04:48.043 --> 04:04:55.151
MATT: Those who got 15 or higher, you notice the
writhing on the walls. The walls are encased in

04:04:55.151 --> 04:05:03.247
what looks like a tapestry of bodies. Hundreds of
humanoid individuals that are woven into each

04:05:03.247 --> 04:05:09.575
other, each missing their left hand and/or left
eye from their body, and they're all just

04:05:09.575 --> 04:05:15.566
squirming and writhing. Many of them are in
various states of decay, and they're just moving

04:05:15.566 --> 04:05:21.395
after that ice that was encasing them had
shattered. There's a low, weird moaning drone

04:05:21.395 --> 04:05:27.139
that's beginning to fill the room. The black orb
itself is starting to rise out of the center of

04:05:27.225 --> 04:05:28.957
the pedestal, as well.

04:05:28.957 --> 04:05:36.269
Now, Vex, since you had the top of this, and Vax.
What do you want to do?

04:05:36.269 --> 04:05:40.847
LIAM: Wait, there's an orb coming up from where?

04:05:40.847 --> 04:05:42.455
TRAVIS: The center of the pedestal.

04:05:42.455 --> 04:05:43.922
MATT: The center of the platform she's on.

04:05:43.922 --> 04:05:45.587
SAM: She's got blood on it. She's doing a magic
ritual.

04:05:45.587 --> 04:05:47.859
LIAM: And we're how high in the air from the floor
that she's on?

04:05:47.859 --> 04:05:51.762
MATT: I'd say you're about 30 feet up. She's about
40 feet up. She's actually risen a little above

04:05:51.762 --> 04:05:52.686
you guys.

04:05:52.686 --> 04:05:56.415
LAURA: I'm going to guzzle a potion, and then I'm
going to shoot Percy's special arrow, question

04:05:56.415 --> 04:05:58.072
mark? At the orb.

04:05:58.072 --> 04:06:04.079
SAM: At the orb? You're not going to stop this
with an arrow. It's happened already. It's done.

04:06:04.079 --> 04:06:08.410
LIAM: If I go to the very edge, how far am I from
her?

04:06:08.410 --> 04:06:13.726
LAURA: Then what am I supposed to do? Killing her,
what good will it do?

04:06:13.726 --> 04:06:15.103
MATT: 55 feet away.

04:06:15.103 --> 04:06:17.039
LAURA: Maybe she's a sacrifice, at this point.

04:06:17.039 --> 04:06:18.666
LIAM: That's within range, right?

04:06:18.666 --> 04:06:19.913
MATT: Of your daggers?

04:06:19.913 --> 04:06:22.251
LIAM: Yeah. I'm throwing, then, at her.

04:06:22.251 --> 04:06:23.876
MATT: What's the throwing dagger range?

04:06:23.876 --> 04:06:28.317
LIAM: 60 feet, because I'm sharpshooter, so I take
no disadvantage.

04:06:28.317 --> 04:06:31.092
MATT: Then...

04:06:31.092 --> 04:06:34.460
LIAM: Yeah, I don't like her.

04:06:34.460 --> 04:06:36.419
MATT: 20/60, so yeah, you can still hit her.

04:06:36.419 --> 04:06:40.405
LIAM: Yeah, so I'm going to throw two daggers at
her. I don't know if there's any poison left-- I'm

04:06:40.405 --> 04:06:48.837
sure there's not-- on the Life-Stealing, and the
Keen. First one is not good at all. That's a 14,

04:06:48.837 --> 04:07:02.663
and the second one hits. That's a 28. That is the
Life-Stealing. That is seven points of damage.

04:07:02.743 --> 04:07:07.510
MATT: Okay. All right. Vex?

04:07:07.510 --> 04:07:09.608
LAURA: I had said I was going to shoot the orb.

04:07:09.608 --> 04:07:11.280
MATT: Go for it.

04:07:11.280 --> 04:07:14.135
LAURA: All right. I'm going to shoot the special
arrow, question mark.

04:07:14.135 --> 04:07:17.792
TRAVIS: Plus, you're left-handed, and she
apparently has things against lefties.

04:07:17.792 --> 04:07:19.117
LAURA: Yeah, exactly.

04:07:19.117 --> 04:07:20.902
LIAM: You flicked me in the left nut. Are you
complicit?

04:07:20.902 --> 04:07:22.903
TRAVIS: You don't know.

04:07:22.903 --> 04:07:25.956
LAURA: 23?

04:07:26.020 --> 04:07:30.331
MATT: 23? Okay. That does hit the orb. Roll
damage.

04:07:30.331 --> 04:07:35.353
LAURA: I don't know what I'm doing!

04:07:35.353 --> 04:07:37.547
LIAM: Let's see what happens.

04:07:37.547 --> 04:07:38.816
LAURA: 15?

04:07:38.816 --> 04:07:43.104
MATT: Okay, the arrow streaks off and seemingly
hits the orb. Splinters across the surface.

04:07:43.104 --> 04:07:46.468
TALIESIN: It was the arrow, question mark.

04:07:46.468 --> 04:07:59.158
MATT: Oh, it was the explosive one? Oh, okay. The
arrow arcs off. Did you roll with disadvantage on

04:07:59.241 --> 04:08:01.388
that one because it is the explosive arrow?

04:08:01.388 --> 04:08:07.875
LAURA: Oh shit. No. 15.

04:08:07.875 --> 04:08:14.250
MATT: 15. The arrow whizzes past and slams into
the bottom of the pillar. You see a muffled

04:08:14.250 --> 04:08:20.205
explosion and light flash, and it rocks the center
a bit, but she still maintains concentration. She

04:08:20.205 --> 04:08:22.137
looks over at where it came from.

04:08:22.137 --> 04:08:25.490
LAURA: Should I have shot her? I'm sorry. I should
have shot her!

04:08:25.490 --> 04:08:28.137
SAM: It's fine. It wouldn't have done anything.

04:08:28.137 --> 04:08:33.127
MARISHA: Can I try something? Am I able to try
something? Is she still bleeding

04:08:33.127 --> 04:08:34.420
all over this orb?

04:08:34.420 --> 04:08:39.344
MATT: The bleeding has finished. The orb is rising
up and pulsing.

04:08:39.344 --> 04:08:40.486
LIAM: Question.

04:08:40.486 --> 04:08:41.428
MATT: Yes.

04:08:41.428 --> 04:08:42.465
LIAM: Did we surprise her?

04:08:42.465 --> 04:08:44.668
MATT: No, she is well aware of you guys.

04:08:44.668 --> 04:08:49.455
LIAM: She's well aware that we're here. Did I go
before her? Is there initiative here? Did I go

04:08:49.455 --> 04:08:50.497
before her turn?

04:08:50.497 --> 04:08:53.050
MATT: Right now, as people arrive, I'm
counting this. I'll probably do initiative after

04:08:53.050 --> 04:08:55.082
we finish this set.

04:08:55.153 --> 04:08:56.394
LAURA: Can I still fly?

04:08:56.394 --> 04:08:59.006
MATT: You can still fly if you want, yeah.

04:08:59.006 --> 04:09:00.380
SAM: How far?

04:09:00.380 --> 04:09:01.489
MATT: 55 feet.

04:09:01.489 --> 04:09:04.818
SAM: Am I going soon?

04:09:04.818 --> 04:09:06.151
MATT: We're getting to that now.

04:09:06.151 --> 04:09:09.210
LIAM: I think this is going to be shot down, and
I'm fine if it is, but I know that with

04:09:09.210 --> 04:09:13.416
Assassinate, if I go before the enemy does, it's
an automatic critical.

04:09:13.416 --> 04:09:21.523
MATT: This is one of those circumstances where you
guys have been already in combat. This isn't a

04:09:21.530 --> 04:09:25.644
scenario where you got the jump on them. She's
aware that you guys are there and she's just

04:09:25.644 --> 04:09:27.581
trying to finish this while ignoring that
circumstance.

04:09:27.581 --> 04:09:32.075
LAURA: I'm going to pull out a fancy robe from my
bag and I'm going to try to fly towards the orb.

04:09:32.075 --> 04:09:33.306
MATT: Okay.

04:09:33.306 --> 04:09:34.684
MARISHA: While she does that--

04:09:34.684 --> 04:09:38.066
TALIESIN: Keyleth's got shit.

04:09:38.066 --> 04:09:40.362
MARISHA: It's not going to work, but I can try.

04:09:40.362 --> 04:09:42.614
MATT: All right, you three.

04:09:42.614 --> 04:09:52.419
MARISHA: Okay, so you could argue that our bodies
are made of 70 percent water, right, so if I cast

04:09:52.419 --> 04:09:56.584
Control Water, can I move her blood?

04:09:56.584 --> 04:10:06.925
MATT: You can certainly try. Her blood has already
cast across the orb and it seems to have initiated

04:10:06.925 --> 04:10:12.421
whatever is part of it. There's not still blood
pouring onto it; she scattered across it once.

04:10:12.421 --> 04:10:16.322
MARISHA: So wiping the blood off probably wouldn't
work?

04:10:16.322 --> 04:10:17.453
MATT: You can try.

04:10:17.453 --> 04:10:18.836
TRAVIS: Let's say no.

04:10:18.836 --> 04:10:22.176
LIAM: If she rolls really high. Really high.

04:10:22.176 --> 04:10:24.952
TALIESIN: How good do you feel about a natural
20?

04:10:24.952 --> 04:10:30.198
MARISHA: "How good do you feel about a natural
20?" Well, judging by the shit that's been going

04:10:30.198 --> 04:10:36.338
down today-- fuck it! I already said it. I'm going
to do it. I'm going to do Control Water and I'm

04:10:36.338 --> 04:10:40.574
going to see if I can suck all the blood off of
the orb.

04:10:40.574 --> 04:10:45.379
MATT: Okay. Roll a d20, add your wisdom modifier.

04:10:45.379 --> 04:10:48.422
MARISHA: Okay. Oh, did you see that?

04:10:48.422 --> 04:10:51.547
TALIESIN: I did. That was cruel.

04:10:51.547 --> 04:10:53.153
MARISHA: It was on a 20.

04:10:53.153 --> 04:10:54.306
TALIESIN: And then it bounced.

04:10:54.306 --> 04:10:56.596
MARISHA: 15.

04:10:56.596 --> 04:11:03.600
MATT: Okay. Focusing from this distance, you try
to-- The blood shifts across the surface, but there

04:11:03.600 --> 04:11:09.333
is some sort of power that's holding it to the
orb. It is unmoved. I know. Scanlan?

04:11:09.333 --> 04:11:11.457
SAM: I've got one shot at this, right?

04:11:11.457 --> 04:11:12.623
LIAM: Yes.

04:11:12.623 --> 04:11:18.258
SAM: I'm going to try to cast-- I can't cast
anything anymore. I'm going to try to cast

04:11:18.258 --> 04:11:28.207
Suggestion on her, and I will say, 
Stop, collaborate and listen. Because I'm a gnome

04:11:28.421 --> 04:11:35.426
who's on a mission. Follow me as I kill your
husband the lich, and I'll make you my bitch.

04:11:35.426 --> 04:11:37.625
TRAVIS: Her husband was a vampire.

04:11:37.625 --> 04:11:39.025
SAM: Oh, yeah. Whatever.

04:11:39.025 --> 04:11:40.224
MATT: It didn't rhyme. It's fine.

04:11:40.224 --> 04:11:44.616
LIAM: Come on. Hail Mary pass, here we go.

04:11:44.616 --> 04:11:48.183
MATT: Okay.

04:11:48.183 --> 04:11:56.905
SAM: Suggestion is a-- oh, she probably can't be
charmed. It's a wisdom saving throw.

04:11:56.905 --> 04:12:00.184
MATT: Okay, she rolled a 19. What's your DC on
that?

04:12:00.184 --> 04:12:01.435
SAM: 19.

04:12:01.435 --> 04:12:03.078
MATT: 19. Yeah, with the cone.

04:12:03.078 --> 04:12:04.666
(groaning)

04:12:04.666 --> 04:12:06.264
LIAM: Good attempt, though, Sam.

04:12:06.264 --> 04:12:09.191
SAM: Never mind! Carry on!

04:12:09.191 --> 04:12:10.199
MATT: Percy?

04:12:10.199 --> 04:12:19.602
TALIESIN: I'm going to take a shot with Bad News
because this is getting really ridiculous. I'm

04:12:19.602 --> 04:12:28.632
going to try and get her attention and get her to
pay attention. Let's have a normal roll. Oh, for

04:12:28.632 --> 04:12:30.561
the love of God!

04:12:30.561 --> 04:12:31.709
MARISHA: No.

04:12:31.709 --> 04:12:33.099
LIAM: One? 20?

04:12:33.099 --> 04:12:34.511
TALIESIN: So, Bad News--

04:12:34.511 --> 04:12:37.299
LAURA: Misfire?

04:12:37.299 --> 04:12:39.107
MATT: All right, try and repair it.

04:12:39.107 --> 04:12:41.854
TALIESIN: Just barely!

04:12:41.854 --> 04:12:42.979
MATT: Okay.

04:12:42.979 --> 04:12:53.526
TALIESIN: And I can try and get one more bullet to
come out of it at this point, so I'm going to make

04:12:53.526 --> 04:13:02.010
one last attempt to make it shoot, after clearing
the chamber. Better! Jesus H. Christ. 24.

04:13:02.010 --> 04:13:03.210
MATT: That'll hit.

04:13:03.210 --> 04:13:06.429
LIAM: Come on. Coup de grace.

04:13:06.429 --> 04:13:09.069
MARISHA: Coup de grace.

04:13:09.069 --> 04:13:13.841
TALIESIN: This is at least going to get her
attention.

04:13:13.841 --> 04:13:24.747
MARISHA: At least distract her. Come on, Percy.
That was a 12 on a d12, which is dope.

04:13:24.747 --> 04:13:28.737
TALIESIN: Yeah, that's 21. 27 points of damage.

04:13:28.737 --> 04:13:34.512
MATT: Okay. So the (gunshot noise) blast from Bad
News scatters through the air and slams into her

04:13:34.512 --> 04:13:37.962
side, and she's nearly thrown off the top of the
platform from the blast of it. You can see blood

04:13:37.962 --> 04:13:42.516
streaking down her other arm now, and she has
blood down the side of her face, down one arm and

04:13:42.516 --> 04:13:47.743
the other, and she's shaking in place on the
platform. She sees you lifting towards, holding

04:13:47.743 --> 04:13:52.300
the robe to the side, and she's looking at the
orb, and doesn't even seem to really know what's

04:13:52.362 --> 04:13:56.232
going to happen. There's this anticipation and
fear in her eyes. Everything's been torn from her,

04:13:56.232 --> 04:13:58.852
at this point. She's a caged animal with nothing
to lose.

04:13:58.852 --> 04:14:07.939
That finishes your turn. Taking her turn, she sees
you rushing towards her. She extends her finger--

04:14:07.939 --> 04:14:11.014
LAURA: Oh, wait! I took a potion. I took a potion!
I said it on the last turn, and I didn't use it.

