MATT: That's your full turn. You want to do Divine
Intervention?

04:28:15.374 --> 04:28:16.819
ASHLEY: Yeah.

04:28:16.819 --> 04:28:18.223
MATT: Okay. Go ahead and roll.

04:28:18.223 --> 04:28:20.192
SAM: What is that?

04:28:20.192 --> 04:28:36.283
MATT: Roll a d10 and then another d10, and let me
know the numbers in succession.

04:28:36.283 --> 04:28:37.670
ASHLEY: 12.

04:28:37.670 --> 04:28:39.788
MATT: You are what level?

04:28:39.788 --> 04:28:41.078
ASHLEY: 11.

04:28:41.078 --> 04:28:43.524
MATT: Unfortunately, that just fails.

04:28:43.524 --> 04:28:51.802
LIAM: I scream at the top of my lungs, pull her
out of here! I'm still climbing dead bodies.

04:28:51.802 --> 04:28:59.508
TALIESIN: I've got hold of the rope and just
trying to yell, toss her off! Because that way

04:28:59.508 --> 04:29:01.493
we can see if we can counterweight her back down.

04:29:01.493 --> 04:29:05.388
TRAVIS: I'm at the top, so we can gently get her
down. I could jump down with you.

04:29:05.388 --> 04:29:06.414
LAURA: Okay.

04:29:06.414 --> 04:29:08.843
TRAVIS: I'll jump and hold her.

04:29:08.843 --> 04:29:10.928
TALIESIN: I'll ride the rope up.

04:29:10.928 --> 04:29:14.028
MATT: Okay. You're on the same side as them
jumping down now.

04:29:14.028 --> 04:29:16.252
TALIESIN: Oh, that's right. Never mind.

04:29:16.252 --> 04:29:17.790
MATT: They would come down to meet you.

04:29:17.790 --> 04:29:19.123
LIAM: Have I reached the top?

04:29:19.123 --> 04:29:21.941
MATT: We'll say now you've managed to climb up
towards the top.

04:29:21.941 --> 04:29:27.204
LIAM: I want to pick up Pike under my arm like a
fucking football and run forward after my sister.

04:29:27.204 --> 04:29:29.124
MATT: You grab her and bolt off the side.

04:29:29.124 --> 04:29:35.032
TRAVIS: Once we hit the ground-- we're outside of
the room, right? Should we try to heal her? I've

04:29:35.032 --> 04:29:36.136
got a common.

04:29:36.136 --> 04:29:40.378
MATT: There's going to be 14 points of fall damage
to you as you land because right now you're not

04:29:40.378 --> 04:29:44.139
carefully landing. This is just clutching her and
jumping off. You, make an acrobatics check.

04:29:44.139 --> 04:29:48.494
LIAM: That's a 20.

04:29:48.494 --> 04:29:54.608
MATT: 20? Okay. You manage to take only two damage
from the fall. Make another death saving throw.

04:29:54.608 --> 04:29:58.170
TALIESIN: I believe in you!

04:29:58.170 --> 04:30:00.309
LAURA: Save. I've only failed one.

04:30:00.309 --> 04:30:05.198
LIAM: I'm planting Pike's glowing form right down
on my sister's chest.

04:30:05.198 --> 04:30:07.954
TRAVIS: Can I put a common? I have a common.

04:30:07.954 --> 04:30:13.713
LIAM: You did succeed three times.

04:30:13.713 --> 04:30:15.340
TALIESIN: She succeeded three times.

04:30:15.340 --> 04:30:17.966
MATT: Three times. No, you succeeded--

04:30:17.966 --> 04:30:18.945
SAM: Twice.

04:30:18.945 --> 04:30:19.920
LAURA: Three times.

04:30:19.920 --> 04:30:26.051
MATT: Three times. Yeah, so with that, as you're
carrying her there, there's a moment where all of

04:30:26.051 --> 04:30:33.667
a sudden, Vex's eyes open and (deep breath). Vex
is sitting there, looking around, confused,

04:30:33.667 --> 04:30:38.696
catching her breath in Grog's arms as he's bolting
down the steps of the ziggurat.

04:30:38.696 --> 04:30:47.710
LAURA: Grog, you smell terrible. (chuckles
weakly)

04:30:47.710 --> 04:30:49.820
SAM: Maybe we should get out of here.

04:30:49.820 --> 04:30:51.409
TRAVIS: Do something to that little ball.

04:30:51.409 --> 04:31:00.068
MARISHA: I'm alone with the little ball, aren't I?
Okay, I'm going to go up to it. Can I tell any

04:31:00.068 --> 04:31:03.441
type of magical properties from it from looking at
it?

04:31:03.441 --> 04:31:04.978
MATT: Make an arcana check.

04:31:04.978 --> 04:31:10.269
MARISHA: Oh, Jesus. Oh, that's good! 19 total?

04:31:10.269 --> 04:31:18.415
MATT: 19 total. You have no idea what this is. You
haven't seen something like this before. You

04:31:18.415 --> 04:31:24.077
inspect it very closely, and it's literally like
the sphere has been shrunk to this size. You look

04:31:24.077 --> 04:31:26.776
very closely and it looks like it's spinning
impossibly fast in place.

04:31:26.776 --> 04:31:28.214
TRAVIS: Who's still in there?

04:31:28.214 --> 04:31:31.328
SAM: I'm in there. I go up there, too.

04:31:31.328 --> 04:31:33.439
TRAVIS: Check on Lady Shithead.

04:31:33.439 --> 04:31:41.816
SAM: Yeah? Okay, I'm going to turn back and go to
check out Lady Shithead. I don't know why I'm

04:31:41.816 --> 04:31:43.466
still in this room. We should get out of here.

04:31:43.466 --> 04:31:46.550
TALIESIN: I'm going to try and open the doors from
that side to see if there's any way to open them.

04:31:46.550 --> 04:31:48.426
MATT: Make a strength check.

04:31:48.426 --> 04:31:53.441
MARISHA: What is the net of dead bodies doing? Are
they limp?

04:31:53.441 --> 04:31:56.284
MATT: They're just limp. Still in the tapestry,
arms fallen.

04:31:56.284 --> 04:32:00.467
TALIESIN: 11.

04:32:00.467 --> 04:32:03.443
MATT: 11? Doors aren't budging.

04:32:03.443 --> 04:32:05.949
TRAVIS: Here, you take your sister. I'll go back
to the doors.

04:32:05.949 --> 04:32:07.466
LIAM: All right.

04:32:07.466 --> 04:32:09.579
TRAVIS: I go back to the doors and try the doors.

04:32:09.579 --> 04:32:12.170
MATT: Okay. Strength check.

04:32:12.170 --> 04:32:15.227
ASHLEY: Can I try to Cure Wounds again, on Vex?

04:32:15.227 --> 04:32:25.233
MATT: Okay. You run up to Vex as she's in Vax's
arms. Once again, the spell slot is expended, but

04:32:25.233 --> 04:32:31.050
no magic seems to appear. There is some sort of
blockage or void of magic use in this vicinity.

04:32:31.050 --> 04:32:33.440
MARISHA: Even outside of this building?

04:32:33.440 --> 04:32:34.553
TRAVIS: 19.

04:32:34.553 --> 04:32:41.045
MATT: 19? (impact noise) The doors slam open from
the force of Grog's foot, opening the passageway

04:32:41.045 --> 04:32:42.695
inside the room.

04:32:42.695 --> 04:32:44.398
MARISHA: Would my Sunbeam still be up?

04:32:44.398 --> 04:32:46.735
MATT: No, that's passed, for now.

04:32:46.735 --> 04:32:50.011
TRAVIS: Can I make my way over to Scanlan to go
check on Lady Briarwood?

04:32:50.011 --> 04:32:52.923
MATT: Sure. You eventually make your way there at
a full run. You run around the corner and you can

04:32:52.923 --> 04:32:53.956
see her.

04:32:53.956 --> 04:32:54.994
SAM: Alive? Dead?

04:32:54.994 --> 04:33:04.259
MATT: She is on the ground, unconscious, sitting
in this carved hand symbol in the ground.

04:33:04.259 --> 04:33:10.279
SAM: Do we want this girl alive for some reason? I
can't move her.

04:33:10.279 --> 04:33:15.342
TRAVIS: We need to figure out what we're doing
with the little black ball of universal death.

04:33:15.342 --> 04:33:16.774
TALIESIN: Let's get her out of there.

04:33:16.774 --> 04:33:18.427
SAM: Let's just get us out of here.

04:33:18.427 --> 04:33:19.756
TRAVIS: Could we just leave it?

04:33:19.756 --> 04:33:21.850
LAURA: No. Can you put it in a vial?

04:33:21.850 --> 04:33:23.547
SAM: Put it in a vial?

04:33:23.547 --> 04:33:29.687
MARISHA: I pull out a piece of that green glass
that we took from before.

04:33:29.687 --> 04:33:33.137
SAM: Okay, that's smart.

04:33:33.137 --> 04:33:34.600
TRAVIS: Give it a poke.

04:33:34.600 --> 04:33:36.215
MARISHA: I'm going to jam it into it.

04:33:36.215 --> 04:33:37.546
MATT: Okay.

04:33:37.546 --> 04:33:38.757
LAURA: Oh god.

04:33:38.757 --> 04:33:41.921
SAM: Just hit the black hole.

04:33:41.921 --> 04:33:50.037
MATT: Make a strength saving throw.

04:33:50.037 --> 04:33:51.645
TALIESIN: Whoa!

04:33:51.645 --> 04:33:53.450
MARISHA: That's a natural 20.

04:33:53.450 --> 04:34:03.066
MATT: As you take the glass and jam it in there,
the glass, in what seems almost like slow-mo,

04:34:03.066 --> 04:34:11.070
seems to crackle and shatter like brittle stone,
and immediately vanish into the darkness. As your

04:34:11.070 --> 04:34:17.122
hand gets to that point of no resistance, you feel
this immediate, extremely strong suction begin to

04:34:17.122 --> 04:34:27.803
pull towards your hand, and you yank back with all
your might, suffering 18 points of damage as you

04:34:27.803 --> 04:34:32.013
(grunts) pull away from this small spinning orb.

04:34:32.013 --> 04:34:34.210
SAM: Okay, so maybe we don't touch the orb
anymore.

04:34:34.210 --> 04:34:35.721
LAURA: Don't touch the orb.

04:34:35.721 --> 04:34:38.723
MARISHA: Nothing happened to it? Still just--

04:34:38.723 --> 04:34:41.304
MATT: Still just sitting there. A little speck in
space.

04:34:41.304 --> 04:34:44.590
TALIESIN: We're not leaving this thing.

04:34:44.590 --> 04:34:46.719
MARISHA and SAM: What do you mean we're not
leaving it?!

04:34:46.719 --> 04:34:48.752
SAM: What are we going to do to it?

04:34:48.752 --> 04:34:50.075
MARISHA: It's indestructible.

04:34:50.075 --> 04:34:54.555
TRAVIS: We're obviously not equipped. I'll grab
Lady Briarwood and drag her out of the room

04:34:54.555 --> 04:34:55.704
towards the doors.

04:34:55.704 --> 04:34:56.541
MATT: Okay.

04:34:56.541 --> 04:34:59.285
SAM: Wait, what's that-- the horn of--

04:34:59.285 --> 04:35:00.580
TRAVIS: Orcus?

04:35:00.580 --> 04:35:03.388
SAM: The Horn of Orcus? Can that counter-- we
don't have it.

04:35:03.388 --> 04:35:06.623
LAURA: You want to put the two bad things
together?

04:35:06.623 --> 04:35:09.194
SAM: Yeah, maybe they'll become a good thing.

04:35:09.194 --> 04:35:10.211
LAURA: No.

04:35:10.211 --> 04:35:10.874
SAM: No?

04:35:10.874 --> 04:35:12.060
LAURA: Two negatives make a positive?

04:35:12.060 --> 04:35:14.372
SAM: That's what I say to all my women.

04:35:14.372 --> 04:35:21.126
LIAM: I don't know what's going on, but I've got
her and I'm hugging her from behind and turning my

04:35:21.126 --> 04:35:24.485
back towards whatever is in that room. I don't
know what's going on.

04:35:24.485 --> 04:35:25.859
MATT: Okay.

04:35:25.859 --> 04:35:31.139
MARISHA: I can try and tear this whole building
down. I still have my elemental shape. I can go

04:35:31.139 --> 04:35:33.295
earth elemental and start ripping this thing
apart.

04:35:33.295 --> 04:35:35.353
TRAVIS: Bury it like the pharaohs of old?

04:35:35.353 --> 04:35:42.295
SAM: Sure. Why not? Let's get out of here. Do you
want to take Briarwood with us, or bury her in the

04:35:42.295 --> 04:35:43.626
rubble?

04:35:43.626 --> 04:35:45.339
TRAVIS: We can't kill her in here.

04:35:45.339 --> 04:35:49.004
TALIESIN: I'm afraid of what blood will do to that
thing.

04:35:49.004 --> 04:35:51.413
TRAVIS: She kept talking about a sacrifice. We
can't kill her.

04:35:51.413 --> 04:35:53.509
SAM: You think she was going to jump into that
orb?

04:35:53.509 --> 04:35:57.321
TRAVIS: I think she understood she had to give a
life for it.

04:35:57.321 --> 04:35:59.886
MARISHA: I think something was going to come
through that orb.

04:35:59.886 --> 04:36:00.977
LAURA: Yeah.

04:36:00.977 --> 04:36:05.411
LIAM: Let's drag her out of here. Percy, you can
shoot her in the head a hundred yards from here.

04:36:05.411 --> 04:36:08.307
TRAVIS: And then you can bury it once we're out of
the way.

04:36:08.307 --> 04:36:10.127
MARISHA: Okay.

04:36:10.127 --> 04:36:13.099
TRAVIS: I drag her out of the room and toward the
steps.

04:36:13.099 --> 04:36:17.900
MATT: Okay. As you're holding her in your arms,
what's everyone doing?

04:36:17.900 --> 04:36:19.546
MARISHA: Everyone, get out.

04:36:19.546 --> 04:36:22.545
LIAM: I'm picking up my sister and lurching after
Grog.

04:36:22.545 --> 04:36:23.723
LAURA: I can walk.

04:36:23.723 --> 04:36:25.701
LIAM: I'm picking you up, and I'm lurching after
Grog!

04:36:25.701 --> 04:36:31.442
MATT: So as Grog rushes down the steps of the
ziggurat, clutching the unconscious and bleeding

04:36:31.442 --> 04:36:39.084
body of Lady Delilah Briarwood. Vax rushing
behind, carrying the barely-conscious, limp body

04:36:39.084 --> 04:36:46.592
of Vex'ahlia, the rest of you racing out. You,
your hand bloodied from the terrible force of

04:36:46.592 --> 04:36:52.600
whatever that was. You go charging down the steps
of the ziggurat. Is anyone taking Cassandra, or

04:36:52.600 --> 04:36:53.652
are you leaving her behind?

04:36:53.652 --> 04:36:54.884
TALIESIN: I'm taking Cassandra.

04:36:54.884 --> 04:36:57.792
MATT: You reach over and pick up Cassandra, put
her over your shoulder, and you begin racing down

04:36:57.792 --> 04:36:59.251
the front of the ziggurat steps.

04:36:59.251 --> 04:37:01.449
MARISHA: Am I tearing this place down?

04:37:01.449 --> 04:37:03.215
TRAVIS: Not yet. Not until we're out of here.

04:37:03.215 --> 04:37:05.552
MARISHA: I'll stay behind.

04:37:05.552 --> 04:37:06.829
MATT: You stay behind?

04:37:06.829 --> 04:37:09.234
TRAVIS: Do you have to be there to do it?

04:37:09.234 --> 04:37:12.397
MARISHA: Being an earth elemental and ripping it
apart.

04:37:12.397 --> 04:37:13.759
LIAM: She's doing it physically.

04:37:13.759 --> 04:37:16.287
TRAVIS: Well, let's all get to the point where
it's not going to collapse on us.

04:37:16.287 --> 04:37:19.676
TALIESIN: Why don't we just open up the acid and
let it pour down in there.

04:37:19.676 --> 04:37:21.011
SAM: Where is that?

04:37:21.011 --> 04:37:22.336
LAURA: That's so far away.

04:37:22.336 --> 04:37:26.569
TALIESIN: We have to go that way, anyway. Once we
get there, let's open the spigot, point it towards

04:37:26.569 --> 04:37:28.326
the doors, and let it do its work.

04:37:28.326 --> 04:37:32.032
MARISHA: I don't know if that's enough acid to
take down and destroy a thing.

04:37:32.032 --> 04:37:36.398
LAURA: Might as well try it. Do we have any acid?
You have acid, can we pour it?

04:37:36.398 --> 04:37:38.068
TRAVIS: It's like three little acid vials.

04:37:38.068 --> 04:37:39.951
LIAM: We've got acid from a tube.

04:37:39.951 --> 04:37:44.498
SAM: Why don't we just seal up the hole and get
out of here?

04:37:44.498 --> 04:37:49.505
LIAM: Let's get out of here. Keyleth, it's a good
idea. Destroy the temple.

04:37:49.505 --> 04:37:54.477
TALIESIN: Do some damage to the temple, and then
once we're all the way out, we'll open the acid.

04:37:54.477 --> 04:37:57.877
MARISHA: Do we want to leave a spinning black hole
of death under the city?

04:37:57.877 --> 04:38:03.029
TALIESIN: It could just swallow the entire city
and everybody could die. This is my problem, at

04:38:03.029 --> 04:38:04.399
the moment.

04:38:04.399 --> 04:38:09.073
MARISHA: You guys go. I'm going to tear it down.
I'll be okay. I'll meet you there.

04:38:09.073 --> 04:38:11.152
LAURA: What?

04:38:11.152 --> 04:38:12.452
ASHLEY: No.

04:38:12.452 --> 04:38:15.160
TALIESIN: She can earth shape. She'll be fine.

04:38:15.160 --> 04:38:24.328
LIAM: I push my sister into Grog's massive arms
because he can hold fucking five people, and I

04:38:24.328 --> 04:38:26.346
start running back towards the ziggurat.

04:38:26.346 --> 04:38:27.577
MATT: Okay.

04:38:27.577 --> 04:38:29.664
LAURA: I'm laying on top of Lady Briarwood right
now.

04:38:29.664 --> 04:38:30.828
LIAM: Yes. Yes, you are.

04:38:30.828 --> 04:38:32.192
LAURA: Great.

04:38:32.192 --> 04:38:34.757
TALIESIN: 70 percent of her, at the very least.

04:38:34.757 --> 04:38:38.041
MARISHA: I stand at the top of the temple, and I
wait to see them go out of range.

04:38:38.041 --> 04:38:44.031
MATT: Okay. They all begin to step down the bottom
of the stairs, except for Vax, who begins running

04:38:44.031 --> 04:38:45.466
back up the steps towards you.

04:38:45.466 --> 04:38:52.750
MARISHA: Vax, go. No. Go.

04:38:52.750 --> 04:38:55.123
LIAM: Whatever you're going to do, just fucking do
it.

04:38:55.123 --> 04:39:02.722
MARISHA: I concentrate for a minute, and I go into
the ground.

04:39:02.722 --> 04:39:08.979
MATT: As you focus your attention towards your
earthen core and triggering the transformation

04:39:08.979 --> 04:39:12.735
effect, nothing happens.

04:39:12.735 --> 04:39:14.248
LAURA: Magic. It kills all magic!

04:39:14.248 --> 04:39:15.361
MARISHA: Even Beast Shape?

04:39:15.361 --> 04:39:16.739
MATT: It's a magical transformation.

04:39:16.739 --> 04:39:20.089
MARISHA: Never mind! Run!

04:39:20.089 --> 04:39:21.531
(laughter)

04:39:21.531 --> 04:39:22.747
MARISHA: Fuck it! Run.

04:39:22.747 --> 04:39:23.588
TRAVIS: We all leave.

04:39:23.588 --> 04:39:25.763
LAURA: Can you try pouring acid on the thingy?

04:39:25.763 --> 04:39:27.969
TALIESIN: I'm going to do it once we're out. We're
just going to go.

04:39:27.969 --> 04:39:30.969
MATT: As Vox Machina charges down the front of the
steps of the ziggurat,

04:39:30.969 --> 04:39:33.419
we'll call that for the night.

04:39:33.419 --> 04:39:35.987
(groaning)

04:39:35.987 --> 04:39:37.978
LAURA: And I rolled a one right as that final.

04:39:37.978 --> 04:39:39.416
LIAM: For no reason.

04:39:39.416 --> 04:39:40.821
SAM: We killed the Briarwoods.

04:39:40.821 --> 04:39:42.234
TALIESIN: Well, one and a half of them.

04:39:42.234 --> 04:39:44.936
SAM: We didn't die. Yet.

04:39:44.936 --> 04:39:46.073
LAURA and MARISHA: Oh my god.

04:39:46.073 --> 04:39:51.593
LAURA: I can't believe I almost died again from
that damn death ray!

04:39:51.593 --> 04:39:53.713
MARISHA: By one point.

04:39:53.713 --> 04:39:58.943
TRAVIS: So if you had rolled 76 points of necrotic
damage?

04:39:58.943 --> 04:40:01.799
MATT: She'd have been dead instantly and then come
back as a zombie in the next round.

04:40:01.799 --> 04:40:03.121
MARISHA: And would become what?

04:40:03.121 --> 04:40:05.867
LAURA: If I hadn't taken that potion right before
I leapt off--

04:40:05.867 --> 04:40:07.078
MATT: You would have been dead.

04:40:07.078 --> 04:40:10.091
MARISHA: Thank god you took that fucking potion!

04:40:10.091 --> 04:40:13.624
MATT: That went a little longer than anticipated.

04:40:13.624 --> 04:40:14.963
LIAM: You're a bad man!

04:40:14.963 --> 04:41:00.788
[no audio]

04:41:00.788 --> 04:41:02.533
(laughter)

04:41:02.533 --> 04:41:04.097
MARISHA: I think Pike's playlist is up right now.

04:41:04.097 --> 04:41:05.465
TALIESIN: Hey!

04:41:05.465 --> 04:41:08.841
SAM: Hey, Percy? How much does that comic cost?

04:41:08.841 --> 04:41:10.540
TALIESIN: That comic is--

04:41:10.540 --> 04:41:11.637
SAM: Free.

04:41:11.637 --> 04:41:14.980
TALIESIN: Was free. After this weekend, it's one
healing potion.

04:41:14.980 --> 04:41:17.418
MARISHA: That won't work.

04:41:17.418 --> 04:41:19.673
TALIESIN: Goddamn it.

04:41:19.673 --> 04:41:21.230
LAURA: A bunch of wasted healing potions.

04:41:21.230 --> 04:41:24.641
MATT: Okay, guys. Thank you all so much for your
patience, for your diligence, for watching this

04:41:24.641 --> 04:41:25.988
extremely--

04:41:25.988 --> 04:41:26.920
LAURA: Long.

04:41:26.920 --> 04:41:30.479
MATT: Long, dark episode. We'll see you next week.
Is it Thursday yet?

04:41:30.479 --> 04:41:32.452
